ch of other people were too.","index":746,"end_time":2738.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2732.949,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":747,"end_time":2738.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2738.39,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"From the past.","index":748,"end_time":2739.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2739.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I just kind of like.","index":749,"end_time":2741.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2739.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Stopped.","index":750,"end_time":2743.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2743.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It and then like, put it back in.","index":751,"end_time":2744.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2743.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think what I might do is I might cancel the entire series when I cancel next week''s meeting.","index":752,"end_time":2751.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2744.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then I''m going to start fresh for the new year.","index":753,"end_time":2755.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2752.48,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":754,"end_time":2756.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2755.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And create a new series for Wednesday.","index":755,"end_time":2759.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2756.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"January 7th.","index":756,"end_time":2760.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2759.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Repeats weekly.","index":757,"end_time":2762.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2761.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And it''s you, me, Sam, and Colin.","index":758,"end_time":2766.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2762.48,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":759,"end_time":2768.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2767.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Cool.","index":760,"end_time":2769.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2769.05,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":761,"end_time":2770.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2769.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, wait, one more thing.","index":762,"end_time":2777.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2776.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Invoice for December.","index":763,"end_time":2780.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2778.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Does the invoice for December cover services that take place in that month.","index":764,"end_time":2791.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2784.41,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or is it the other way?","index":765,"end_time":2796.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2794.82,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''ll have to check.","index":766,"end_time":2799.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2798.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, no worries.","index":767,"end_time":2800.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2799.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, because I do have the invoice from December.","index":768,"end_time":2803.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2800.66,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I haven''t submitted it yet.","index":769,"end_time":2804.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2803.06,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, but I don''t know if.","index":770,"end_time":2805.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2804.26,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I mean, now that I can send it to you if you want it.","index":771,"end_time":2807.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2805.26,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But it''s the one you sent me.","index":772,"end_time":2809.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2807.58,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"6,500.","index":773,"end_time":2811.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2810.9,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":774,"end_time":2813.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2812.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right.","index":775,"end_time":2814.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2813.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"No question then.","index":776,"end_time":2814.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2814.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"There''s nothing to follow up on then.","index":777,"end_time":2816.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2814.82,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If we have that invoice, we just need to pop it in to our co op thing for reimbursement.","index":778,"end_time":2821.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2816.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I think a couple weeks ago Tristan sent the remaining ones for 2025.","index":779,"end_time":2827.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2822.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right?","index":780,"end_time":2828.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2827.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":781,"end_time":2831.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2829.83,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"October, November, December.","index":782,"end_time":2833.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2832.47,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":783,"end_time":2835.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2833.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":784,"end_time":2836.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2835.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":785,"end_time":2837.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2837.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":786,"end_time":2840.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2839.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":787,"end_time":2841.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2840.71,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":788,"end_time":2842.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2841.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have a wonderful holiday.","index":789,"end_time":2844.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2842.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":790,"end_time":2844.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2844.23,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Merry Christmas, everything.","index":791,"end_time":2847.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2846.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":792,"end_time":2848.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2847.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":793,"end_time":2849.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2848.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Bye.","index":794,"end_time":2851.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2851.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Bye.","index":795,"end_time":2851.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2851.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Bye.","index":796,"end_time":2852.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2852.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"dateString":"2025-12-17T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"rpontbriand@icorps.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_MDUyZTNiYTMtMTMxNi00YWUyLWI0MjktZjNiZjI1NWU5MGMy@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28\",\"Oid\":\"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07\"}","participants":["joe.michalowski@marketersindemand.com,mia.mixan@newnorth.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,dallion.duran-ballen@marketersindemand.com,rpontbriand@icorps.com,sbagnall@icorps.com","joe.michalowski@marketersindemand.com","fred@fireflies.ai","mia.mixan@newnorth.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","dallion.duran-ballen@marketersindemand.com","sbagnall@icorps.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KCHT10AD3QSS4S71ZZBNETX5","organizer_email":"rpontbriand@icorps.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Launched AI Readiness ABM campaign; 60 contacts reached third email in the drip sequence.","Added dashboard visibility into Smartlead; Ruby to share access for real-time lead tracking.","Clarified inbound lead source confusion with Kristin follow-up process and lifecycle tagging.","Team discussed formalizing a ''meeting requested'' status for high-intent LinkedIn leads.","Agreed to schedule marketing operations alignment meeting post-holidays to refine lead stages."],"highlights":[{"quote":"This is a lead who filled out a Contact Us form for all intents and purposes.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"quote":"The campaign is prioritizing follow-up with people who’ve already received the first email.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"Retargeting works... we just closed a client that’s been in HubSpot for nine years.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"topics":["abm","lead routing","tracking","reporting","seo"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-19T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Lead Management**\n\nThe team confirmed strong progress on the **AI Readiness assessment ABM campaign**, with **22 points delivered in December** and **59 points of management tasks remaining** for the month (08:31).  \n- **Ruby Pontbriand** highlighted the campaign’s focus on a smaller, prioritized pool of contacts, sending up to the **third email to 60 people** so far, emphasizing timely follow-ups rather than mass outreach.  \n- **Nathalie Mintjens** reported the campaign targets about **873 contacts total**, with the system sending personalized drip emails rather than bulk blasts, improving engagement tracking.  \n- Ruby requested access to the campaign dashboard to better visualize contact stages and improve sales coordination; Nathalie agreed to share login details for enhanced transparency (12:04).  \n- They discussed a recent lead from the nurture campaign who requested a sales meeting via the free IT checkup form, illustrating the campaign’s ability to generate qualified sales opportunities beyond content downloads (14:42).  \n- Ruby flagged the need to better differentiate lead types in the CRM, suggesting clearer labels like “meeting requested” to distinguish hand-raisers from content downloaders, improving sales follow-up prioritization (19:20).  \n- Samuel and Ruby debated lifecycle stage definitions: Ruby noted sales prefers to treat LinkedIn leads differently, reserving MQL status for leads showing reciprocal interest post-contact, while Samuel advocated for keeping these as MQLs to maintain marketing alignment (22:26).  \n- Ruby proposed a marketing operations review early in the new year to clarify lead lifecycle stages and definitions, aiming to align marketing and sales perspectives for lead qualification and reporting (26:17).  \n- Ruby emphasized that despite different lead types, all leads still require follow-up, but sales should focus more on leads explicitly requesting meetings, ensuring efficient use of Kristen’s time (29:54).  \n- Ruby shared a success story of a client converted after years of content nurture, proving the value of sustained engagement and multi-touch lead development (32:20).\n\n## **Lead Lifecycle and CRM Process Improvements**\n\nClarifying lead categories and follow-up workflows is critical for smooth sales-marketing handoff and accurate reporting (23:17).  \n- Ruby suggested adding a “meeting requested” status in the CRM to trigger notifications similar to website form fills, alerting sales teams promptly and unifying lead handling processes (34:03).  \n- Nathalie agreed to explore developer options for mimicking website form notification workflows for LinkedIn form fills, improving visibility and response times (35:53).  \n- Samuel offered to share example workflows from their system to aid development and alignment on notification routing (37:00).  \n- Ruby plans to cancel and reset recurring meetings in January, creating a streamlined weekly process involving **Samuel, Nathalie, Ruby, and Colin** to maintain ongoing coordination (45:55).  \n- Invoice processing was briefly confirmed, with December invoices covering that month’s services and no pending follow-ups, ensuring financial clarity (46:16).\n\n## **SEO Strategy and Website Maintenance**\n\nThe SEO strategy focuses on targeting **low difficulty, high-volume keywords** selected through **Ahrefs** to improve rankings and drive relevant traffic to localized pages (38:30).  \n- Nathalie will send Jeff a detailed keyword list per page with monthly search volumes and difficulty scores, explaining the rationale to satisfy his thorough review needs (41:49).  \n- Ruby confirmed this transparency will help Jeff track SEO progress effectively and validate keyword targeting decisions (42:12).  \n- They agreed that keyword-driven pages will appear in relevant regional searches, avoiding mismatches like Boston results showing for Philadelphia queries (39:38).  \n- Ruby raised concern over broken links leading to **404 errors**, suggesting this become part of ongoing website upkeep and management tasks to preserve site health (42:41).  \n- Nathalie noted blog posts are likely the main source of outdated links due to landing page updates, and plans to coordinate with web team to scan and fix these errors to maintain user experience and SEO integrity (43:38).\n\n## **Scheduling and Team Coordination**\n\nThe team agreed to pause meetings during the holiday weeks, resuming the regular cadence on **Wednesday, January 7th**, to ensure productivity without overloading team members during vacation periods (44:40).  \n- Nathalie will send scheduling links for any interim communications, but the main working rhythm will pause to accommodate planned absences (44:45).  \n- Ruby confirmed updating the meeting invite list to include key personnel and streamline participation for the new year’s workflow (45:20).","outline":null,"keywords":["AI Readiness","Marketing Qualified Leads","Lead Management","SEO Keyword Strategy","LinkedIn Campaign","Meeting Scheduling"],"overview":"- **AI Readiness Campaign Progress:** 22 points delivered in December; 59 tasks left for completion.  \n- **Targeted Email Strategy:** Focus on 873 contacts with personalized drip emails improving engagement and follow-up.  \n- **Lead Type Differentiation:** Suggestions made for clearer CRM labels like “meeting requested” for better sales prioritization.  \n- **Lead Lifecycle Review Proposal:** Marketing operations review suggested for early January to align definitions of lead qualification.  \n- **SEO Strategy Focus:** Targeting low difficulty, high-volume keywords to improve search rankings and relevant traffic.  \n- **Meeting Schedule Adjustments:** Meetings paused during holidays, resuming January 7th to balance workload and team absences.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nProvide Ruby Pontbriand with login credentials for the AI readiness campaign dashboard to increase transparency (12:09)\nExplore options with developers to implement notification workflows mimicking website form fills for LinkedIn meeting requests (35:53)\nSend Jeff a detailed recap email on SEO keyword targeting, including monthly search volume, difficulty, and rationale (41:49)\nPerform a website audit to identify and fix 404 errors, focusing on blog post links, coordinating with web support team (43:39)\nCoordinate scheduling by sending out a scheduling link for next week and confirm no meetings during Nathalie’s absence (44:10)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nCancel the existing recurring meeting series and create a fresh weekly series starting January 7th including Sam, Nathalie, Ruby, and Colin (45:43)\nReview and modify the contact list view (e.g., adding columns) to better distinguish between lead campaigns like Free IT Checkup vs. Smart IT Budget guide for improved qualification clarity (15:47)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nShare the workflow example used for discovery meeting booked notifications to help design the LinkedIn meeting request notification (37:06)\nSubmit the December invoice for reimbursement processing (46:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"30fc9750-97b7-430a-9be8-1e032b696ee3","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
