INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: iCorps + New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Campaign Performance and Lead Management**

The team confirmed strong progress on the **AI Readiness assessment ABM campaign**, with **22 points delivered in December** and **59 points of management tasks remaining** for the month (08:31).  
- **Ruby Pontbriand** highlighted the campaign’s focus on a smaller, prioritized pool of contacts, sending up to the **third email to 60 people** so far, emphasizing timely follow-ups rather than mass outreach.  
- **Nathalie Mintjens** reported the campaign targets about **873 contacts total**, with the system sending personalized drip emails rather than bulk blasts, improving engagement tracking.  
- Ruby requested access to the campaign dashboard to better visualize contact stages and improve sales coordination; Nathalie agreed to share login details for enhanced transparency (12:04).  
- They discussed a recent lead from the nurture campaign who requested a sales meeting via the free IT checkup form, illustrating the campaign’s ability to generate qualified sales opportunities beyond content downloads (14:42).  
- Ruby flagged the need to better differentiate lead types in the CRM, suggesting clearer labels like “meeting requested” to distinguish hand-raisers from content downloaders, improving sales follow-up prioritization (19:20).  
- Samuel and Ruby debated lifecycle stage definitions: Ruby noted sales prefers to treat LinkedIn leads differently, reserving MQL status for leads showing reciprocal interest post-contact, while Samuel advocated for keeping these as MQLs to maintain marketing alignment (22:26).  
- Ruby proposed a marketing operations review early in the new year to clarify lead lifecycle stages and definitions, aiming to align marketing and sales perspectives for lead qualification and reporting (26:17).  
- Ruby emphasized that despite different lead types, all leads still require follow-up, but sales should focus more on leads explicitly requesting meetings, ensuring efficient use of Kristen’s time (29:54).  
- Ruby shared a success story of a client converted after years of content nurture, proving the value of sustained engagement and multi-touch lead development (32:20).

## **Lead Lifecycle and CRM Process Improvements**

Clarifying lead categories and follow-up workflows is critical for smooth sales-marketing handoff and accurate reporting (23:17).  
- Ruby suggested adding a “meeting requested” status in the CRM to trigger notifications similar to website form fills, alerting sales teams promptly and unifying lead handling processes (34:03).  
- Nathalie agreed to explore developer options for mimicking website form notification workflows for LinkedIn form fills, improving visibility and response times (35:53).  
- Samuel offered to share example workflows from their system to aid development and alignment on notification routing (37:00).  
- Ruby plans to cancel and reset recurring meetings in January, creating a streamlined weekly process involving **Samuel, Nathalie, Ruby, and Colin** to maintain ongoing coordination (45:55).  
- Invoice processing was briefly confirmed, with December invoices covering that month’s services and no pending follow-ups, ensuring financial clarity (46:16).

## **SEO Strategy and Website Maintenance**

The SEO strategy focuses on targeting **low difficulty, high-volume keywords** selected through **Ahrefs** to improve rankings and drive relevant traffic to localized pages (38:30).  
- Nathalie will send Jeff a detailed keyword list per page with monthly search volumes and difficulty scores, explaining the rationale to satisfy his thorough review needs (41:49).  
- Ruby confirmed this transparency will help Jeff track SEO progress effectively and validate keyword targeting decisions (42:12).  
- They agreed that keyword-driven pages will appear in relevant regional searches, avoiding mismatches like Boston results showing for Philadelphia queries (39:38).  
- Ruby raised concern over broken links leading to **404 errors**, suggesting this become part of ongoing website upkeep and management tasks to preserve site health (42:41).  
- Nathalie noted blog posts are likely the main source of outdated links due to landing page updates, and plans to coordinate with web team to scan and fix these errors to maintain user experience and SEO integrity (43:38).

## **Scheduling and Team Coordination**

The team agreed to pause meetings during the holiday weeks, resuming the regular cadence on **Wednesday, January 7th**, to ensure productivity without overloading team members during vacation periods (44:40).  
- Nathalie will send scheduling links for any interim communications, but the main working rhythm will pause to accommodate planned absences (44:45).  
- Ruby confirmed updating the meeting invite list to include key personnel and streamline participation for the new year’s workflow (45:20).',
  '2025-12-17 15:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide Ruby Pontbriand with login credentials for the AI readiness campaign dashboard to increase transparency (12:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Explore options with developers to implement notification workflows mimicking website form fills for LinkedIn meeting requests (35:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Send Jeff a detailed recap email on SEO keyword targeting, including monthly search volume, difficulty, and rationale (41:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Perform a website audit to identify and fix 404 errors, focusing on blog post links, coordinating with web support team (43:39)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate scheduling by sending out a scheduling link for next week and confirm no meetings during Nathalie’s absence (44:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Cancel the existing recurring meeting series and create a fresh weekly series starting January 7th including Sam, Nathalie, Ruby, and Colin (45:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and modify the contact list view (e.g., adding columns) to better distinguish between lead campaigns like Free IT Checkup vs. Smart IT Budget guide for improved qualification clarity (15:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Share the workflow example used for discovery meeting booked notifications to help design the LinkedIn meeting request notification (37:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Submit the December invoice for reimbursement processing (46:40)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect (2025-12-18 13:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '4995ddd4-5ee9-4673-9a9b-c773e431992a',
    '2025-12-18 13:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KC71QMDMJ47DYVJHRBB3MZ8S',
    'Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
    '{"Shane Billings","Nathalie Mintjens","Keenan Toward","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1695,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1',
    '{"id":"01KC71QMDMJ47DYVJHRBB3MZ8S","title":"Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect","summary":{"notes":"## **Product Demo and Onboarding Development**\n\nThe demos confirmed strong customer interest but highlighted a critical need for a structured onboarding and support package to ease product adoption.\n\n- **Keenan Toward reported that both demos engaged customers deeply, revealing a key barrier: clients struggle to train their teams to use the product effectively, prompting the creation of a tiered onboarding support package** offering self-led and fully managed options (02:09).  \n    - This package aims to address launch hesitancy by providing tailored training and support based on team size and client preference.  \n    - Keenan emphasized that onboarding support will likely become about 30% of demo conversations, reflecting its importance in closing deals.  \n    - The plan is to add this onboarding segment visibly on the homepage once developed, increasing transparency and confidence for prospects.  \n    - Noelani from 212Dental, a demo participant, exemplified this need due to staffing shortages and hiring challenges.  \n\n- **Keenan also identified two demo features that resonated most: the automated email scoreboard update and the main dashboard scoreboard, which provide quick team performance insights and accountability tracking** (03:37).  \n    - Customers showed interest in enhanced reporting features detailing request types and responsibility assignments, signaling a demand for deeper data visibility.  \n    - Natalie Mintjens suggested updating website imagery to better showcase these features alongside the onboarding offering to align marketing with demo feedback.  \n    - Shane Billings and Nathalie discussed intermittent site cache issues affecting visibility of recent updates, with Shane planning to investigate developer-side solutions (06:16).  \n\n- **Keenan recommended maintaining healthcare as the broader target market while keeping dental as the specialty background, cautioning against mixed messaging that confuses prospects** (07:55).  \n    - The team agreed to focus current marketing on dental to control costs but consider a healthcare landing page later, balancing market reach and budget constraints.  \n    - Shane stressed the priority remains closing paying clients before expanding target segments (10:01).  \n\n## **Marketing Strategy and Website Performance**\n\nMarketing is focused on refining messaging and targeting to improve lead quality, engagement, and conversion while managing costs.\n\n- **LinkedIn ad campaigns tightened targeting to 1,800 prospects, causing cost-per-click to rise but improving lead quality, though conversion goals have yet to be met**; the paid media specialist recommended warming audiences with website visit campaigns before retargeting with lead-gen ads (19:19).  \n    - Shane accepted paying up to **$20 per click** if those clicks convert but noted the current campaigns fail to convert adequately (20:42).  \n    - Nathalie proposed expanding targeting slightly to balance cost and reach, aiming to find an optimal audience size (20:50).  \n\n- **Keenan plans to leverage LinkedIn data by reaching out personally to prospects who engaged with the site and ads once his LinkedIn account is linked to the tool, targeting follow-up conversations to drive demos** (21:07).  \n    - Shane has proactively contacted some companies based on click data, increasing direct engagement efforts (22:10).  \n    - Keenan will complete LinkedIn setup by Tuesday and then start outreach as a top priority (14:48, 22:49).  \n\n- **Website traffic metrics show positive momentum, with a 37% increase in visitors and 27% rise in page views over the last 30 days, driven mainly by direct traffic and account-based marketing (ABM)** (23:04).  \n    - The case study page is notably high-performing, indicating trust-building content appeals to visitors.  \n    - The team will monitor bounce rates to assess if refreshed homepage messaging improves visitor engagement and retention.  \n\n- **Social media content reviews confirmed most posts are engaging and aligned with messaging; Keenan emphasized the importance of keeping posts consistent with homepage messaging and demo insights to reinforce value propositions around coaching, reporting, and compliance** (15:39).  \n    - Minor video editing tweaks were noted but deemed not critical to delay posting.  \n    - Brad’s podcast content is valuable for knowledge sharing and should be incorporated carefully into the messaging mix.  \n\n## **Resource and Partnership Management**\n\nThe partnership is committed to staying within scope and focusing effort where it yields the best return, with a reset on overage balances.\n\n- **Colin Costigan announced that the outstanding negative balance of 470 points, equivalent to approximately $47,000 in out-of-scope work, will be forgiven as a goodwill gesture to support continued partnership** (24:01).  \n    - Moving forward, the team will work within a fixed monthly scope, presenting plans in spreadsheets with flexibility to swap tasks as priorities shift.  \n    - Shane appreciated this approach, highlighting the need to prioritize high-return activities due to limited budget and stressed creativity in maximizing impact with fewer resources (25:17).  \n\n- **Colin reinforced the strategy to expand LinkedIn targeting within reason to reduce cost per engagement and increase velocity through marketing channels, leveraging the team’s expertise in scrappy, efficient growth tactics** (26:01).  \n    - Shane welcomed this mindset, emphasizing disciplined focus on what works to accelerate closed deals, which are critical to business survival (26:54).  \n\n## **Sales Enablement and Messaging Alignment**\n\nSales demos and marketing must align tightly around client pain points to increase conversion rates.\n\n- **Keenan shared that prospects consistently describe team communication challenges, reliance on spreadsheets, and non-compliant messaging as core problems, positioning the product as a coaching and management tool to fix these behaviors** (17:15).  \n    - This insight shapes the narrative for demos and social messaging to emphasize reporting, coaching, and request tracking as key differentiators.  \n    - Recording future demos is planned to capture customer interactions for ongoing messaging refinement (18:32).  \n    - Nathalie noted that evolving messaging based on demo patterns will strengthen marketing effectiveness over time.  \n\n- **Keenan’s personal demo approach includes sharing his dental industry background and tailoring conversations to specific client challenges, enhancing credibility and relevance** (16:50).  \n    - This approach was validated by demo feedback and will continue to guide sales training and content development.  \n\n## **Operational Execution and Timelines**\n\nKey deliverables are progressing with clear next steps and timelines aimed at supporting sales and marketing efforts.\n\n- **Keenan will finalize LinkedIn account linkage and begin outreach by Tuesday as his top priority, integrating the platform into ongoing lead engagement** (14:48, 22:49).  \n- **The onboarding and support package development is targeted for completion next week, with follow-up review and homepage update to follow, coordinated via email due to holiday schedules** (27:33).  \n- **Natalie will continue to monitor website analytics and campaign performance post-homepage update to measure impact on engagement and lead quality** (23:04).  \n- **The team agreed to keep social content postings aligned with homepage messaging and demo insights to maintain consistency and reinforce value propositions** (15:39).  \n\nThese coordinated efforts aim to reduce onboarding objections, improve lead conversion, and accelerate closed deals before year-end.","outline":null,"keywords":["Onboarding","Demo Feedback","LinkedIn Outreach","Website Updates","Marketing Strategy","Ad Campaigns"],"overview":"- **Customer Interest:** Demos indicated strong interest but revealed onboarding support is crucial for effective product adoption.\n\n- **Onboarding Package:** A tiered onboarding support package will offer tailored training based on team size and preferences.\n\n- **Marketing Focus:** LinkedIn ads optimized targeting, improving lead quality but aiming for better conversion rates despite rising costs.\n\n- **Website Traffic Growth:** Recent metrics show a 37% visitor increase, primarily due to direct traffic and successful account-based marketing strategies.\n\n- **Sales Messaging Alignment:** Teams must address core client pain points and enhance demos to increase conversions and reinforce product value.\n\n- **Action Plans:** Key deliverables include onboarding package completion and LinkedIn outreach, improving lead engagement and sales efforts.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nDevelop a tiered onboarding and support package for customers to ease product launch in teams (02:09)\nLink LinkedIn account to the Gripon tool early next week after finalizing personal job situation (13:20)\nReview and approve minor edits to Brad’s social post video before posting (15:46)\nAlign all future social posts and messaging to reflect homepage messaging and demo customer needs focusing on coaching, reporting, and request handling (17:15)\nRecord future demos for internal review and messaging refinement (18:32)\nResume LinkedIn outreach to warm leads after website updates and LinkedIn integration (21:05)\nSend LinkedIn account linking details to Natalie Mintjens by Tuesday following holiday week (27:31)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nAssist Keenan with any issues linking his LinkedIn account to the tool (13:06)\nContinue monitoring LinkedIn ad campaigns and adjust targeting to balance audience size and cost per click (19:19)\nMonitor website analytics focusing on impact of new homepage messaging on visitor engagement and bounce rates (23:04)\nProvide Keenan with social post schedules and instructions (14:06)\nCollaborate with team through the holidays on onboarding/support plan and LinkedIn outreach coordination (27:31)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nFollow up with developers to resolve website caching issues causing some users to see old site version (07:10)\nSupport marketing strategy focusing on scrappy, high-impact campaigns to generate paying customers (25:44)\nEngage in LinkedIn outreach to contacts identified from ad campaign data (22:10)\nCollaborate with team to ensure monthly scope and balance point overage (24:53)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize internal agreement to reset negative points balance and establish monthly scoped plans to control overage (24:01)\nProvide monthly spreadsheets detailing scope and points usage for transparency and planning (24:53)\nAssist team with strategy for optimizing LinkedIn audience size and campaign efficiency (26:31)\n"},"duration":28.25,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Shane Billings"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Keenan Toward"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"That''s weird.","index":0,"end_time":4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.36,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m going to try to get off and rejoin.","index":1,"end_time":7.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.24,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s see what happens.","index":2,"end_time":8.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.12,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":3,"end_time":8.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey, Keenan, how are you?","index":4,"end_time":14.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":12.4,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Good, how are you?","index":5,"end_time":16.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m doing well.","index":6,"end_time":17.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":16.56,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Ah.","index":7,"end_time":43.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I haven''t a clue.","index":8,"end_time":45.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.25,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But you guys can hear me, right?","index":9,"end_time":50.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, we can hear you all.","index":10,"end_time":53.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":11,"end_time":54.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just so you know, I may be pulled away.","index":12,"end_time":61.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t think I will, but I may get a phone call because I get random calls from my boss and I gotta take those, so.","index":13,"end_time":70.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":14,"end_time":71.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":15,"end_time":72.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Will Dave be joining?","index":16,"end_time":75.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":17,"end_time":76.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We got.","index":18,"end_time":78.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We got the people we need, though.","index":19,"end_time":80.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, Perfect.","index":20,"end_time":86.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":21,"end_time":90.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just looking at your points and then I think at the end we can also.","index":22,"end_time":94.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know you had the question last week about the backlog of points, so we can discuss that at the end as well.","index":23,"end_time":100.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But just looking at December.","index":24,"end_time":101.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we have 28 so far delivered, getting the social content done and developing the new LinkedIn AD package.","index":25,"end_time":111.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we have 46 more in working, which are your monthly management tasks, And then update on the campaign.","index":26,"end_time":122.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I wanted to see how the two demos went last week, Keenan.","index":27,"end_time":127.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So both demos, the customers, they really engage with the product and what the product does for them.","index":28,"end_time":135.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.43,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that''s why I came back to you guys with the adjustments on what we wanted to see on the website.","index":29,"end_time":140.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":135.35,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I basically took the points of engagement from both the demos that really drew the customers in and created conversation, and that''s what I adjusted onto the website.","index":30,"end_time":154.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":140.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So they both went really well.","index":31,"end_time":158.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"One customer really wants to start, but what we''re learning is we need to develop an onboarding training support for them to be able to get started.","index":32,"end_time":171.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":159.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It seemed like for both of them, one of the challenges they would face is trying to launch the product within their teams, train their teams and get their teams utilizing the product.","index":33,"end_time":182.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.19,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so that''s what I''m in the process of now, is developing an onboarding package with a tiered system for basically what kind of support they would like to have if they.","index":34,"end_time":194.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":183.32,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"If they''re an organization that has enough people that wants to have somebody lead and train their teams and deliver expectations, or if they''re an organization that would like us to handle that for them.","index":35,"end_time":205.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.84,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So we''re going to offer both.","index":36,"end_time":207.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.24,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s the next step in what I''m trying to put together for this.","index":37,"end_time":211.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.92,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But they actually both went really well.","index":38,"end_time":214.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.96,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Customers were engaged.","index":39,"end_time":216.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.04,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The demo piece is very big.","index":40,"end_time":221.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.68,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And really the two things that I think we''d want to show as many places as possible is one, there''s the email that you get from a grip on when you''re signed up that gives you your scoreboard.","index":41,"end_time":235.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.6,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s a huge coaching tool because it allows the managers and the leaders in the organization to check an email very quickly and understand, hey, we have a lot of things that have not been done.","index":42,"end_time":246.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I need to make a call today or, hey, everything looks good.","index":43,"end_time":249.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.27,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We''re on track.","index":44,"end_time":250.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.31,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I can go about my business, focus on patients.","index":45,"end_time":252.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that was a piece that I showed them that they really liked.","index":46,"end_time":256.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":253.63,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And then obviously the scoreboard itself, which is the beginning of the demo, that piece they loved as well.","index":47,"end_time":264.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I think we need to have more on the reporting side.","index":48,"end_time":269.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.72,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So what the reporting shows and how the reporting shows, what the.","index":49,"end_time":274.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What the request types.","index":50,"end_time":276.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.12,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That was a big one for reporting them, being able to see the request types.","index":51,"end_time":281.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":276.52,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The other one was just who has responsibilities.","index":52,"end_time":286.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Right.","index":53,"end_time":286.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.32,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"If there''s a.","index":54,"end_time":287.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.64,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"A request on each side.","index":55,"end_time":288.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.8,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that main scoreboard piece, those were the two that drew them in during the demo that we had longer conversations about.","index":56,"end_time":296.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.76,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And they''ve.","index":57,"end_time":296.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They felt like that would benefit their team.","index":58,"end_time":299,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.8,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":59,"end_time":300.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":60,"end_time":301.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And maybe that''s.","index":61,"end_time":302.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know we made changes to the actual copy on the site, but maybe we can update the imagery too to show those parts of the tool specifically.","index":62,"end_time":311.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll forward you an email.","index":63,"end_time":312.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Natalie.","index":64,"end_time":313.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So you have a copy of what he''s talking about.","index":65,"end_time":317.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You have to sign up for Gripon in order to see it.","index":66,"end_time":320.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll forward an email.","index":67,"end_time":323.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m forwarding it to you now.","index":68,"end_time":325.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s.","index":69,"end_time":325.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s not from my normal email, so you''ll see it though.","index":70,"end_time":333.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just sent it.","index":71,"end_time":334.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":72,"end_time":337.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I think that would be good.","index":73,"end_time":340.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Natalie is getting some of that involved in the homepage.","index":74,"end_time":344.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.53,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The other thing that I want to do is put our support package, once I get that developed, I would like to put that in a segment on the homepage as well.","index":75,"end_time":354.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.21,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I think that that''s probably.","index":76,"end_time":356.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.41,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And Nolani, she''s from 212Dental, is one of the demos.","index":77,"end_time":361.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That was her specific piece.","index":78,"end_time":363.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.53,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She just said, hey, we''re shorthanded.","index":79,"end_time":365.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''m running an office right now.","index":80,"end_time":366.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.17,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''m trying to hire people.","index":81,"end_time":367.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.41,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I just.","index":82,"end_time":368.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.4,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I don''t see how we would launch this in our team currently.","index":83,"end_time":371.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.96,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We''re probably gonna have to wait.","index":84,"end_time":373.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.76,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so that was.","index":85,"end_time":374.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.52,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That was the hang up for them.","index":86,"end_time":375.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.6,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So.","index":87,"end_time":376.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.4,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So, Natalie, I know you are currently working on the.","index":88,"end_time":380.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The website with Keenan''s previous changes.","index":89,"end_time":387.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.2,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know how these new requests fit in.","index":90,"end_time":391.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Do we do an interim release and then add these new requests or.","index":91,"end_time":395.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.08,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So the.","index":92,"end_time":397.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The changes from Keenan are already live?","index":93,"end_time":400.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They are.","index":94,"end_time":401.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.94,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"These are the ones that you request.","index":95,"end_time":403.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Look at that.","index":96,"end_time":405.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Good job.","index":97,"end_time":405.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Good job, everyone.","index":98,"end_time":406.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, these went live yesterday.","index":99,"end_time":411.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":100,"end_time":412.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.139,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":101,"end_time":413.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, I published them and I thought.","index":102,"end_time":414.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I looked and I only saw some things, but.","index":103,"end_time":417.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Great.","index":104,"end_time":417.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":418.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So what was weird for me is I cleared my cache of cookies yesterday and I saw them, but when I logged in this morning, I saw the old site again.","index":106,"end_time":424.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.74,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I was like, what am I doing?","index":107,"end_time":425.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.94,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What happened?","index":108,"end_time":426.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.82,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And then I cleared my cache cookies again and it came back.","index":109,"end_time":429.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So we''re good.","index":110,"end_time":430.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.71,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Let me double check then because I haven''t cleared my.","index":111,"end_time":433.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":430.59,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m seeing the old one.","index":112,"end_time":439.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Your developers.","index":113,"end_time":441.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.11,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Maybe it''s a. I''ll ping my developers and see if it''s something on our end.","index":114,"end_time":447.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":115,"end_time":449.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I know for me, sometimes it doesn''t, it doesn''t show automatically, but when I open a private browser, it shows me the new site.","index":116,"end_time":458.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":461.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If you do a private browser, you''re never going to get cache.","index":118,"end_time":463.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.04,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Well, and, and, and everyone who clicks on it for the first time is going to get the new stuff.","index":119,"end_time":470.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.08,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But I need, I still need to.","index":120,"end_time":472.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.88,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":473.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey, I have a, I have a question for this group right here though, about how we are trying to move forward with this.","index":122,"end_time":481.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.36,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Because in everything that I''ve looked at, we either have something that says it''s dental specific or something that says healthcare.","index":123,"end_time":489.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.66,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"My thought is that we''re going health care because it''s a broader audience and it can be used there as well.","index":124,"end_time":498.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.54,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Dental is our specialty because it''s our background and where we came from.","index":125,"end_time":502.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.98,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I''ve noticed that there''s both in our marketing within here.","index":126,"end_time":507.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.5,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so some pieces make it look like we''re specific to dental.","index":127,"end_time":511.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.9,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Some say healthcare.","index":128,"end_time":513.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.82,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What.","index":129,"end_time":513.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.42,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Any thoughts on that from anybody else?","index":130,"end_time":517.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.66,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":131,"end_time":520.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"From the marketing perspective, we''ve been focusing mostly on dental, also with the targeting and who we''re reaching out to, but that has also led to, like last week we were talking about the cost per click on LinkedIn being really high.","index":132,"end_time":535.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That has led to, you know, because we have to narrow the audience so much.","index":133,"end_time":538.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":535.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So if we can open it up to health care, I think that, that, that is a new segment that we could target in terms of the actual website.","index":134,"end_time":547.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":539.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think would be best to have a separate landing page that''s more health care general.","index":135,"end_time":552.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What I''m hearing is we could.","index":136,"end_time":556.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.91,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''ll cost us to, to expand.","index":137,"end_time":559.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":560.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, so let''s wait on that then.","index":139,"end_time":561.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.35,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I just, I, I saw both and so that''s why that first tagline at the top of the page, that''s why I have healthcare there.","index":140,"end_time":570.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.95,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that was one of the conversations that I had with Clemens.","index":141,"end_time":580.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I''m not gonna know how to pronounce his name, but the other gentleman that I had the demo with, those two that I talked to sounded like they do both dental and healthcare based on the conversation.","index":142,"end_time":594.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.31,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So.","index":143,"end_time":595.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.74,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And, and we do.","index":144,"end_time":598.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We just haven''t marketed to both sides.","index":145,"end_time":601.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.98,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":146,"end_time":602.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.62,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":147,"end_time":602.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":602.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And.","index":148,"end_time":603.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.14,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And well, if we got more clients over there, we would go.","index":149,"end_time":608.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.78,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":150,"end_time":608.339,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We''re still searching for our first close.","index":151,"end_time":610.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.339,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":612.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.02,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And.","index":153,"end_time":613.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I''m not, you know, I''ll take anyone''s money.","index":154,"end_time":618.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":155,"end_time":619.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m not picky.","index":156,"end_time":620.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So let''s stay the course.","index":157,"end_time":621.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.58,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I think proper plan at this point is to build out the onboarding and support plan and get that on here.","index":158,"end_time":630.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.94,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So those teams that are hesitant to make a change because they can''t launch it themselves or support it within their leadership, train it, all of those things that we get that plan in place and we put that on here so they understand that they have that.","index":159,"end_time":645.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":630.5,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that''s a tool that I think that''ll drive more demos, to be honest, because I think that''ll be.","index":160,"end_time":650.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.45,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That.","index":161,"end_time":650.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.49,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''ll probably be 30% of the conversation in a demo is they''ll want to know what we do for them to make sure this gets launched appropriately.","index":162,"end_time":659.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.89,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I''ve dealt with this.","index":163,"end_time":660.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.21,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I was in the motorsports industry and that was the same thing in changing your CRM at that point was we''re all trained on this CRM.","index":164,"end_time":669.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":661.45,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We all know how to do everything here.","index":165,"end_time":671.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.97,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But how do you get your whole team within a week over to a new CRM?","index":166,"end_time":676.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":671.33,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so I''d like to stay the course there, make that the next plan, if you''re good with that.","index":167,"end_time":681.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.13,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Shane.","index":168,"end_time":681.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.33,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Very.","index":169,"end_time":682.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Hey, did you hear back from.","index":170,"end_time":685.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What was her name?","index":171,"end_time":691.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Noelani.","index":172,"end_time":692.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":691.65,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We talked yesterday and I sent her kind of what my idea was for a support plan and just asked her if she didn''t mind taking a look and seeing if that''d be something that she thought would be effective for her team.","index":173,"end_time":707.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.45,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I sent her the.","index":174,"end_time":709.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":707.74,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The general, the 30, 60, 90 that you and I had discussed.","index":175,"end_time":712.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.18,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Shane.","index":176,"end_time":712.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.26,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so I''m just waiting for a reply on that.","index":177,"end_time":716.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.98,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She typically is like me.","index":178,"end_time":717.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She replies first thing in the morning early, and then she''s running an office.","index":179,"end_time":721.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.06,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I''m guessing at that point she''s in her day and too busy to go back and forth.","index":180,"end_time":725.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":721.5,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So.","index":181,"end_time":726.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I love the onboarding.","index":182,"end_time":729.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think that''s a great idea.","index":183,"end_time":730.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s see if she bites.","index":184,"end_time":731.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.83,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":732.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":186,"end_time":734.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":187,"end_time":736.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And Shane, like, we.","index":188,"end_time":737.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ve seen that the website, I mean, it''s driving a lot of views People get to the contact page.","index":189,"end_time":742.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But maybe that hesitancy about the onboarding is what''s holding people back from.","index":190,"end_time":747.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Actually, it could very well be.","index":191,"end_time":749.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":749.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.15,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":193,"end_time":751.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, it''s hard to say.","index":194,"end_time":755.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, it''s step one, give them an idea of what we do.","index":195,"end_time":757.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Step two, overcome objections.","index":196,"end_time":761.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.98,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right?","index":197,"end_time":761.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":198,"end_time":762.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And if that''s the main objection that they have, great.","index":199,"end_time":768.099,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, we.","index":200,"end_time":771.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":201,"end_time":771.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I will say that it''s a sample size of 1.","index":202,"end_time":774.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There''s probably different objections for different people.","index":203,"end_time":776.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So I think it''s a big one.","index":204,"end_time":778.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.74,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Anyway, we''ll see.","index":205,"end_time":782.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.83,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We will see.","index":206,"end_time":785.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right.","index":207,"end_time":787.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then just another note, Keenan.","index":208,"end_time":790.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I had sent over the instructions to link your LinkedIn account to our tool.","index":209,"end_time":795.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If you run into any issues with that, just let me know.","index":210,"end_time":799.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":211,"end_time":800.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so there''s.","index":212,"end_time":801.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.51,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I had to slow down on that because I actually have a.","index":213,"end_time":805.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":801.71,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"A job offer I''m in the middle of for my day to day, and I didn''t want to change my LinkedIn and tell them I''m the VP of another company and then have that offer get, get lost in the weeds.","index":214,"end_time":820.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":805.89,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that''s all finalized as of last night.","index":215,"end_time":822.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.29,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I''m good there.","index":216,"end_time":823.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.01,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I want to make sure that I take a couple days, so I might do that at the beginning of next week is kind of what I''m thinking, to be honest.","index":217,"end_time":831.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.41,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, Sounds good.","index":218,"end_time":833.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":219,"end_time":835.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then once that''s done, like, LinkedIn has been a place where we''ve gotten the most engagement, like most people responding to messages.","index":220,"end_time":841.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So.","index":221,"end_time":843.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll be good to start that back up again.","index":222,"end_time":846.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":847.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.73,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"When does our first post go?","index":224,"end_time":849.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":847.53,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What.","index":225,"end_time":850.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":849.69,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What day is it?","index":226,"end_time":850.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.01,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Like social posts?","index":227,"end_time":854.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":855.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.73,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s up to you.","index":229,"end_time":857.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I had sent over the document, so.","index":230,"end_time":860.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":857.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So Keenan, I think she''s also talking about, like, your account will start reaching out to people, and that''s what we''ve seen.","index":231,"end_time":870.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So we have.","index":232,"end_time":871.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":870.5,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We have to have that account for them to come from.","index":233,"end_time":873.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":871.54,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yes.","index":234,"end_time":874.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":235,"end_time":876.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":875.7,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":236,"end_time":877.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.66,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And.","index":237,"end_time":878.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And that will start.","index":238,"end_time":879.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s where we''ve gotten a lot of.","index":239,"end_time":881.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Of connections.","index":240,"end_time":883.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like, probably the best, frankly.","index":241,"end_time":887.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":242,"end_time":888.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.64,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Because they actually start talking.","index":243,"end_time":890.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":891.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I meet with their HR team Monday morning.","index":245,"end_time":893.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.44,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I get back Monday afternoon.","index":246,"end_time":895.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.68,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll probably send that over to you on Tuesday.","index":247,"end_time":897.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":895.08,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Natalie.","index":248,"end_time":897.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.16,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll work on that as my Tuesday morning project.","index":249,"end_time":900.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.96,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, that''s perfect.","index":250,"end_time":902.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And just so you''re aware, it.","index":251,"end_time":905.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It sends out messages from your account to other people on LinkedIn.","index":252,"end_time":911.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":253,"end_time":912.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.29,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":913.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I''ll.","index":255,"end_time":914.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":913.69,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll be able to see the message.","index":256,"end_time":915.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.29,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Right.","index":257,"end_time":916.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":915.73,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And it''s.","index":258,"end_time":916.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.01,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":259,"end_time":917.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It acts as if it''s your Account.","index":260,"end_time":918.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":261,"end_time":920.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.33,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":262,"end_time":920.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.37,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Now.","index":263,"end_time":921.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Now, this one, we.","index":264,"end_time":924.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.05,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We paused the LinkedIn ad.","index":265,"end_time":926.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Ads.","index":266,"end_time":927.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.53,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"These are the ads, right?","index":267,"end_time":928.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"No, these are the social posts.","index":268,"end_time":930.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":929.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":269,"end_time":932.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do social posts.","index":270,"end_time":933.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":271,"end_time":934.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So you had taken a look at these last week, I believe, Keenan.","index":272,"end_time":938.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":273,"end_time":939.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So these are the ones that you will handle posting.","index":274,"end_time":942.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just wanted to see if you had any questions about these.","index":275,"end_time":945.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No.","index":276,"end_time":946.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.19,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And.","index":277,"end_time":946.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.55,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And honestly, most of them looked pretty good.","index":278,"end_time":949.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I mean, most of them were good there.","index":279,"end_time":951.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":950.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The second video of Brad speaking, I think there''s just a small editing in the beginning that''s.","index":280,"end_time":960.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":952.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I mean, it''s not enough to say, hey, let''s not run that.","index":281,"end_time":963.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.95,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But it was one that I had to watch it twice because I was like, he starts talking, and then you could tell it was an edit in the middle of him in the sentence, and it sounds like he almost starts to repeat himself in a different way and then starts talking again.","index":282,"end_time":977.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.55,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Other than that, I went through all of them.","index":283,"end_time":980.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.5,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I went through all the images, I went through the videos, I went through the wording and terminology on everything.","index":284,"end_time":986.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.7,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I think they''re engaging.","index":285,"end_time":989.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.26,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And then as we go forward, I just want to make sure that anything, obviously with Brad talking on the podcast is great because he''s got a lot of knowledge there as well.","index":286,"end_time":1001.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991.38,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But everything going forward, you know, I think needs to just stay on message with the homepage and the messages we''re trying to deliver there, because it was a noticeable reaction within the demos in the conversation for those pieces, and that was everything that they said they were looking for.","index":287,"end_time":1021.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.97,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So the way I start my demo is I say, you know, I''ll give you some background from where I''m at, where I came from, you know, what I did, and I tell them about my experience in dental, and I say, okay, let''s make this conversation geared towards you.","index":288,"end_time":1035.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1022.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So tell me what exactly what you''re trying to solve for and what your issues are.","index":289,"end_time":1039.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.9,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They both describe it exactly the same.","index":290,"end_time":1041.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.58,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They both describe it as, hey, you know, I can''t get my team to communicate.","index":291,"end_time":1046.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1042.02,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We.","index":292,"end_time":1046.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.14,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The spreadsheet thing comes up a lot.","index":293,"end_time":1048.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.58,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"You know, we''re going back and forth on spreadsheets.","index":294,"end_time":1050.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1048.26,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We can''t get people to respond.","index":295,"end_time":1051.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1050.38,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We have claims that are sitting.","index":296,"end_time":1053.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1051.62,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I don''t have time to go back and forth and manage and see who needs to do what next.","index":297,"end_time":1058.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.42,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that.","index":298,"end_time":1059.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1058.78,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That was a lot of it.","index":299,"end_time":1060.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.82,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The other piece is obviously the HIPAA compliance that they have people that are sending emails that they can''t be sending and text messages they can''t be sending.","index":300,"end_time":1068.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.78,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so this is really like A, it''s a coaching and management tool towards those behaviors and that''s really where they engaged and wanted to see more.","index":301,"end_time":1080.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1069.26,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Like how do I coach my team on it?","index":302,"end_time":1081.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1080.14,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What does the reporting allow me to see?","index":303,"end_time":1083.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.9,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I know what my team is doing and that''s where we really dug in.","index":304,"end_time":1087.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1083.78,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so I just want to make sure that as we go forward, our social posts are geared towards those messages and we make sure that we really drive the value of the reporting, coaching and the requests that come in through.","index":305,"end_time":1104.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.74,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Through a grip on that dashboard.","index":306,"end_time":1106.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1104.37,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, got it.","index":307,"end_time":1108.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You didn''t happen to record those demos, did you?","index":308,"end_time":1111.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I did not record the first two, but I wanted it, so I, I used the first two and I talked to Shane about this.","index":309,"end_time":1120.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.09,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I use the first two as kind of, this is my first experience with a grip on and talking through it with customers.","index":310,"end_time":1126.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.81,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I use the first two to one, get information for us on what.","index":311,"end_time":1130.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What engage the customers.","index":312,"end_time":1132.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1130.73,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I also, I use mine to re gear my demo and to develop my talk track.","index":313,"end_time":1140.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.45,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I''ll record the next one and make sure that we have something we could show there as well.","index":314,"end_time":1145.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1140.53,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":315,"end_time":1145.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1145.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":316,"end_time":1147.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":317,"end_time":1147.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And over time it''ll allow us to just refine our messaging even more as we start to see patterns in what people care about.","index":318,"end_time":1155.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":319,"end_time":1156.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.81,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":320,"end_time":1159.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":321,"end_time":1160.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then looking at our LinkedIn ads.","index":322,"end_time":1163.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we took a look at it with the cost per click, Shane, from last week, and what we saw is that it increased after we changed our targeting.","index":323,"end_time":1172.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If you remember before, we had a lot of people filling in the forms, but they weren''t necessarily the right fit for a grip on.","index":324,"end_time":1180.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1172.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So then we started tightening the targeting.","index":325,"end_time":1182.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We got our campaigns to bring targeting around 1800 people, which is quite a tight group for LinkedIn.","index":326,"end_time":1189.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And ultimately that''s what make the cost per click rise.","index":327,"end_time":1192.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then also our.","index":328,"end_time":1193.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Our goals for These campaigns on LinkedIn are for lead generation.","index":329,"end_time":1197.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So specifically getting people to submit the form, not clicks.","index":330,"end_time":1201.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1197.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that means that the algorithm is willing to pay more per click if it thinks that someone is likely to convert.","index":331,"end_time":1208.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So our recommendations, though our paid media specialist said we could warm the audience first by running a website visit campaign.","index":332,"end_time":1218.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So with the goal of getting clicks specifically and getting people to the website, warming them up first and then retargeting them later with ads with forms.","index":333,"end_time":1229.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":334,"end_time":1231.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That sounds reasonable.","index":335,"end_time":1232.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.04,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, I get it that the goal was optimized for lead generations, but we failed to meet that goal as well.","index":336,"end_time":1237.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.08,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":337,"end_time":1239.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1239.51,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So.","index":338,"end_time":1240.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1240.15,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"If that''s our goal, I''m okay paying $20 a click if those people do convert, but they did not.","index":339,"end_time":1249.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":340,"end_time":1250.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":341,"end_time":1251.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1251.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And we''re also going to look at expanding the targeting too.","index":342,"end_time":1256.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1251.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we started with a very large pool.","index":343,"end_time":1259.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We may be overcorrected a little bit and making it smaller.","index":344,"end_time":1262.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll work on trying to find that happy medium.","index":345,"end_time":1265.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":346,"end_time":1266.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So Natalie, with these, the information we''re getting from this, is this the information where we''re actually getting people that we can reach out to?","index":347,"end_time":1274.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1267.95,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Like am I getting email addresses, names, companies, something that I can be researching and reaching back out to, or am I not getting that from this?","index":348,"end_time":1285.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1276.83,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"No, that would be if they submit the form specifically.","index":349,"end_time":1289.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1290.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But we do have the.","index":351,"end_time":1292.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yesterday.","index":352,"end_time":1294.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have you been looking at this, Keenan?","index":353,"end_time":1296.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Well, I was waiting for the new launch first before I started to direct people towards what we had.","index":354,"end_time":1302.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.62,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So with the website up now, that''s kind of where I want to spend some time is going back to these people and having a conversation with them.","index":355,"end_time":1310.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1303.38,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, it would be good to go back to them.","index":356,"end_time":1312.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It would be good to go back to maybe some of the other ones that we came close to before that we''ve been had conversations with.","index":357,"end_time":1320.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So.","index":358,"end_time":1320.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":359,"end_time":1322.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And there are.","index":360,"end_time":1323.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"There are a couple of companies that keep popping up week after week.","index":361,"end_time":1327.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1323.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This easy.","index":362,"end_time":1330.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If you go to the third email clicks, I''ve been looking at that.","index":363,"end_time":1333.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There''s some companies here like Cord ds, Cord sdp and so some people clicked on it twice.","index":364,"end_time":1342.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.78,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I''ve actually reached out to those people on LinkedIn and just introduce myself.","index":365,"end_time":1347.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.78,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But.","index":366,"end_time":1349.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.02,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And, and then there''s like there''s a lot of.","index":367,"end_time":1353.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Of companies here that are.","index":368,"end_time":1356.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Seem to be pinged.","index":369,"end_time":1358.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1357.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":370,"end_time":1360.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1360.06,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1361.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1360.62,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So once I get my LinkedIn set up with a grip on chain.","index":372,"end_time":1364.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.02,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the plan was to get the website done, get my LinkedIn set up.","index":373,"end_time":1369.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.02,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":374,"end_time":1370.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then this will be kind of the plan is to go back through and start reaching out to some of these people.","index":375,"end_time":1375.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.26,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":376,"end_time":1376.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1376.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":377,"end_time":1378.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then looking at our dashboard, so the website is picking up again.","index":378,"end_time":1388.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1384.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We can see the traffic increased or visitors are up 37%.","index":379,"end_time":1392.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Page views are up 27% for the last 30 days.","index":380,"end_time":1396.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1392.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And the largest sources are direct traffic and ABM.","index":381,"end_time":1401.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1396.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The case study page as well is doing really well.","index":382,"end_time":1404.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1402.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that trust content is what people are looking at and engaging with.","index":383,"end_time":1408.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1404.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then now that the new homepage messaging is launched, we''ll be able to see if that helps with the bounce rate.","index":384,"end_time":1415.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1409.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Meaning people that are.","index":385,"end_time":1417.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1416.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Meaning people are staying engaged on the site for longer.","index":386,"end_time":1420.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1417.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":387,"end_time":1427.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.81,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Cool.","index":388,"end_time":1429.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1429.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Any other questions about what we''re working on?","index":389,"end_time":1431.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Nope.","index":390,"end_time":1432.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.27,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Cool.","index":391,"end_time":1434.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1434.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll hand It over to Colin then.","index":392,"end_time":1439.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":393,"end_time":1440.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey, Shane, how''s it going?","index":394,"end_time":1442.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1441.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":395,"end_time":1442.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":396,"end_time":1443.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right.","index":397,"end_time":1444.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1443.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting geared up for holiday season.","index":398,"end_time":1446.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1444.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, I know how it goes.","index":399,"end_time":1451.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1447.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":400,"end_time":1453.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1452.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So wanted to update you.","index":401,"end_time":1454.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1453.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had some conversations internally.","index":402,"end_time":1456.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1454.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you were asking also about the points balance.","index":403,"end_time":1459.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1456.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so with that being at negative 470, that''s, that''s virtually $47,000 worth of work that we''ve done outside of scope.","index":404,"end_time":1468.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1459.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But with our relationship and our partnership, everything that we''ve done is striving towards hitting goals.","index":405,"end_time":1475.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1469.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":406,"end_time":1476.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1475.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so with.","index":407,"end_time":1477.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1476.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not with, with landing some demos, but not seeing them convert, we want to continue the partnership and so wanted to give you a.","index":408,"end_time":1487.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1477.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"An early Christmas present of wiping the slate clean of those 470 points overage.","index":409,"end_time":1493.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1487.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":410,"end_time":1493.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But with all that being said, we are working on a monthly plan of staying within our scope.","index":411,"end_time":1501.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1494.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''ll present that to you in a spreadsheet every month.","index":412,"end_time":1504.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1502.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if we need to, like, if we have a new, A new approach or anything we want to take, we''ll just have to swap something out on a monthly basis.","index":413,"end_time":1512.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1505.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just want to stay within a finite number of overage.","index":414,"end_time":1517.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1512.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":415,"end_time":1518.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I think it''s respectful for both sides.","index":416,"end_time":1520.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1518.12,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And you''re right.","index":417,"end_time":1523.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, fundamentally our goal is we''ve got to get people paying us.","index":418,"end_time":1529.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1523.4,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We have had a couple demos, but only a couple, like literally two or three.","index":419,"end_time":1535.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I would say that we have to figure out how to do more more with less.","index":420,"end_time":1542.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1537.04,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That means that we''re going to have to be creative.","index":421,"end_time":1544.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1542.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep.","index":422,"end_time":1545.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1544.46,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It means that we''re going to have to really think about where is the best place to spend our time that has the most return.","index":423,"end_time":1552.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And so what I may not be buying with points I hope to purchase.","index":424,"end_time":1559.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1554.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"With your brain power.","index":425,"end_time":1560.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.62,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":426,"end_time":1562.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1561.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s like even the stuff that Natalie was just talking about in the last couple of minutes of.","index":427,"end_time":1566.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1562.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Keenan mentioned it too.","index":428,"end_time":1568.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1567.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, expanding into the health care audience.","index":429,"end_time":1570.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1568.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if we get a larger or if we overcorrected on LinkedIn ads and we expand that audience a little bit more than the more people we talk to, it''s actually going to be a little bit cheaper because we''re not fighting with so many people to talk to a smaller list of people.","index":430,"end_time":1583.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1570.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s definitely some widening of the net that we can do and just get more velocity through the channels that we''re using.","index":431,"end_time":1591.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1583.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":432,"end_time":1592.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, you guys are the experts and I expect you to know how to take us to the next level.","index":433,"end_time":1599.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So.","index":434,"end_time":1600.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.74,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I recognize that we''re not rich, but in a way that''s an advantage because we''ll have to focus.","index":435,"end_time":1608.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.14,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, we really will have to say this is.","index":436,"end_time":1611.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1608.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"This is what works and this is what doesn''t, and.","index":437,"end_time":1614.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1612.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep.","index":438,"end_time":1615.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1614.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s where we specialize, is scrappy.","index":439,"end_time":1617.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1615.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":440,"end_time":1618.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1617.74,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":441,"end_time":1618.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":442,"end_time":1618.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s be scrappy.","index":443,"end_time":1620.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m going to.","index":444,"end_time":1620.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, next week is obviously Christmas.","index":445,"end_time":1623.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.59,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m gonna say I, I really, I''ll challenge you guys, and I''m sure you''re challenging yourself.","index":446,"end_time":1629.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You don''t need me to extra challenge, but we''ve gotta, we''ve gotta start getting some.","index":447,"end_time":1635.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.87,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Some closed deals in order to keep this business alive, so.","index":448,"end_time":1638.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1635.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, I''ve mentioned that before.","index":449,"end_time":1640.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1639.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''ll mention it again.","index":450,"end_time":1642.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.03,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Appreciate all you do.","index":451,"end_time":1643.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1642.31,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s go.","index":452,"end_time":1645.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":453,"end_time":1647.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1646.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":454,"end_time":1649.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1648.88,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":455,"end_time":1652.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1651.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, guys, have a merry Christmas.","index":456,"end_time":1655.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.04,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I will send that LinkedIn over to you Tuesday, Natalie.","index":457,"end_time":1658.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We get that part of it started.","index":458,"end_time":1660.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1658.88,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I''m working on the onboarding and support plan, so I''m going to try to have that done next week as well.","index":459,"end_time":1668.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.32,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so we can kind of figure out a time frame for that, but we can do that through email with the holidays coming up and everything.","index":460,"end_time":1676.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I know we don''t talk next week.","index":461,"end_time":1678.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676.89,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, I appreciate it.","index":462,"end_time":1680.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.81,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":463,"end_time":1681.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1680.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I wish you all a merry Christmas and I''ll see you after.","index":464,"end_time":1685.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1681.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":465,"end_time":1687.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":466,"end_time":1687.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.45,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":467,"end_time":1688.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1687.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":468,"end_time":1688.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1688.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"See you guys.","index":469,"end_time":1689.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1688.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-18T13:30:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com,shane@agrippon.com,f.dominguez@agrippon.com,j.samstag@agrippon.com,monique.king@agrippon.com,david.reynolds@agrippon.com,keenan.toward@agrippon.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com","shane@agrippon.com","f.dominguez@agrippon.com","j.samstag@agrippon.com","monique.king@agrippon.com","david.reynolds@agrippon.com","keenan.toward@agrippon.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC71QMDMJ47DYVJHRBB3MZ8S","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Delivered 28 December items and launched key website copy updates and LinkedIn ad package.","Keenan reported strong demo engagement but emphasized onboarding support need as buyer barrier.","Team aligned on moving forward with healthcare onboarding plan and tailoring messaging accordingly.","Ad targeting adjustments raised cost per click but may better qualify leads for follow-up.","Colin reset 470-point scope overage to reinforce partnership; monthly scope control plan in place."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Customers were engaged. The demo piece is very big.","speaker":"Keenan Toward"},{"quote":"We’ve got to start getting some closed deals in order to keep this business alive.","speaker":"Shane Billings"},{"quote":"Wanted to give you an early Christmas present of wiping the slate clean.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","onboarding","launch","ads","scope"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-19T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Product Demo and Onboarding Development**\n\nThe demos confirmed strong customer interest but highlighted a critical need for a structured onboarding and support package to ease product adoption.\n\n- **Keenan Toward reported that both demos engaged customers deeply, revealing a key barrier: clients struggle to train their teams to use the product effectively, prompting the creation of a tiered onboarding support package** offering self-led and fully managed options (02:09).  \n    - This package aims to address launch hesitancy by providing tailored training and support based on team size and client preference.  \n    - Keenan emphasized that onboarding support will likely become about 30% of demo conversations, reflecting its importance in closing deals.  \n    - The plan is to add this onboarding segment visibly on the homepage once developed, increasing transparency and confidence for prospects.  \n    - Noelani from 212Dental, a demo participant, exemplified this need due to staffing shortages and hiring challenges.  \n\n- **Keenan also identified two demo features that resonated most: the automated email scoreboard update and the main dashboard scoreboard, which provide quick team performance insights and accountability tracking** (03:37).  \n    - Customers showed interest in enhanced reporting features detailing request types and responsibility assignments, signaling a demand for deeper data visibility.  \n    - Natalie Mintjens suggested updating website imagery to better showcase these features alongside the onboarding offering to align marketing with demo feedback.  \n    - Shane Billings and Nathalie discussed intermittent site cache issues affecting visibility of recent updates, with Shane planning to investigate developer-side solutions (06:16).  \n\n- **Keenan recommended maintaining healthcare as the broader target market while keeping dental as the specialty background, cautioning against mixed messaging that confuses prospects** (07:55).  \n    - The team agreed to focus current marketing on dental to control costs but consider a healthcare landing page later, balancing market reach and budget constraints.  \n    - Shane stressed the priority remains closing paying clients before expanding target segments (10:01).  \n\n## **Marketing Strategy and Website Performance**\n\nMarketing is focused on refining messaging and targeting to improve lead quality, engagement, and conversion while managing costs.\n\n- **LinkedIn ad campaigns tightened targeting to 1,800 prospects, causing cost-per-click to rise but improving lead quality, though conversion goals have yet to be met**; the paid media specialist recommended warming audiences with website visit campaigns before retargeting with lead-gen ads (19:19).  \n    - Shane accepted paying up to **$20 per click** if those clicks convert but noted the current campaigns fail to convert adequately (20:42).  \n    - Nathalie proposed expanding targeting slightly to balance cost and reach, aiming to find an optimal audience size (20:50).  \n\n- **Keenan plans to leverage LinkedIn data by reaching out personally to prospects who engaged with the site and ads once his LinkedIn account is linked to the tool, targeting follow-up conversations to drive demos** (21:07).  \n    - Shane has proactively contacted some companies based on click data, increasing direct engagement efforts (22:10).  \n    - Keenan will complete LinkedIn setup by Tuesday and then start outreach as a top priority (14:48, 22:49).  \n\n- **Website traffic metrics show positive momentum, with a 37% increase in visitors and 27% rise in page views over the last 30 days, driven mainly by direct traffic and account-based marketing (ABM)** (23:04).  \n    - The case study page is notably high-performing, indicating trust-building content appeals to visitors.  \n    - The team will monitor bounce rates to assess if refreshed homepage messaging improves visitor engagement and retention.  \n\n- **Social media content reviews confirmed most posts are engaging and aligned with messaging; Keenan emphasized the importance of keeping posts consistent with homepage messaging and demo insights to reinforce value propositions around coaching, reporting, and compliance** (15:39).  \n    - Minor video editing tweaks were noted but deemed not critical to delay posting.  \n    - Brad’s podcast content is valuable for knowledge sharing and should be incorporated carefully into the messaging mix.  \n\n## **Resource and Partnership Management**\n\nThe partnership is committed to staying within scope and focusing effort where it yields the best return, with a reset on overage balances.\n\n- **Colin Costigan announced that the outstanding negative balance of 470 points, equivalent to approximately $47,000 in out-of-scope work, will be forgiven as a goodwill gesture to support continued partnership** (24:01).  \n    - Moving forward, the team will work within a fixed monthly scope, presenting plans in spreadsheets with flexibility to swap tasks as priorities shift.  \n    - Shane appreciated this approach, highlighting the need to prioritize high-return activities due to limited budget and stressed creativity in maximizing impact with fewer resources (25:17).  \n\n- **Colin reinforced the strategy to expand LinkedIn targeting within reason to reduce cost per engagement and increase velocity through marketing channels, leveraging the team’s expertise in scrappy, efficient growth tactics** (26:01).  \n    - Shane welcomed this mindset, emphasizing disciplined focus on what works to accelerate closed deals, which are critical to business survival (26:54).  \n\n## **Sales Enablement and Messaging Alignment**\n\nSales demos and marketing must align tightly around client pain points to increase conversion rates.\n\n- **Keenan shared that prospects consistently describe team communication challenges, reliance on spreadsheets, and non-compliant messaging as core problems, positioning the product as a coaching and management tool to fix these behaviors** (17:15).  \n    - This insight shapes the narrative for demos and social messaging to emphasize reporting, coaching, and request tracking as key differentiators.  \n    - Recording future demos is planned to capture customer interactions for ongoing messaging refinement (18:32).  \n    - Nathalie noted that evolving messaging based on demo patterns will strengthen marketing effectiveness over time.  \n\n- **Keenan’s personal demo approach includes sharing his dental industry background and tailoring conversations to specific client challenges, enhancing credibility and relevance** (16:50).  \n    - This approach was validated by demo feedback and will continue to guide sales training and content development.  \n\n## **Operational Execution and Timelines**\n\nKey deliverables are progressing with clear next steps and timelines aimed at supporting sales and marketing efforts.\n\n- **Keenan will finalize LinkedIn account linkage and begin outreach by Tuesday as his top priority, integrating the platform into ongoing lead engagement** (14:48, 22:49).  \n- **The onboarding and support package development is targeted for completion next week, with follow-up review and homepage update to follow, coordinated via email due to holiday schedules** (27:33).  \n- **Natalie will continue to monitor website analytics and campaign performance post-homepage update to measure impact on engagement and lead quality** (23:04).  \n- **The team agreed to keep social content postings aligned with homepage messaging and demo insights to maintain consistency and reinforce value propositions** (15:39).  \n\nThese coordinated efforts aim to reduce onboarding objections, improve lead conversion, and accelerate closed deals before year-end.","outline":null,"keywords":["Onboarding","Demo Feedback","LinkedIn Outreach","Website Updates","Marketing Strategy","Ad Campaigns"],"overview":"- **Customer Interest:** Demos indicated strong interest but revealed onboarding support is crucial for effective product adoption.\n\n- **Onboarding Package:** A tiered onboarding support package will offer tailored training based on team size and preferences.\n\n- **Marketing Focus:** LinkedIn ads optimized targeting, improving lead quality but aiming for better conversion rates despite rising costs.\n\n- **Website Traffic Growth:** Recent metrics show a 37% visitor increase, primarily due to direct traffic and successful account-based marketing strategies.\n\n- **Sales Messaging Alignment:** Teams must address core client pain points and enhance demos to increase conversions and reinforce product value.\n\n- **Action Plans:** Key deliverables include onboarding package completion and LinkedIn outreach, improving lead engagement and sales efforts.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nDevelop a tiered onboarding and support package for customers to ease product launch in teams (02:09)\nLink LinkedIn account to the Gripon tool early next week after finalizing personal job situation (13:20)\nReview and approve minor edits to Brad’s social post video before posting (15:46)\nAlign all future social posts and messaging to reflect homepage messaging and demo customer needs focusing on coaching, reporting, and request handling (17:15)\nRecord future demos for internal review and messaging refinement (18:32)\nResume LinkedIn outreach to warm leads after website updates and LinkedIn integration (21:05)\nSend LinkedIn account linking details to Natalie Mintjens by Tuesday following holiday week (27:31)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nAssist Keenan with any issues linking his LinkedIn account to the tool (13:06)\nContinue monitoring LinkedIn ad campaigns and adjust targeting to balance audience size and cost per click (19:19)\nMonitor website analytics focusing on impact of new homepage messaging on visitor engagement and bounce rates (23:04)\nProvide Keenan with social post schedules and instructions (14:06)\nCollaborate with team through the holidays on onboarding/support plan and LinkedIn outreach coordination (27:31)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nFollow up with developers to resolve website caching issues causing some users to see old site version (07:10)\nSupport marketing strategy focusing on scrappy, high-impact campaigns to generate paying customers (25:44)\nEngage in LinkedIn outreach to contacts identified from ad campaign data (22:10)\nCollaborate with team to ensure monthly scope and balance point overage (24:53)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize internal agreement to reset negative points balance and establish monthly scoped plans to control overage (24:01)\nProvide monthly spreadsheets detailing scope and points usage for transparency and planning (24:53)\nAssist team with strategy for optimizing LinkedIn audience size and campaign efficiency (26:31)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"9cb2e80d-8e3b-433d-a38d-c93e13f09b38","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
