    '{"id":"01KC78YMG00WTGP1QT7DWACVPN","title":"Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Sales Guide and Visual Asset Refinement**\n\nThe team is finalizing updates to the **IPM and Optimizer sales guides and related visuals** to improve clarity and brand consistency ahead of upcoming launches (04:07).\n\n- **Lou Bogani presented multiple refinements** including reducing logo size for better spacing and adjusting image placements to avoid awkward cropping (04:07).\n    - Roz emphasized the need to maintain distinct image libraries per product, preventing cross-use to strengthen product identity (10:24).\n    - Lou agreed to replace images that conflicted with these guidelines and remove certain icons for a cleaner look (11:04).\n    - Color adjustments were requested, with Roz directing a shift to lighter gray tones and gradient bubbles for a fresher look aligned with current branding preferences (06:04, 07:56).\n    - Lou committed to uploading updated files to the shared folder for testing and final review before distribution (16:15).\n\n- **The team is testing a new file export method limiting swatches** to five or six colors to solve prior color inconsistencies experienced when transferring files via Google software (02:07).\n    - Roz described persistent color distortion issues with Google Docs and suggested testing Adobe file transfer as a potential solution (02:27).\n    - Natalie Mintjens will coordinate updates and verify if Lou’s new method resolves the problem before sending files externally (16:18).\n\n- **Roz identified key image style directions for RPD marketing materials**, differentiating between RPD’s statement/bill printing focus and IPM’s distributed print use cases to maintain clear product narratives (24:00).\n    - She stressed the importance of subtle Ricoh red accents in images to strengthen brand recognition without overwhelming visuals (25:23).\n    - Roz requested imagery that suggests large print plants or shop floors without revealing competitor equipment to avoid legal issues (25:23).\n    - Lou and Roz agreed on creating horizontal and vertical versions of images to enhance flexibility in PowerPoints and sales guides (18:02).\n\n- **The RPD sales guide and PowerPoint must be ready by late February** to enable regional teams to receive materials at least 30 days before the April launch, highlighting the brochure and PowerPoint as the highest priorities (34:05).\n    - Roz plans to send the RPD battle card soon for template updates, noting it contains no new images, only hero shots and content formatting (35:37).\n    - Natalie will continue managing the rollout and updates across all assets post-finalization (35:55).\n\n## **Product Imagery Strategy and Brand Consistency**\n\nThe group focused on aligning product imagery with marketing goals and brand guidelines to enhance differentiation and customer recognition (20:24).\n\n- **Roz provided detailed guidance on image selection**, favoring subtle color use and avoiding overly bright or \"primary school\" looks for professional appeal (21:05).\n    - She recommended reducing red elements to a single highlight per image, improving visual balance and brand coherence (17:21).\n    - Roz noted some images needed texture adjustments to appear more natural, avoiding overly perfect skin tones (23:17).\n    - She requested adjustments on specific colors, such as shifting bottle colors to Ricoh red or making them clear to match brand standards (19:14).\n\n- **Product differentiation between RPD and IPM was clarified** to ensure marketing materials reflect the distinct use cases and customer needs for each product (27:30).\n    - RPD targets companies with one or two print locations focusing on bulk statement printing.\n    - IPM serves distributed print environments with multiple locations, often government or large enterprises.\n    - Roz plans to maintain clear visual and narrative separation to reduce customer confusion and support sales positioning (28:15).\n\n- **Competitive landscape considerations influenced image selection**, particularly avoiding visuals that reveal competitor equipment on print floors (25:23).\n    - Roz praised prior work on Avanti-related images but confirmed the Avanti relationship has ended from a company ownership perspective, affecting branding and integration references (29:30).\n    - Colin Costigan raised the need to review and potentially update documents mentioning Avanti to reflect current status, with Roz confirming this is a regional responsibility (30:52).\n\n## **Operational Workflow and Timeline Planning**\n\nThe team agreed on workflows and timelines critical to launching updated materials smoothly, incorporating feedback cycles and holiday scheduling (36:41).\n\n- **Roz requested final images and sales guides be ready for regional distribution by late February**, setting internal deadlines accordingly (34:05).\n    - Natalie Mintjens will coordinate updates and deliverables, ensuring Lou uploads revisions promptly for review (16:15).\n    - The team will test file transfers using Adobe methods to avoid color distortion and improve efficiency (02:07).\n\n- **Holiday scheduling conflicts were addressed**, with the team deciding to cancel the meeting landing on Christmas and New Year’s Day due to holidays in Canada and overlapping absences (36:41).\n    - Roz proposed no meetings during the week of December 29th since Natalie and others are out, recommending email updates instead (37:56).\n    - Natalie confirmed availability for quick calls during December 22-24 if needed to resolve last-minute issues (38:32).\n\n- **Continuous communication through email will cover interim updates**, minimizing disruption during the holiday season while maintaining project momentum (38:28).\n    - Roz emphasized availability for quick calls if questions arise despite the holiday period (38:32).\n\n## **Video Production and Multi-format Content Delivery**\n\nThe team is delivering an animated video with alternate music versions to provide choice and better align with refreshed brand energy (16:26).\n\n- **Natalie reported the first cut of the animated video will be delivered the same day**, with two music variants—one more upbeat—to match the updated animation style (16:26).\n    - Roz confirmed readiness to review and provide feedback promptly (16:44).\n    - This aligns with broader efforts to refresh content and keep marketing materials engaging and current.\n\n- **Multiple formats and orientations for images are planned** to increase flexibility across sales guides and PowerPoints (18:02).\n    - Roz suggested creating both vertical and horizontal versions of key images to enhance usability.\n    - This supports varied presentation needs and improves visual appeal across platforms.\n\n## **Stakeholder Collaboration and Responsibility Alignment**\n\nClear ownership and collaboration processes were established to ensure smooth execution and accountability (16:15).\n\n- **Lou Bogani is responsible for updating and uploading revised files** including sales guides, charts, and images to the shared folder for testing and review (16:15).\n    - Natalie Mintjens will manage coordination, task tracking, and final delivery to external recipients (16:18).\n    - Roz will provide detailed feedback on imagery and content to ensure alignment with branding and marketing goals (15:49).\n\n- **Roz will send product shots and image libraries to Natalie and Nina** to support ongoing creative work and maintain consistency across materials (18:41).\n    - This enables the team to work from a shared asset pool, reducing duplication and speeding revisions.\n    - Roz’s deep domain knowledge of commercial print and marketing nuances guides asset selection and messaging (29:04).\n\n- **The team agreed on iterative feedback cycles, emphasizing testing and refinement**, especially regarding color accuracy and image placement, to avoid delays and rework (02:07, 14:08).\n    - This process includes testing swatch-limited files and Adobe transfer methods to resolve technical issues impacting quality.\n    - Clear communication channels and prompt feedback loops are prioritized to meet tight deadlines.\n\n## **Brand and Product Positioning Philosophy**\n\nDiscussions revealed a deliberate approach to maintaining product clarity and competitive advantage through visual and messaging discipline (27:30).\n\n- **Roz highlighted the importance of distinct visual narratives for RPD versus IPM** to reduce customer confusion and reinforce product strengths (27:30).\n    - She emphasized the strategic use of imagery that reflects real-world use cases and customer environments.\n    - This visual clarity supports the sales process by helping prospects self-identify with the right solution.\n\n- **The team consciously avoids overusing red and dark grays**, opting instead for lighter grays and subtle red accents to modernize the brand while respecting legacy identity (06:04, 07:56).\n    - This shift responds to internal feedback and market trends favoring cleaner, lighter aesthetics.\n    - Roz explained this is part of a broader brand refresh philosophy to stay relevant without losing brand equity.\n\n- **Competitive integrations like Avanti remain possible but are de-emphasized** in marketing as company relationships have evolved, reflecting a shift in strategic partnerships (29:42).\n    - The team plans to phase out residual references and focus on Ricoh’s own product strengths and ecosystem.\n    - This approach clarifies market positioning and avoids confusion around partnerships.","outline":null,"keywords":["sales guide","color calibration","Ricoh Predictive Dynamics","image assets","branding guidelines","marketing collateral"],"overview":"- **Sales Guides & Visuals:** Finalizing updates for IPM and Optimizer sales guides to enhance clarity and brand consistency before launches.\n\n- **Image Adjustments:** Image libraries will be distinct per product, with reduced logos, lighter colors, and horizontal/vertical formats for flexibility.\n\n- **Color Consistency Issues:** Testing new file export methods to limit color swatches and resolve issues with Google Docs color distortions.\n\n- **RPD Launch Timeline:** RPD sales guide and PowerPoint must be ready by late February for regional teams before April launches.\n\n- **Holiday Meeting Changes:** Meetings on December 25 and January 1 are canceled; updates will be shared via email during the holiday.\n\n- **Differentiated Messaging:** Clear visual narratives for RPD and IPM to reduce customer confusion and support distinct marketing strategies.","action_items":"\n**Lou Bogani**\nShare updated sales guide files with reduced swatches for color testing (02:07)\nAdjust images to avoid cropping issues and replace conflicting images with product-specific imagery (08:39)\nChange gray boxes to lighter gradient per current branding refresh and finalize icon updates (06:10)\nRemove product overview text from current page, rearrange content to reduce whitespace, and add personas under target markets to save space (12:29)\nUpload amended files to shared drive folder to verify color export consistency (13:38)\nSwitch outline colors to charcoal on Optimizer materials for cleaner visuals (15:00)\nUpdate product shots and sales guide images following Roz’s feedback to reflect brand colors and styling (14:31)\nDeliver final sales guide package to Nathalie Mintjens after requested updates are completed (15:59)\n\n**Roz (Rosalynne Regan)**\nProvide product shots and GUI images for marketing materials to Nathalie and Lou (18:41)\nReview and confirm updated files for color accuracy and overall design after receiving from Lou (15:50)\nSend RPD Battle Card for template updating once RPD images are finalized (34:05)\nCoordinate timeline to finalize RPD sales guides and PowerPoint by end of February for April launch (32:23)\nAdvise on regional messaging surrounding Avanti references and integrations (29:42)\nNotify team regarding scheduling around holiday periods and handle any urgent needs via email or calls (36:51)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nConsolidate Lou’s completed tasks and upload new files for review (16:04)\nSend the first cut of animated video along with two music version options to Roz for approval (16:26)\nPrepare Process Director brochure for delivery by Monday (16:44)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nConfirm if any content needs updates regarding Avanti mentions and inform relevant parties (29:31)\n"},"duration":39.86000061035156,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Lou Bogani"},{"id":3,"name":"Roz"},{"id":4,"name":"Roz"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Now this.","index":0,"end_time":6.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This fireflies always confuses me on if you have an E or not.","index":1,"end_time":10.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do.","index":2,"end_time":13.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think it''s just too long.","index":3,"end_time":14.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How could you not know?","index":4,"end_time":18.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If I had an ear.","index":5,"end_time":19.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Not this whole time.","index":6,"end_time":20.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s only the fireflies that confuses.","index":7,"end_time":22.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I always spell it with an E and then this thing joins.","index":8,"end_time":27.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":9,"end_time":37.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":10,"end_time":38.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.33,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":11,"end_time":39.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.85,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":12,"end_time":42.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.609,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":13,"end_time":44.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":43.53,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":14,"end_time":44.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.05,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I still haven''t bothered him today, so he''s doing fine.","index":15,"end_time":48.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":46.01,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"No, it''s.","index":16,"end_time":50.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.93,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":17,"end_time":50.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":50.61,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":18,"end_time":51.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":50.97,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Hey, Roz.","index":19,"end_time":52.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":20,"end_time":53.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":52.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Hey.","index":21,"end_time":53.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":53.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''ll bother you, Lou.","index":22,"end_time":54.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":53.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I don''t mind.","index":23,"end_time":55.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":54.94,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m happy.","index":24,"end_time":56.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":56.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":25,"end_time":57.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.22,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Good, thanks.","index":26,"end_time":59.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":58.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"How are you?","index":27,"end_time":60.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":59.3,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Oh, good, good.","index":28,"end_time":62.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.78,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So, Roz, I know Colin already told you a little bit, but I also want to introduce Nina.","index":29,"end_time":73.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yes.","index":30,"end_time":74.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":74.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Another strategist on our team.","index":31,"end_time":76.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"She''ll be providing more support here.","index":32,"end_time":78.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hello.","index":33,"end_time":79.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Hello, Nina.","index":34,"end_time":79.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":79.2,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Welcome to the chaos.","index":35,"end_time":82.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":81.24,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Nice to meet you and to join the chaos.","index":36,"end_time":85.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":83.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Nice to meet you as well.","index":37,"end_time":88.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":86.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Welcome.","index":38,"end_time":88.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":88.12,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"All right, we can jump right in.","index":39,"end_time":94.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think we can start with the two projects that you''re working on, Lou.","index":40,"end_time":98.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":99.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.84,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"If you want to walk through those with Roz.","index":42,"end_time":102.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":43,"end_time":103.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.44,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So, Ross, before, like, starting, I made kind of.","index":44,"end_time":108.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":103.32,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Oh, the camera folks.","index":45,"end_time":109.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.43,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So what we.","index":46,"end_time":111.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.99,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"With the stuff that we talked.","index":47,"end_time":113.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.87,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yes.","index":48,"end_time":113.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.35,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The last call I sent Natalie, let me check.","index":49,"end_time":119.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":114.27,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Which one is it?","index":50,"end_time":120.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.75,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The Total Floor Flow Optimizer sales guide.","index":51,"end_time":126.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.47,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s in good shape.","index":52,"end_time":129.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":127.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":130.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.71,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But what I.","index":54,"end_time":130.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.11,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"But what I did with that file that you''re gonna receive from Natalies, I re.","index":55,"end_time":135.559,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.279,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I only left the swatches that we talked about, like, so just for us to test if.","index":56,"end_time":141.759,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":135.559,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay.","index":57,"end_time":142.679,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":142.239,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":58,"end_time":142.999,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":142.679,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":59,"end_time":143.439,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":142.999,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":144.959,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":144.479,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Translate.","index":61,"end_time":146.319,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":145.679,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":146.959,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":146.479,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I want to test if that file, when you get it to the.","index":63,"end_time":150.759,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.199,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"To the, to the Google, like, like software, it gets, like, what, Weird in terms of color.","index":64,"end_time":157.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":150.759,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":158.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":157.73,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Or is that in design, when we export it with so many swatches, it messes up the colors.","index":66,"end_time":164.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":158.41,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like.","index":67,"end_time":164.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":164.49,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe.","index":68,"end_time":165.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":164.81,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, so yeah, let''s.","index":69,"end_time":166.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":165.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":70,"end_time":167.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":166.77,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Let''s test drive that because, yeah, we''ve been having that weirdness.","index":71,"end_time":169.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":167.21,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I just, like I said I before, I think it has to do with kind of the, like, what.","index":72,"end_time":174.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":169.85,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"What was happening with the PowerPoints that was driving me, you know, crazy.","index":73,"end_time":178.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":174.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, you guys were seeing them totally fine.","index":74,"end_time":180.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":178.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then I was seeing them not.","index":75,"end_time":182.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":180.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And Natalie, you were like, show me.","index":76,"end_time":184.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":182.05,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m like, yeah, here you go.","index":77,"end_time":185.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":184.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And it was all over the place because of Google Docs.","index":78,"end_time":188.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":185.73,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":79,"end_time":188.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":188.45,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":190.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":189.73,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So by all means, please, yeah, send it.","index":81,"end_time":192.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":190.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Send it through.","index":82,"end_time":193.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":192.65,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And let''s see if, though, if that fixes the problem, and I''ll let you guys know one way or the other.","index":83,"end_time":199.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":193.41,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"If it doesn''t fix it, then, Natalie, I think maybe we start using our transfer folder for this kind of thing, and we can maybe test drive that to see if that solves the problem as well.","index":84,"end_time":209.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":199.89,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because it is really weird.","index":85,"end_time":211.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":209.82,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like.","index":86,"end_time":211.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":211.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, just subtle differences.","index":87,"end_time":213.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":211.5,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But I look at my.","index":88,"end_time":215.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":213.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, I look at them and I''m like, I know it''s off.","index":89,"end_time":217.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":215.02,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, I can tell just because I look at that red as an example, all day, every day, and twice on Saturday, it feels like.","index":90,"end_time":225.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":217.9,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And, you know, after a while, you can just.","index":91,"end_time":227.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":225.38,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You can just see it.","index":92,"end_time":228.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":227.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":93,"end_time":228.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":228.62,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Collins, quit laughing.","index":94,"end_time":230.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":228.94,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I can see you laughing.","index":95,"end_time":231.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":230.46,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Quit laughing.","index":96,"end_time":232.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":231.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":233.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I also just.","index":98,"end_time":234.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lou, I haven''t had a chance to talk to you about it, but I talked to Nina and Natalie Ross about our conversation with testing these out and also possibly using the Adobe file transfer method as well.","index":99,"end_time":247.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":100,"end_time":248.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":247.96,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So let me share my screen for this one, the first one.","index":101,"end_time":252.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.88,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So you can see here, this one, there were some small changes.","index":102,"end_time":259.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":253.56,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So here the logo on the bottom right corner is reduced in size, so it gets a little bit more breathing room.","index":103,"end_time":265.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.2,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":104,"end_time":266.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":265.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Then we have.","index":105,"end_time":267.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.23,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Then here is the file.","index":106,"end_time":269.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.83,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Here we have the file that.","index":107,"end_time":270.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.23,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"It has all the colors that.","index":108,"end_time":272.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":270.35,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The correct colors, like the correct gradients, colors and all that.","index":109,"end_time":277.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.75,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"For the images on tops from the folder that I got, some of the images were kind of tricky to fit into this frame.","index":110,"end_time":285.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So you might see that here on the left corner, you can see.","index":111,"end_time":289.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.15,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"I mean, that''s fine.","index":112,"end_time":291.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":289.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It was just, I think the initial placement of some of them.","index":113,"end_time":294.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":291.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"One of them looked like the dude''s head was floating.","index":114,"end_time":298.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":295.55,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, floating was cut off at the neck.","index":115,"end_time":299.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":298.11,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, it looked like a floating head across the top of the white box.","index":116,"end_time":302.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":299.93,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And I was just like, okay, that''s creepy.","index":117,"end_time":304.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":302.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Let''s not do that.","index":118,"end_time":306.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":305.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That said, though, if the.","index":119,"end_time":309.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":307.61,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The library of images that we have is like, I think this is fine, to be clear, but if we are using images that aren''t working, let''s go to Shutterstock or whatever.","index":120,"end_time":320.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":309.69,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Let''s find something stock that we can put in.","index":121,"end_time":322.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":320.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, I''m totally okay with that.","index":122,"end_time":324.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":322.73,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I obviously would like to lean into our library, but if we have to go to stock, that''s fine.","index":123,"end_time":329.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":324.37,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I. I''m not.","index":124,"end_time":330.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":329.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re not gonna.","index":125,"end_time":331.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":330.79,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''m not gonna lose any sleep over it, that''s for sure.","index":126,"end_time":334.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":331.95,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Right.","index":127,"end_time":335.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So then.","index":128,"end_time":336.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":335.75,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"So, yeah, so then this, like, this file ended up looking really, like, sharp in terms of colors and all the stuff.","index":129,"end_time":342.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.27,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Everything is in the right place in the Right.","index":130,"end_time":344.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.79,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like gradients.","index":131,"end_time":345.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.59,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"The boxes are the same color iconography.","index":132,"end_time":349.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.03,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Also, I''m sorry, these gray boxes, they.","index":133,"end_time":353.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Look really solid gray to me, and maybe that''s just how I''m viewing it, but they are.","index":134,"end_time":360.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":353.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Usually.","index":135,"end_time":360.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":360.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"They''re quite a bit lighter in the normal file.","index":136,"end_time":364.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":360.68,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, we.","index":137,"end_time":365.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.88,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Can I switch it up?","index":138,"end_time":366.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.68,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Like, I made it a bit more dark, but we can switch it up to the lighter one.","index":139,"end_time":370.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.96,"speaker_name":"Lou Bogani"},{"text":"Can we just leave it at the lighter?","index":140,"end_time":372.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":370.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So here''s what''s going on in Rico land is that we''re kind of stepping away from that darker gray that we kind of had all over the place as the refresh, and I don''t want to go back to that.","index":141,"end_time":384,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":372.48,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So if we can just go back to that lighter gray that we had going on, maybe, you know, test drive, maybe to see how it looks.","index":142,"end_time":393.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":384,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That gradient that we used in the PowerPoint, you know, where it goes from that really light gray to the white wash. Sure.","index":143,"end_time":401.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":393.59,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":401.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":401.43,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Maybe see how that looks.","index":145,"end_time":403.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":401.87,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But I do like the.","index":146,"end_time":404.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":403.07,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"The like, I do like having the box.","index":147,"end_time":406.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":404.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It.","index":148,"end_time":407.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":406.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It makes everything stand out.","index":149,"end_time":409.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":407.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I just can''t have it quite that dark otherwise.","index":150,"end_time":412.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":409.27,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I know.","index":151,"end_time":412.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":412.39,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''ll just.","index":152,"end_time":413.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":412.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I''ll just be sending it back to you to.","index":153,"end_time":415.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":413.91,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"To change because.","index":154,"end_time":416.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":415.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah,