-- Meeting: Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2025-12-19 13:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2025-12-19 13:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KC9FN2MEQDYNVZFSBS7XGAN2',
    'Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan","Axel Völker","Eli Bebinger","Axel Völker","Colin Costigan","Bettina","MaximilianRabeler","HendrikPollex"}'::text[],
    2107,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01KC9FN2MEQDYNVZFSBS7XGAN2","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Strategy and Target Market Shift**\n\nThe team decided to **pause the current Hayreach campaign and switch focus from the US to the DACH region** to build more predictable demand for Desi Dollo (03:28).\n\n- **Colin Costigan outlined a goal to double qualified leads from one to two per week over the next two quarters** by targeting IT consulting firms in Germany, Austria, and Switzerland (08:13).\n    - The focus is on decision makers in resource management and operations within companies facing staffing and operational pressures.\n    - The sales cycle can vary widely, from immediate to up to two years, requiring tailored marketing assets for long-term nurture.\n    - This regional shift involves new ABM foundational documents and dynamic messaging customized for various job titles like HR, team leads, and resource managers.\n    - The approach aims to engage multiple stakeholders per company to start conversations broadly, rather than targeting a single contact.\n\n- **Maximilian Rabeler emphasized that smaller companies under 50 employees often do not require resource management tools**, and that multiple roles including HR and sales handle CV and skills management differently (12:12).\n    - This insight will inform segmentation and messaging to avoid irrelevant outreach.\n    - Colin and Max plan a detailed review of current customer data in Dynamics to refine job title targeting and personalized communication (15:09).\n\n- **The marketing roadmap includes new ads, email content, and lead funnels adapted for the DACH market**, with ongoing measurement and iteration based on results (09:33).\n    - The US campaign is ending while the DACH campaign is scheduled to launch in the first week of January to avoid the holiday low engagement period (29:15).\n    - Marketing technology and operational activities are tracked in the Pulse portal for transparency and collaboration.\n\n## **Lead Generation and Conversion Metrics**\n\nClear benchmarks and measurement frameworks are in place to track progress and optimize lead quality.\n\n- **Currently, the team averages approximately one qualified lead or demo request per week, with demo scheduling delays of two to three weeks** typical in the sales process (16:30).\n    - Leads are defined as decision makers engaging in discovery or demo calls.\n    - Tracking will be done via HubSpot, integrated with Microsoft Dynamics, with Max responsible for managing the tech stack and access (18:33).\n\n- **Free registrations average below one valid company per week after filtering out very small companies under 20 employees** (26:54).\n    - These registrations currently occur without marketing support, so targeted campaigns are expected to increase this number.\n    - Registration quality is a key concern, with many signups from companies unlikely to pay.\n\n- **Lead nurturing will involve both inbound and outbound campaigns**, with sales enablement materials and website resources to support prospects in longer sales cycles (18:47).\n    - The team will develop nurture workflows for prospects interested but not ready to buy, addressing contract lock-ins and timing issues.\n\n## **Product Offers and Marketing Assets**\n\nThe team evaluated existing offers and planned new content strategies aligned with regional preferences and concerns.\n\n- **The original offer of formatting 50 CVs into a skills matrix for free is unlikely to work in DACH due to data privacy concerns and reluctance to share CVs without formal agreements** (23:01).\n    - Max and Axel agreed that data privacy rules in Germany make this offer complicated and potentially off-putting.\n    - The team will seek simpler offers that prospects can engage with without legal hurdles.\n\n- **A proposed alternative is a self-guided demo using tools like Storylane, allowing prospects to explore Desi Dollo without registration or data sharing** (25:53).\n    - This aims to reduce friction and improve conversion rates compared to previous low-performing demos.\n    - The second ongoing offer is encouraging prospects to register for a free account and explore the system themselves.\n\n- **Colin described a content engine strategy using biweekly interviews with industry guests to generate multiple marketing assets** (20:48).\n    - Content will be distributed across podcasts, YouTube, and blog formats to boost SEO and brand positioning.\n    - Bettina will provide a list of potential interviewees for planning.\n    - The team decided to postpone previous US-focused interview plans until next year.\n\n## **Campaign Execution and Timeline**\n\nThe rollout plan balances preparation, localization, and resource allocation for an effective launch.\n\n- **Email domains are being warmed up for Bettina’s LinkedIn outreach, with an automated connection tool (Heyreach) to increase network growth starting immediately** (19:29).\n    - Bettina agreed to use her LinkedIn Pro account for outreach to maximize connection volume (19:48).\n    - Max is assigned responsibility for managing tools and technology integration on the client side (29:01).\n\n- **The updated ABM plan document and email sequences will be delivered next week for translation, followed by ad creatives the week after, using Figma files for easy review and localization** (28:45).\n    - The landing page will be rebuilt on desidollo.com to focus on the DACH audience, highlighting the Storylane demo and product features (30:18).\n    - The campaign launch is targeted for the first week of January to avoid holiday season engagement dips (29:15).\n\n- **The US campaign will conclude its ads and outreach today to prioritize resources on the DACH market** (29:15).\n\n## **Data, CRM Integration, and Analysis**\n\nData-driven decision making and CRM integration underpin campaign effectiveness and personalization.\n\n- **Max will analyze closed lost opportunities in Dynamics to identify timing, feature gaps, or other reasons for lost deals** (31:46).\n    - Bettina will provide insights on earlier sales stages and lead interactions.\n    - This analysis will inform personalized outreach and messaging to improve conversion rates on re-engagement campaigns.\n\n- **Marketing emails will use contact data sourced through Clay, which accesses LinkedIn’s contact database, including German email addresses** (34:07).\n    - This enables targeted outbound campaigns while respecting regional data regulations.\n    - Colin confirmed that all campaign signals and webhooks are documented in detail in the ABM plan for transparency and tracking (33:40).\n\n## **Team Roles and Collaboration**\n\nClear ownership and collaboration plans support smooth execution.\n\n- **Bettina is responsible for LinkedIn outreach and will provide interviewee contacts for the content strategy** (19:29, 20:48).\n- **Max manages the technical stack, tool access, CRM data extraction, and campaign monitoring** (18:33, 29:01).\n- **Colin leads the marketing strategy, content development, and campaign execution, coordinating with Axel, Eli, and others for regional adaptation**.\n- **The team will continue refining target personas and messaging through upcoming data reviews and meetings, with an immediate follow-up planned for Tuesday** (15:09).\n\nThis structured approach balances immediate campaign launches with ongoing data refinement and content development to grow qualified leads steadily in the DACH market.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","DACH Region","Lead Generation","Content Marketing","ABM Roadmap","Sales Enablement"],"overview":"- **Campaign Shift:** Hayreach campaign paused; focus now on DACH region to enhance demand for Desi Dollo.  \n- **Lead Goals:** Aim to double qualified leads to two per week targeting German-speaking IT consulting firms over two quarters.  \n- **Marketing Adaptation:** New ads and email content will launch in early January, improving engagement based on regional preferences.  \n- **Registration Challenges:** Free registrations currently below one valid company per week; targeted campaigns expected to improve quality.  \n- **Privacy Concerns:** Original CV offering unsuitable for DACH; exploring simpler alternatives like self-guided demos to ease engagement.  \n- **Data Analysis:** CRM integration to analyze lost opportunities and refine messaging for improved lead conversion rates.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare full presentation slide deck with client team post-meeting for review (14:55)\nSend instructions for connecting Heyreach tool to Bettina’s LinkedIn for automated outreach (19:29)\nDeliver updated ABM plan document and email sequences for translation by the Friday following the meeting (28:55)\nDeliver ad creative Figma files for translation the Monday after email sequences (29:00)\nStart drafting the DACH landing page focusing on a new demo experience for the campaign launch (30:18)\nFollow up with Max and Bettina to review closed-lost opportunities and personalize marketing approach (31:47)\n\n**Bettina**\nProvide list of potential guests for the content podcast series to Colin and marketing team (20:30)\nSupport translation of email sequences and ad creatives (28:55)\nHandle closed-lost opportunity details and coordinate feedback for refinement of sales and marketing messaging after holiday break (32:21)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nManage technical and tool stack integration including HubSpot, Pulse, Figma, and Clay (29:03)\nFilter and extract data on closed-lost opportunities from CRM for review (32:47)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nCoordinate internally for guest candidates for podcast and other marketing content (20:30)\nConfirm LinkedIn profiles and tool usage for outreach automation with Bettina (19:50)\nEngage in providing feedback on campaigns and support for translation and technology access (28:45)\n"},"duration":35.11000061035156,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":3,"name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"id":4,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":5,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":6,"name":"Bettina"},{"id":7,"name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"id":8,"name":"HendrikPollex"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sam.","index":0,"end_time":25.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Eli.","index":1,"end_time":194.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":2,"end_time":197.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How''s it going, Colin?","index":3,"end_time":198.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":197.31,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":198.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":198.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How are you?","index":5,"end_time":199.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very good, thank you.","index":6,"end_time":201.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was wondering.","index":7,"end_time":204.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":203.59,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So are we gonna keep the hay reach going?","index":8,"end_time":207.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":204.39,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"We''re probably not.","index":9,"end_time":209.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":10,"end_time":209.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we''re.","index":11,"end_time":210.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re switching the entire.","index":12,"end_time":211.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":13,"end_time":212.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":211.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Target focus.","index":14,"end_time":213.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I do.","index":15,"end_time":214.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m.","index":16,"end_time":215.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":214.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m good with turning that off for sure.","index":17,"end_time":217.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":215.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":219.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":219.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m actually pausing that today based on our conversation.","index":19,"end_time":222.149,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tuesday.","index":20,"end_time":222.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.149,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":21,"end_time":223.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":223.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":22,"end_time":224.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":223.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How''s it going with you?","index":23,"end_time":225.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":224.95,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Going well.","index":24,"end_time":227.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just gearing up for holiday season.","index":25,"end_time":230.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":227.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":231.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":230.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You off next week?","index":27,"end_time":232.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":231.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No, we''re actually just closed on Christmas.","index":28,"end_time":235.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":233.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or on the 25th and on the 1st.","index":29,"end_time":237.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":30,"end_time":239.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":238.76,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''ll probably be pretty slow, I imagine.","index":31,"end_time":244.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":248.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":247.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi, Natalie.","index":33,"end_time":252.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":251.16,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Hello.","index":34,"end_time":253.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie''s another strategist on our team.","index":35,"end_time":259.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is going to be joining our calls moving forward.","index":36,"end_time":261.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":37,"end_time":264.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":265.55,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":265.07,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":39,"end_time":266.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you as well.","index":40,"end_time":268.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":267.31,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":41,"end_time":275.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Morning.","index":42,"end_time":277.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":43,"end_time":288.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":288.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s pretty early in Mexico.","index":44,"end_time":296.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Da.","index":45,"end_time":297.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s 7:30am.","index":46,"end_time":301,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can I see a problem here?","index":47,"end_time":304.44,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":303,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s quite late.","index":48,"end_time":305.32,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":304.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Nice.","index":49,"end_time":318.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got a big team joining today.","index":50,"end_time":321.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.69,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yes, we do.","index":51,"end_time":322.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Hendrik.","index":52,"end_time":324.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Somehow my camera is not working pretty good as you can see.","index":53,"end_time":330.53,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":325.89,"speaker_name":"HendrikPollex"},{"text":"What''s going on.","index":54,"end_time":338.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":337.25,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s the correct one.","index":55,"end_time":341.45,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":340.57,"speaker_name":"HendrikPollex"},{"text":"There you go.","index":56,"end_time":342.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":57,"end_time":347.29,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":346.73,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Hey.","index":58,"end_time":349.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":348.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":59,"end_time":349.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fine.","index":60,"end_time":351.77,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":351.37,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And you?","index":61,"end_time":352.33,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":351.77,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":62,"end_time":353.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":63,"end_time":354.57,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":354.17,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Ready for holidays?","index":64,"end_time":356.89,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":355.61,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":65,"end_time":358.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is Axel or Johim joining?","index":66,"end_time":363.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hopefully they should.","index":67,"end_time":366.42,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":364.66,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"There''s Axel.","index":68,"end_time":368.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":69,"end_time":373.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":373.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey, Axel.","index":70,"end_time":375.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":71,"end_time":375.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Chris?","index":72,"end_time":376.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":376.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Good.","index":73,"end_time":377.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":377.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So Johan will join.","index":74,"end_time":379.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":378.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ve not seen him join.","index":75,"end_time":381.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wasn''t quite with him.","index":76,"end_time":384.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"He''s joining.","index":77,"end_time":385.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":384.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":78,"end_time":385.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Max, Is he not joining?","index":79,"end_time":390.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":388.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m here.","index":80,"end_time":391.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":390.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m here.","index":81,"end_time":391.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":391.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where are you?","index":82,"end_time":393.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":393.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you see me?","index":83,"end_time":394.56,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":393.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":84,"end_time":394.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You do a big.","index":85,"end_time":395.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I see you now.","index":86,"end_time":397.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":396.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":87,"end_time":398.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":397.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You''ve seen me today quite a few times before.","index":88,"end_time":402.44,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":400.36,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":403.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s not showing everyone here for me.","index":90,"end_time":407.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":405.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, a lot of people here now.","index":91,"end_time":409,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":407.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we have a new colleague on your side.","index":92,"end_time":413.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":409.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We do.","index":93,"end_time":414.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello, Johim.","index":94,"end_time":416.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":95,"end_time":417.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":417.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Nice to see you as well.","index":96,"end_time":420.17,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":418.21,"speaker_name":"HendrikPollex"},{"text":"Yeah, we got a.","index":97,"end_time":420.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":420.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got a big team here.","index":98,"end_time":422.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":420.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":99,"end_time":422.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":422.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Wow.","index":100,"end_time":423.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":422.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we have one new face from our side.","index":101,"end_time":426.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":424.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is Natalie.","index":102,"end_time":426.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s another strategist that.","index":103,"end_time":427.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":426.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is joining the account to help out with everything as we were transitioning our target market and everything like that.","index":104,"end_time":433.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":435.57,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":435.17,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Nice to meet all of you.","index":106,"end_time":436.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, nice to meet you.","index":107,"end_time":438.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":436.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And Axel, did you want to do.","index":108,"end_time":441.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":440.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should we do like a round of introductions or should we just hop into it?","index":109,"end_time":445.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we only have about 27 minutes left.","index":110,"end_time":447.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can just start.","index":111,"end_time":449.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think probably met most of the persons.","index":112,"end_time":452.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":449.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":113,"end_time":453.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And guys, we''ll all get to know.","index":114,"end_time":455.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":453.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Each other over the next few weeks as well, so.","index":115,"end_time":457.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":116,"end_time":458.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I will share my screen.","index":117,"end_time":460.459,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, can everyone see that?","index":118,"end_time":463.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":119,"end_time":464.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":463.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":120,"end_time":465.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so based on our conversation.","index":121,"end_time":468.46,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":465.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On Tuesday, Axel, which was a kickoff.","index":122,"end_time":470.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For switching our target market focus from.","index":123,"end_time":474.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":470.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The United States to the Docs region.","index":124,"end_time":476.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is our proposed marketing roadmap for Decidalo focused in that region.","index":125,"end_time":481.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":477.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I want to talk through the strategy, the goals that we''re optimizing for.","index":126,"end_time":485.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":482.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the channel tactics that we will use to get there.","index":127,"end_time":488.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":128,"end_time":491.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":489.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So, you know, you''ve seen a previous.","index":129,"end_time":495.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":493.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Version of our roadmap when we wrote.","index":130,"end_time":496.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It for the United States market.","index":131,"end_time":497.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":496.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is really designed to move Desi do into more predictable demand.","index":132,"end_time":502.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":498.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys have mentioned some numbers.","index":133,"end_time":505.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":503.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max, you were, you were given some detail as well of right now we kind of have one lead coming in per week.","index":134,"end_time":512.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":506.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''ll get into our goals.","index":135,"end_time":513.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":512.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Slide a little bit later on.","index":136,"end_time":514.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But virtually what we''re looking to do.","index":137,"end_time":517.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is through the course of the next two quarters, increase that to.","index":138,"end_time":522.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":517.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To an average of two leads per week.","index":139,"end_time":524.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And obviously we''re hoping to get more, but we want to have that solid.","index":140,"end_time":528.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":525.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Baseline of measurement and, and then we''ll activate a few channels to really get out into the market a little bit further, especially in the DAX region.","index":141,"end_time":537.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re looking for qualified conversions and.","index":142,"end_time":541.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":537.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Conversations that come out of those.","index":143,"end_time":543.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So decision makers at IT services and IT consulting firms, and obviously we''ve talked about the sales cycle can be a bit unpredictable.","index":144,"end_time":553.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":543.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It can be extremely short if someone''s.","index":145,"end_time":555.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ready to make a decision, or it.","index":146,"end_time":556.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":555.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can be upwards of two years in some cases.","index":147,"end_time":558.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll have to develop a lot of marketing assets to, to help provide.","index":148,"end_time":563.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some fodder for those prospects that are.","index":149,"end_time":566.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":563.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the longer sales cycles.","index":150,"end_time":567.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not going to spend too much time on this slide.","index":151,"end_time":573.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":570.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the same model that we''ve been using.","index":152,"end_time":575.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The important thing to note is now that we are rewriting the roadmap, we''ll.","index":153,"end_time":580.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":575.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have some updated foundational documents that outline the entire ABM approach and strategy now that we are switching from Eli to Bettina and and targeting different prospects in a different region.","index":154,"end_time":591.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we will go through our.","index":155,"end_time":593.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Regular looking at the measurements and metrics.","index":156,"end_time":596.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":593.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then making changes to our execution based on that.","index":157,"end_time":599.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that would be new ads, new email content, new leads that we''re funneling.","index":158,"end_time":604.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":599.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Into the campaigns themselves.","index":159,"end_time":606.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":160,"end_time":608.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":608.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So like I mentioned, this roadmap is built for IT consulting firms across the docked region, mainly pain points being that they''ve outgrown spreadsheets, they have a.","index":161,"end_time":619.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":610.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bench, even though that we need to be careful of using that exact term in specific regions.","index":162,"end_time":624.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are feeling like they need to enhance their utilization.","index":163,"end_time":628.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":625.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re having some staffing and delivery pressure and on the operations side.","index":164,"end_time":633.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not only stemming on the resource management side, they are dealing with.","index":165,"end_time":637.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":634.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The pain every day, but the operation side is certainly looking to enhance their tech stack, their visibility into actual utilization of their team.","index":166,"end_time":646.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to pull up what the ideal target account is.","index":167,"end_time":652.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":648.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so these are the parameters that.","index":168,"end_time":653.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would use to identify companies in the docs region and then we would.","index":169,"end_time":657.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":653.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get into job titles after that.","index":170,"end_time":659.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So obviously location, Germany, Austria, Switzerland, the industry being IT services and consulting.","index":171,"end_time":665.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":659.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know I had this on Tuesday, but just want to verify the.","index":172,"end_time":668.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":665.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Revenue and employee levels as well as the technologies.","index":173,"end_time":670.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the revenue we typically don''t really know.","index":174,"end_time":675.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We look at the employees.","index":175,"end_time":676.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s easier to figure out on LinkedIn.","index":176,"end_time":679.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":676.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For example, but yeah, I think it''s that.","index":177,"end_time":681.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the employee range is that.","index":178,"end_time":683.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":681.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s probably relates to that revenue.","index":179,"end_time":685.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":683.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":180,"end_time":686.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And revenue is.","index":181,"end_time":687.569,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":686.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It tends to be a lesser factor in the way that we define these parameters because depending on any source that.","index":182,"end_time":693.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":687.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You look at, it will be a different range.","index":183,"end_time":695.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":184,"end_time":697.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":697.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And so the ideal person or prospect that we would pull out of these companies would be someone in resource management.","index":185,"end_time":708.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":699.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or with an operations title.","index":186,"end_time":710.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is not a real company, but this is someone that we have developed a mind map for or an empathy map to determine what are the pain points they''re feeling and what messaging.","index":187,"end_time":720.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":710.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would resonate with them so that they move forward in a conversation with Desi Dalo.","index":188,"end_time":724.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s not the whole truth.","index":189,"end_time":732.07,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":729.59,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":190,"end_time":732.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s only for our resource management features.","index":191,"end_time":735.43,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":732.27,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like we, at least from what I got is that the, like the companies start lower with their skills and cvs because from quite a few of them we know that they just had some SharePoint with Word documents and these were the CVs and the skills were maintained inside those Word documents.","index":192,"end_time":756.68,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":735.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And every time they needed to send out a cv, it''s like half an hour of work.","index":193,"end_time":763.08,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":757.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But who''s doing.","index":194,"end_time":764.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":764.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Isn''t that also resource managers doing like the poi?","index":195,"end_time":768.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":764.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And so I think.","index":196,"end_time":769.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Who''s that?","index":197,"end_time":769.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":769.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it''s very different.","index":198,"end_time":771.72,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":770.12,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, sometimes it''s even HR and sales and sometimes it''s just some team manager.","index":199,"end_time":780,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":771.96,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And the team managers may have different roles depending on like what kind of team they have.","index":200,"end_time":786.3,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":780,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Whether these are project managers or, I don''t know, SAP consultants, whatever.","index":201,"end_time":793.34,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":786.3,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, this is a really good conversation.","index":202,"end_time":798.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":796.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To have right now.","index":203,"end_time":799.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Max, the approach that we take is not only picking one prospect at each company, we want to talk to multiple prospects at each company.","index":204,"end_time":807.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":800.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And really the analogy is like starting the conversation around the water cooler.","index":205,"end_time":811.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":808.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess in most companies that is the virtual water cooler as there''s a lot of remote work.","index":206,"end_time":816.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we want to have.","index":207,"end_time":818.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":816.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the coffee maker in Germany.","index":208,"end_time":820.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":209,"end_time":821.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of water coolers here.","index":210,"end_time":822.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":821.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":211,"end_time":823.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to have content that resonates with people, you know, in the day to day.","index":212,"end_time":827.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":823.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I just got this RFP and I need to pick a list of consultants and send their resumes over in a single format.","index":213,"end_time":835.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":827.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then there''s also the operation side and as you''re mentioning HR and maybe some team leads.","index":214,"end_time":840.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":835.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we need to, we need to definitely dive into that a little bit further.","index":215,"end_time":844.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s also, I mean it''s case sensitive.","index":216,"end_time":847.15,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":844.11,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":217,"end_time":847.43,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":847.15,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Because for example, you had this fast growing IT thing and I think that''s something like smaller companies, for example, I don''t know, 50, 50 people working there, 50 employees.","index":218,"end_time":857.39,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":847.43,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"They don''t need a resource management tool because everybody knows everybody and they just can work with some, I don''t know, canvas boards or something and then when they grow too quickly, then they get that this is not sufficient anymore and then they are looking for a tool and that''s maybe where we could jump in for sure.","index":219,"end_time":877.78,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":857.95,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But also it''s like the competition for resource management tools is way bigger than for SCV management tools.","index":220,"end_time":884.5,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":878.66,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And also like this RFP automation thing is closely related to both.","index":221,"end_time":890.13,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":884.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Definitely.","index":222,"end_time":890.85,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":890.13,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But it may also have some other target group like inside the same companies.","index":223,"end_time":896.69,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":891.41,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But the people.","index":224,"end_time":897.97,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":896.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Probably, maybe not.","index":225,"end_time":899.09,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":898.05,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Maybe sometimes, yes, I don''t know.","index":226,"end_time":901.57,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":899.09,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But yeah, keep going with your, with your presentation.","index":227,"end_time":904.77,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":902.37,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I just didn''t want to interrupt that long.","index":228,"end_time":907.49,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":904.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s a great conversation to have.","index":229,"end_time":911.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":909.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know that you and I.","index":230,"end_time":911.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are meeting on Tuesday as well to.","index":231,"end_time":912.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":911.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dive a little bit more into the data of current customers and going through Dynamics as well.","index":232,"end_time":916.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we''ll be able to extract more job titles out of that and then we can talk about really the way that we set up our communication.","index":233,"end_time":923.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":916.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It has dynamic content.","index":234,"end_time":924.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":923.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we say like we''ll put a.","index":235,"end_time":926.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":924.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bracket for pain point one, but it''ll be different for HR than it would be for resource management than it would be for Director of operations.","index":236,"end_time":932.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t need to spend too much time on this slide.","index":237,"end_time":937.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":935.889,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the storyboard framework that we have built out for Decidal.","index":238,"end_time":943.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":937.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this just goes through making the.","index":239,"end_time":945.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Prospect a hero in this journey and.","index":240,"end_time":948.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":945.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How desi Dollo is able to lead.","index":241,"end_time":950.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Them on the right journey to experience.","index":242,"end_time":952.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":950.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Success and avoid failure.","index":243,"end_time":953.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll also be sending over this slide deck after the call for you guys to read the details.","index":244,"end_time":957.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just want to make the most of our time today and go through the highlights.","index":245,"end_time":960.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys are obviously very familiar with your tools.","index":246,"end_time":965.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is just a matrix that goes through all of the different offerings.","index":247,"end_time":968.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of Desi Dollo and then we also take a look at competition.","index":248,"end_time":973.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":968.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are companies that are located in areas like London, Stockholm.","index":249,"end_time":977.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":973.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then comparing Dusty Dollo from a market share standpoint of what is your organic traffic and SEO scores, social media analysis, content strategy, paid media strategy, and brand positioning.","index":250,"end_time":990.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are all numbers that we are looking to enhance as we create new marketing assets in these regions.","index":251,"end_time":996.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so getting into the meat of it.","index":252,"end_time":1001.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":999.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as we talked about on Tuesday, the current benchmark that you guys have is approximately one qualified lead per week.","index":253,"end_time":1008.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1001.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did want to click clarify.","index":254,"end_time":1010.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1008.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that a one qualified lead or one qualified demo call?","index":255,"end_time":1013.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1010.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this more is often basically the same for us, I would say, because.","index":256,"end_time":1022.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1017.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Typically a lead is a request for a demo.","index":257,"end_time":1025.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1022.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, I guess what I want to clarify there is like, are they always scheduling that week or like, do you get a lead with a form fill?","index":258,"end_time":1032.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1025.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know that there''s an option to schedule like based on their availability.","index":259,"end_time":1035.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1032.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but then.","index":260,"end_time":1035.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but then it''s basically just deferred.","index":261,"end_time":1038.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So then we have maybe this week to demo from the guy who requested.","index":262,"end_time":1041.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1038.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It last week or something.","index":263,"end_time":1042.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1041.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think that kind of averages out.","index":264,"end_time":1045.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1042.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":265,"end_time":1046.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so we''re averaging one lead a week.","index":266,"end_time":1048.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1046.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not exactly translating to one demo call per week.","index":267,"end_time":1051.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1048.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As in like you can like if.","index":268,"end_time":1054.739,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1053.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Someone delays or there''s just a delay.","index":269,"end_time":1057.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.739,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But it''s after a few weeks.","index":270,"end_time":1059.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1057.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would say, Betty, what is that?","index":271,"end_time":1061.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You have one demo per week or something or what would you say?","index":272,"end_time":1063.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1061.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, probably.","index":273,"end_time":1064.82,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1063.86,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"I would say when we got a lead, it may take up to two or three weeks, then we can schedule a demo.","index":274,"end_time":1074.62,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1065.58,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":275,"end_time":1076.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1075.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s great.","index":276,"end_time":1078.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what we want to do is track first meetings.","index":277,"end_time":1081.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1078.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those demo calls with target accounts in the docked region and that''ll be.","index":278,"end_time":1084.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1081.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Through inbound and outbound marketing campaigns.","index":279,"end_time":1087.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ve identified qualified lead as a decision maker from a defined target account.","index":280,"end_time":1091.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1087.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is engaging in a discovery or demo call.","index":281,"end_time":1094.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where this will be measured is we do have the free account for HubSpot that we have created for you guys.","index":282,"end_time":1101.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1096.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can give you access at any point, but that is just tracking our marketing activities with Those contacts and then we share that information with you once they convert, obviously.","index":283,"end_time":1110.049,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1101.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you can upload them into Microsoft Dynamics.","index":284,"end_time":1112.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.049,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":285,"end_time":1114.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1113.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you give max access because he''ll.","index":286,"end_time":1116.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Do the tech stack on our side.","index":287,"end_time":1118.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1116.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1119.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, of course.","index":289,"end_time":1125.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":290,"end_time":1126.34,"speaker_id":8,"start_time":1125.78,"speaker_name":"HendrikPollex"},{"text":"Okay, so we are looking to double the current benchmark of leads coming in per week.","index":291,"end_time":1131.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1127.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, we''ve talked about the sales cycle can be lengthy.","index":292,"end_time":1136.019,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1133.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to not only develop this outbound strategy, but provide some sales materials, sales enablement, and then some different resources to place on the website also.","index":293,"end_time":1146.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1136.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That can go into something like a nurture workflow for someone who has shown some interest, but maybe has indicated that it''s not their time to buy.","index":294,"end_time":1154.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe they''re locked into a contract with someone else, but they are interested.","index":295,"end_time":1157.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":296,"end_time":1161.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1160.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Any questions on any goals or anything here?","index":297,"end_time":1163.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1161.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not for me.","index":298,"end_time":1168.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1166.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then outlining this quarter.","index":299,"end_time":1170.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1169.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve already started warming up email domains for Bettina.","index":300,"end_time":1174.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1170.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Bettina, I''ll also be sending you.","index":301,"end_time":1177.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1175.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Instructions to connect to a tool called Heyreach.","index":302,"end_time":1179.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This will be connecting your LinkedIn profile.","index":303,"end_time":1181.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we can automate connection requests and messages going out from your profile.","index":304,"end_time":1186.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1181.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we said we''re going to use your Pro.","index":305,"end_time":1190.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1188.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That probably makes the most sense if.","index":306,"end_time":1191.429,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You use your LinkedIn or.","index":307,"end_time":1193.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1191.429,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s okay.","index":308,"end_time":1194.95,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1193.87,"speaker_name":"Bettina"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":309,"end_time":1195.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1194.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, you''ll get a lot of new connections.","index":310,"end_time":1198.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1196.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not so.","index":311,"end_time":1198.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1198.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not that you wonder.","index":312,"end_time":1200.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1198.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A lot.","index":313,"end_time":1204.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1210.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1209.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so these are the initiatives for the quarter.","index":315,"end_time":1212.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1210.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are in the midst of rebuilding the ABM campaign to work in the docked region.","index":316,"end_time":1217.8,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1212.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So working on a new target market list, we are warming up the email domains and then we are also drafting the messaging that we will send over to you guys for translation as well.","index":317,"end_time":1227.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1217.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As the ad copy that we will send over for translation as part of this.","index":318,"end_time":1232.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also feel, and actually you mentioned this on Tuesday, much stronger that we can land guests on the content series.","index":319,"end_time":1239.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1232.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The utilization effect and use that as a pure content engine.","index":320,"end_time":1242.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1239.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if you have some initial guests in mind.","index":321,"end_time":1245.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1243.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you said that some people.","index":322,"end_time":1246.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1245.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have expressed some interest, is that correct?","index":323,"end_time":1248.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we have.","index":324,"end_time":1249.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would.","index":325,"end_time":1249.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1249.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So Bethy Hasan is on tag and holding.","index":326,"end_time":1253.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1249.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think Betty can pretty easily come up with a list of people that you could interview.","index":327,"end_time":1259.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s it would be as.","index":328,"end_time":1264.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As many people as.","index":329,"end_time":1265.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1264.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you guys want to talk to.","index":330,"end_time":1267.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1265.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that we usually structure this is coming out with a.","index":331,"end_time":1270.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1267.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A recording every two weeks.","index":332,"end_time":1271.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1270.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These would be syndicated to Spotify, Apple Podcast.","index":333,"end_time":1275.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1272.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could even post it on a YouTube channel.","index":334,"end_time":1277.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1275.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also we want to create a.","index":335,"end_time":1279,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1277.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Page on your website for it.","index":336,"end_time":1280.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1279,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":337,"end_time":1282.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That certainly is, is up to you guys though at the clip that you want to record these episodes.","index":338,"end_time":1288.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1284.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also something that we do tend.","index":339,"end_time":1290.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1288.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To do is create a framework.","index":340,"end_time":1292.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Axel, Eli, Yohim, you guys have.","index":341,"end_time":1295.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1292.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Seen the initial framework that we built when Eli was going to record an episode with David.","index":342,"end_time":1298.489,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1295.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Bettina, if you''re able to send over a list of potential interviewees, we.","index":343,"end_time":1303.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1298.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can build out a framework.","index":344,"end_time":1304.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is just, it''s not putting words in your mouth.","index":345,"end_time":1306.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1304.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But just based on our research here, some trending industry topics, here''s something that.","index":346,"end_time":1310.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1306.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The interviewee may want to respond with.","index":347,"end_time":1313.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":348,"end_time":1316.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":349,"end_time":1317.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1317.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Adam, so we''re not doing the.","index":350,"end_time":1319.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1317.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"David one for now, right?","index":351,"end_time":1320.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1319.15,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, no, not this year.","index":352,"end_time":1322.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":353,"end_time":1323.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1323.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t think because I haven''t managed.","index":354,"end_time":1325.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1323.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"To review it and this year I''m.","index":355,"end_time":1327.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1325.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All tied up with year end stuff.","index":356,"end_time":1329.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1327.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we can, we can basically check next year if we want to do it there.","index":357,"end_time":1334.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1330.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":358,"end_time":1336.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And out of those we generate multiple assets and those being multiple short form videos, the actual full episode video, quote.","index":359,"end_time":1344.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1336.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cards, things like that.","index":360,"end_time":1346.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we can also generate SEO, optimized blogs, white papers, any sort of downloadable series of ads.","index":361,"end_time":1353.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1346.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can generate all of those from.","index":362,"end_time":1356,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys having a conversation.","index":363,"end_time":1357.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1356,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why we refer to it as.","index":364,"end_time":1358.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1357.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A content engine after that.","index":365,"end_time":1361.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1358.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually we talked about initially with our US campaign, we had built out the subdomain website of us.desidollar.com obviously not relevant for the docs region.","index":366,"end_time":1371.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1362.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are going to build landing pages directly on the desidollo.com website.","index":367,"end_time":1376.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, makes more sense.","index":368,"end_time":1379.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1377.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":369,"end_time":1379.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1379.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I have our offers detailed here as well.","index":370,"end_time":1383.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1381.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to start with both offers that we have run already and then.","index":371,"end_time":1388.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1383.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are going to ideate on a.","index":372,"end_time":1390.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Third to rotate in if we identify.","index":373,"end_time":1393.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1390.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That one of these isn''t gaining any traction.","index":374,"end_time":1395.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the first offer that we had come up with was getting 50 CVS formatted and thrown into a skills matrix for free.","index":375,"end_time":1403.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1396.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like this still resonates with.","index":376,"end_time":1406.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1404.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Prospects in the docs region.","index":377,"end_time":1407.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you agree?","index":378,"end_time":1408.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, it didn''t really work for the US maybe I think the LinkedIn people just got it wrong.","index":379,"end_time":1415.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you have, if you read resume on LinkedIn then you get all the people looking for jobs.","index":380,"end_time":1421.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1415.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We may not because in Germany would you cv we may not have that problem because that is kind of a.","index":381,"end_time":1427.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1422.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Very specific term that''s not really used for recruiting.","index":382,"end_time":1430.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1427.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think.","index":383,"end_time":1432.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And maybe Betty or Max can answer that.","index":384,"end_time":1435.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think people here are more concerned about like data privacy and I think people will be very reluctant to just send out 50 cvs if they don''t have a data processing agreement and stuff like that.","index":385,"end_time":1451.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1435.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I''m not sure that''s going to have some concerns.","index":386,"end_time":1455.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1452.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I definitely agree.","index":387,"end_time":1457.3,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1456.18,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean thing here is, I mean what we, for example, what we did I think a year ago, is that if you now newly register to our software that you directly have 25 demo profiles which are well filled and because before like you register for some software and the first thing it asks you is hey, upload some data.","index":388,"end_time":1480.25,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1457.38,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And so on the one side it''s definitely you can test with good data better than with your own usually.","index":389,"end_time":1487.93,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1481.29,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But second is definitely in Germany and the regions around it.","index":390,"end_time":1493.29,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1488.57,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s not that thing to directly send your data everywhere, sometimes even because you may not because company things.","index":391,"end_time":1500.89,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1493.29,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":392,"end_time":1502.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And do we think that''s a simple enough hurdle to overcome just by a step being getting a data use agreement signed between them actually providing the data.","index":393,"end_time":1513.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1502.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like they would show interest, we would get that data agreement signed and then they would send over the resume.","index":394,"end_time":1517.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1513.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or the, the cvs.","index":395,"end_time":1518.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is that I think that if the people we target, they will not.","index":396,"end_time":1526.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Feel in the position to do that.","index":397,"end_time":1528.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1526.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They would have to ask their data privacy officer and then it becomes complicated.","index":398,"end_time":1534.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think that makes it just far.","index":399,"end_time":1535.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1534.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Too complicated for them.","index":400,"end_time":1536.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1535.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":401,"end_time":1536.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1536.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":402,"end_time":1539.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1538.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You need to look for something that''s, that''s easier where some person can do that without having to worry about getting.","index":403,"end_time":1548.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Problems from his data security guy.","index":404,"end_time":1553.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1550.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":405,"end_time":1554.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then the first thing, and we''ll take some time to think through some more offers, but the first substitute that comes to mind is using a tool like storylane and I pulled that up the.","index":406,"end_time":1565.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1555.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other day and I know I''ve mentioned that before, where we can build a.","index":407,"end_time":1568.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guided demo where it''s just you record yourself kind of clicking around inside the platform and we''re able to control what the screen says and the call to.","index":408,"end_time":1578.32,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1568.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Action that comes at the end of it and it''s sort of a self.","index":409,"end_time":1580.28,"speak