    '{"id":"01KC7ST0FA3C02ZMDFG61FJQ5H","title":"Inside Tracker // New North Weekly Connect","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Distribution Expansion**\n\nThe team decided to expand the podcast’s presence beyond Apple Podcasts and Spotify to reach more listeners across other platforms.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell confirmed** adding the podcast to additional channels is straightforward and usually takes **24 to 48 hours** for review after submission (02:02).  \n    - This move aims to increase overall reach and capture audiences not accessible through the current platforms.  \n    - Baylee offered support to handle submissions, easing the operational load on Gil.  \n    - Gil agreed to submit the podcast to these new platforms promptly to accelerate visibility.  \n    - Expanding distribution aligns with the goal of sustained growth and wider brand exposure beyond current markets.\n\n- They agreed to **exclude YouTube from new platform submissions** since videos are already posted there (03:04).  \n    - This avoids redundant efforts and focuses resources on untapped podcast directories.  \n    - Baylee confirmed video posting on YouTube covers that channel’s audience well.  \n    - This strategic choice optimizes workload and leverages existing content effectively.\n\n## **Performance Metrics and Recognition**\n\nThe podcast achieved significant growth milestones, showing strong audience engagement and industry recognition.\n\n- The podcast hit **over 1 million total downloads this year**, with **174,000 downloads** in the current year alone, reflecting steady growth (07:33).  \n    - This positions the podcast well above the 90% of shows that fail before episode three, having delivered **24 episodes averaging two per month** (06:28).  \n    - Consistent publishing frequency is a major factor in maintaining and growing the audience base.  \n    - Baylee highlighted that the most popular topics focus on core health themes like muscle, protein, and fundamentals, guiding future content strategy.  \n    - Gil’s posting of episodes like the one with his parents shows potential for personal connection-driven content to engage listeners.\n\n- The podcast earned **top rankings on multiple platforms**, including **#137 in U.S. health fitness, #25 in Singapore health fitness, top 100 on Good Net Podcast, top 5 longevity podcast on Feedspot, and top 3 on Good Pods** (04:13, 09:31).  \n    - These rankings validate the podcast’s quality and help attract sponsorship opportunities as Gil noted (10:30).  \n    - Recognition on these platforms serves as strong marketing collateral to build credibility with advertisers.  \n    - The data shows the podcast is gaining international traction, though the primary aim remains to climb U.S. rankings.  \n    - Tracking these positions regularly provides insight into global market penetration and growth areas.\n\n## **Content Promotion and Social Strategy**\n\nTo build on growth, the team agreed to intensify promotion efforts across social platforms while maintaining audience comfort.\n\n- Baylee recommended **posting about episodes once or twice a week** as a balanced approach to keep engagement without overwhelming followers (11:45).  \n    - Gil plans to use the **Longevity by Design LinkedIn account** to post daily, leveraging a dedicated channel to avoid personal overload (12:12).  \n    - This approach spreads content efficiently and keeps Gil’s personal channels from being saturated.  \n    - Reposting or lightly sharing content helps maintain visibility without excessive new effort.  \n    - The goal is steady, organic audience growth with loyal listeners rather than aggressive paid tactics.\n\n- The team agreed to continue producing **vertical social clips and updated thumbnails**, which have already contributed positively to engagement (07:15).  \n    - These visual assets help attract attention on social feeds and improve brand consistency.  \n    - Using video clips on YouTube and LinkedIn extends reach beyond audio-only listeners.  \n    - Baylee encouraged tying content back to Gil’s company, **Inside Tracker**, to strengthen brand association and commercial potential (10:44).  \n    - This integrated approach supports both audience growth and monetization goals.\n\n## **Operational Review and Next Steps**\n\nThe partnership between Gil and Baylee’s team is strong, with clear plans for continued collaboration and ongoing improvement.\n\n- Baylee shared that all edits for two recent episodes are complete, with Gil planning to review and post soon (05:41).  \n    - This steady content pipeline supports the twice-monthly release schedule proven effective.  \n    - Baylee prepared a detailed **end-of-year review for 2023** with key stats to share with Gil’s team for internal and marketing use (05:17).  \n    - This report will provide useful data to guide 2024 planning and sponsorship discussions.\n\n- Gil affirmed commitment to continuing the podcast without interruption, signaling stable content delivery and partnership longevity (13:00).  \n    - Baylee expressed enthusiasm for next year’s work and willingness to support growth initiatives.  \n    - They agreed to keep focusing on proven topics and promotion strategies for 2024 to sustain momentum.  \n    - Sharing the review and data promptly will help Gil and his team make informed decisions on marketing and sponsorship approaches.\n\n## **Market Insights and Competitive Context**\n\nGil’s observation about competitors using paid promotion highlights the team’s preference for organic growth and long-term loyalty.\n\n- Gil noted that some popular podcasts boost views through paid ads, which might explain their higher numbers despite similar quality (07:48).  \n    - Baylee stressed that organic growth, though slower, builds a more loyal and engaged audience over time (08:21).  \n    - This philosophy favors sustainable brand equity rather than short-term spikes that may not retain listeners.  \n    - The team’s marketing and promotion plans reflect this long-term strategy, avoiding overuse of paid audience buys.  \n    - This approach aims to differentiate the podcast in a crowded market by focusing on authenticity and consistent value.","outline":null,"keywords":["podcast distribution","podcast rankings","podcast downloads","episode promotion","social media strategy","podcast milestones"],"overview":"- **Podcast Expansion:** The podcast will join other platforms to grow audience reach beyond Apple Podcasts and Spotify.  \n- **Growth Milestones:** Over 1 million total downloads this year with 174,000 from 2025, exceeding industry averages for episode longevity.  \n- **Top Rankings:** Achieved high positions in several regions, strengthening prospects for sponsorship opportunities and international visibility.  \n- **Promotion Strategy:** Posting frequency set to once or twice weekly to enhance audience engagement without overwhelming them.  \n- **Operational Review:** Edits for recent episodes completed; end-of-year review prepared to aid 2024 planning and sponsorship discussions.  \n- **Long-term Growth Focus:** Emphasizing organic growth over paid promotions to build a loyal audience and differentiate in a crowded market.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAssist in submitting Gil’s podcast to additional platforms beyond Apple Podcasts and Spotify (02:12)\nSend Gil the end-of-year podcast performance review including stats and recognition rankings for his team’s use (05:11)\n\n**Gil**\nReview the two edited podcast episodes received and post them, with plans to view one with his parents soon (05:53)\nConsider lengthening social media promotion duration and attempt additional social video clip sharing (10:44)\nExplore posting more frequently via Longevity by Design’s LinkedIn and Instagram channels to increase reach without personal overposting (12:19)\n"},"duration":13.59000015258789,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Gil"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Mostly just spending time with my family.","index":0,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":1,"end_time":3.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.96,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s in the.","index":2,"end_time":5.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.76,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"In the area or you''re traveling far?","index":3,"end_time":9.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.88,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"We''re going.","index":4,"end_time":11.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My family rented a cabin.","index":5,"end_time":15.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s about like an hour, hour and a half away from where we live.","index":6,"end_time":20.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just gonna go up in the mountains and hopefully we''re still in Utah.","index":7,"end_time":26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, still in Utah.","index":8,"end_time":27.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":9,"end_time":27.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.47,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, not too far.","index":10,"end_time":28.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Going skiing or.","index":11,"end_time":29.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.67,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Not.","index":12,"end_time":30.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.71,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Probably not skiing.","index":13,"end_time":33.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That would be fun though.","index":14,"end_time":34.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think mostly just we''re gonna play games and maybe watch movies.","index":15,"end_time":40.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My family is.","index":16,"end_time":42.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They.","index":17,"end_time":42.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They like things low key, so.","index":18,"end_time":45.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No.","index":19,"end_time":46.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.71,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"No skiing.","index":20,"end_time":46.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.03,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay.","index":21,"end_time":47.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.71,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":47.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah, well, we''ll definitely be going skiing in the next few weeks.","index":23,"end_time":52.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":24,"end_time":54.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.8,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":25,"end_time":54.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.12,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, I enjoy.","index":26,"end_time":56.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.88,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"What about you?","index":27,"end_time":56.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nothing serious.","index":28,"end_time":59.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.12,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"We might.","index":29,"end_time":60.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.56,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"My kids are coming so we might go to New York City for a couple of days, but we haven''t decided yet.","index":30,"end_time":68.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.76,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"But.","index":31,"end_time":69.279,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.92,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, nothing.","index":32,"end_time":70.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.279,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I was traveling so much, so I like to be at home.","index":33,"end_time":72.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.12,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I haven''t been at home for more than a week in.","index":34,"end_time":76.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.08,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"In a row in the last time.","index":35,"end_time":79.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.4,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"A few months.","index":36,"end_time":79.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.2,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So yeah.","index":37,"end_time":81.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.84,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I have a few things to ask you.","index":38,"end_time":85.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.25,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"To show you.","index":39,"end_time":86.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.41,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Let me show my screen.","index":40,"end_time":87.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.01,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So first update is I have a many recording set for the next months or so from all the conference that I went and I think that.","index":41,"end_time":104.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.49,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":42,"end_time":105.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can you see this screen?","index":43,"end_time":107.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.93,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So basically it''s at a buzz Proud and I.","index":44,"end_time":112.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.37,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"That we are listed in Apple podcasts and Spotify but not on all the rest.","index":45,"end_time":116.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.39,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Is it okay or should we get listed on the other.","index":46,"end_time":121.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.43,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, I would definitely get listed on the other channels as well.","index":47,"end_time":127.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it.","index":48,"end_time":128.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.15,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Maybe it''s a new screen.","index":49,"end_time":129.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.79,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I haven''t seen it before.","index":50,"end_time":130.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.99,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Maybe I never looked at it.","index":51,"end_time":132.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.91,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":52,"end_time":133.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we can help out with that if.","index":53,"end_time":135.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you''d like.","index":54,"end_time":136.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So what should I do if I agree and submit your podcast tomorrow?","index":55,"end_time":143.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.19,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":56,"end_time":143.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.31,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, most of them should be really easy.","index":57,"end_time":146.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":147.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":148.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They all might have slightly different steps.","index":60,"end_time":151.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And what does it do when I''m submitting them?","index":61,"end_time":155.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.03,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"That''s a.","index":62,"end_time":155.989,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.35,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So for most of them it''s.","index":63,"end_time":160.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''ll usually take like 24 to 48 hours to review.","index":64,"end_time":166.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":168.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.86,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So it might.","index":66,"end_time":169.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It might take a minute to actually get published on there.","index":67,"end_time":171.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":68,"end_time":172.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.94,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And some have other questions.","index":69,"end_time":174.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.78,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I see.","index":70,"end_time":174.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.3,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":71,"end_time":176.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like if YouTube is more.","index":72,"end_time":178.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.7,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay, so that was one thing.","index":73,"end_time":180.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.06,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And the other one.","index":74,"end_time":183.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":181.86,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So I think you.","index":75,"end_time":185.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry, just before you go through the YouTube, you probably already have it on YouTube if you''re posting the videos.","index":76,"end_time":193.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":77,"end_time":194.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.86,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So the.","index":78,"end_time":195.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I wouldn''t.","index":79,"end_time":196.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would skip the YouTube one because you''re already publishing.","index":80,"end_time":198.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But they''re doing all the rest correct?","index":81,"end_time":200.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.11,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":201.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":202.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.75,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay.","index":84,"end_time":202.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.15,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay.","index":85,"end_time":203.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.95,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Now do you know this website Repronik or something like that?","index":86,"end_time":210.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.83,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"No, I haven''t heard of it.","index":87,"end_time":211.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a basically a website that rank a podcast.","index":88,"end_time":216.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.83,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So if you were looking at ours, you have an overview and here you can see some of the podcasts providing them subscribers.","index":89,"end_time":226.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.03,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So you can see podcasts addict, how many subscribers we have and so on.","index":90,"end_time":231.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.88,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay.","index":91,"end_time":232.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But what is interesting is.","index":92,"end_time":236.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.92,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Let me make it wider.","index":93,"end_time":238,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.559,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"You can also see a feedback that they receive and they are summarizing but I think that the most interesting is basically that basically they''re showing chart.","index":94,"end_time":250.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.64,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Where do you stand?","index":95,"end_time":251.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.22,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Oh nice.","index":96,"end_time":252.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And for example, you can see that we are 137 as of today change every few hours in the United States health fitness.","index":97,"end_time":263.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.42,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"But for example we are number 25 in Singapore in health fitness on medicine.","index":98,"end_time":269.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.66,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So you can click on that and then you can find yourself.","index":99,"end_time":272.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.46,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Wow, nice.","index":100,"end_time":274.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, so, so I''m showing it to you because maybe it''s good for you to show it to other podcasts.","index":101,"end_time":281.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.12,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve seen that.","index":102,"end_time":283.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.72,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Other podcasts when you are below a certain level you don''t see anything.","index":103,"end_time":286.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.08,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So you are not.","index":104,"end_time":287.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.88,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"But for me I''m seeing that I''m starting to gain more and more in a different countries.","index":105,"end_time":293.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.12,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s good or bad, but yeah, my, my main goal is to be higher in the US but you can see other countries like Canada.","index":106,"end_time":305.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.68,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, Australia.","index":107,"end_time":307.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.36,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So.","index":108,"end_time":308.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.22,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":109,"end_time":309.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.7,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So that''s what I wanted to show you.","index":110,"end_time":311.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.34,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s really interesting.","index":111,"end_time":313.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":112,"end_time":313.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll, I''ll check that out.","index":113,"end_time":314.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any, anything for.","index":114,"end_time":316.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.5,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, I actually we put together an end of year review review for you.","index":115,"end_time":323.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we have just some stats on how your, your podcast did this year and I''ll send it to you after too if so you, so you have it, you can share it with your team.","index":116,"end_time":334.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":117,"end_time":335.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.7,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":118,"end_time":335.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.58,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll just start with some of just our, our normal things with your, your just updates on your account.","index":119,"end_time":347.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we were able to send over two episodes.","index":120,"end_time":350.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think all the edits are done on.","index":121,"end_time":353.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I haven''t, I haven''t had a chance to look at his episode.","index":122,"end_time":356.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.16,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I, I, I, I will look at it hopefully today or tomorrow.","index":123,"end_time":360.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.04,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"But yeah, I got it and it''s great.","index":124,"end_time":362.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.56,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And I posted the one with my parents, so.","index":125,"end_time":365.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.8,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Oh good.","index":126,"end_time":366.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.58,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, awesome.","index":127,"end_time":367.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.38,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"We''ll see how it will.","index":128,"end_time":368.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.5,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So far it''s more or less the same, but I think that it can be either very good or can be very bad and we''ll See?","index":129,"end_time":376.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.3,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":377.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''ll skip your portal for today so that we can spend some time just going over your review for 2025.","index":131,"end_time":386.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":132,"end_time":387.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.34,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So this year, we did a lot together.","index":133,"end_time":391.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We were able to deliver 24 episodes.","index":134,"end_time":395.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you averaged about two a month, which is amazing.","index":135,"end_time":399.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And to put that in perspective, 90% of podcasts don''t make it past episode three.","index":136,"end_time":405.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''ve gone well above that.","index":137,"end_time":409.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ve been doing this for a long time and have been really consistent.","index":138,"end_time":412.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I have a question.","index":139,"end_time":413.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.97,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"In your practice, what is most of the podcast doing it.","index":140,"end_time":419.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.89,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"What, every week?","index":141,"end_time":420.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.01,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Every other week?","index":142,"end_time":420.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.05,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Once a month.","index":143,"end_time":421.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.89,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So you don''t have social.","index":144,"end_time":422.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.65,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, no.","index":145,"end_time":423.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Um, so most of most podcasts either do one a month or one every other week.","index":146,"end_time":430.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":147,"end_time":431.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.51,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":431.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":149,"end_time":432.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.27,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And then we also helped update a lot of designs for your show.","index":150,"end_time":439.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We started doing these vertical social clips, got some new thumbnails stuff for your.","index":151,"end_time":445.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your profiles, things like that, and they seem to have done really well so far.","index":152,"end_time":450.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":451.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.83,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":154,"end_time":451.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.07,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":452.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.03,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Then some huge wins for this year.","index":156,"end_time":455.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think our biggest one was getting over a million downloads.","index":157,"end_time":459.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That is a major milestone, huge accomplishment, and just something to be really proud of.","index":158,"end_time":467.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"By the way, Bailey, I looked at my YouTube channel, and I''ve seen someone left an interesting comment.","index":159,"end_time":477.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.51,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Your podcast is as good as Uberman and what someone else.","index":160,"end_time":485.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.23,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"But somehow they get much more a view.","index":161,"end_time":490.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.67,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And he said, maybe because they are a sponsoring and buying audience.","index":162,"end_time":497.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.23,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So it was interesting to.","index":163,"end_time":498.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.35,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"To see that.","index":164,"end_time":499.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.63,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I just looked at it a few minutes.","index":165,"end_time":501.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.15,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":501.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.27,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s really funny.","index":167,"end_time":503.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":504.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A lot of shows.","index":169,"end_time":505.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, they''ll.","index":170,"end_time":506.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''ll pay to get views and things like that.","index":171,"end_time":509.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":172,"end_time":511.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And that''s something, I mean, you could do, but I think just growing organically slow over time is going to get you a much more loyal following.","index":173,"end_time":520.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I agree.","index":174,"end_time":521.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.35,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":522.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then this year alone, you hit over 174,000 downloads, and you just had, like, consistent growth throughout the entire year.","index":176,"end_time":533.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":533.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.44,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And just some of your, like, best topics seem to be about, like, the core.","index":178,"end_time":541.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The core stuff.","index":179,"end_time":543.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, muscle and protein, fundamentals and big picture health.","index":180,"end_time":547.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":543.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":181,"end_time":550,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.88,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":550.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just so you can see, like, how your podcast downloads were throughout the year, you''re mostly consistent.","index":183,"end_time":557.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then there did tend to be a little bit of a drop in, like, August through October, but then you picked right back up in November, and I think it''s down right now.","index":184,"end_time":567.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just because we haven''t finished.","index":185,"end_time":570.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.72,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":186,"end_time":572,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think that''ll go right back up.","index":187,"end_time":574.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then your best performing episode was with Dr. Lane.","index":188,"end_time":581.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You had over 7,000 downloads on that one.","index":189,"end_time":584.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that was across all of your.","index":190,"end_time":586.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All the different platforms.","index":191,"end_time":589.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then another huge accomplishment which you kind of were showing me earlier is that you have been recognized on several different websites for being a really great health podcast.","index":192,"end_time":603.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re in the top 100 most popular podcasts according to Good Net Podcast.","index":193,"end_time":609.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then you''re in your.","index":194,"end_time":610.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''re in the top five longevity podcasts from Feedspot.","index":195,"end_time":614.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then you''re also on the top three for good pods.","index":196,"end_time":620.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So again, I''ll send this over to you.","index":197,"end_time":622.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But that''s.","index":198,"end_time":622.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"These are amazing.","index":199,"end_time":624.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So great to be recognized and make it onto these lists.","index":200,"end_time":630.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it''s good.","index":201,"end_time":631.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.84,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And it''s good also for marketing in a way that if I would like to start to have sponsors, that''s something good to show them.","index":202,"end_time":639.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.72,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, 100%.","index":203,"end_time":641.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":204,"end_time":642.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.96,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And then just some suggestions for next year is just keep doing what''s been working well.","index":205,"end_time":650.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So like some of the.","index":206,"end_time":653.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The best topics you had or guests thing things on that.","index":207,"end_time":658.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I definitely just keep trying to do that this next year.","index":208,"end_time":661.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then another thing just to consider is promoting episodes for a little bit longer, sharing video clips on YouTube, your LinkedIn, any other social channels you have just to keep expanding that Clear.","index":209,"end_time":678.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then definitely keep tying it back to Inside Tracker.","index":210,"end_time":682.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like you have an amazing company.","index":211,"end_time":683.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So any way that it can be connected is also really helpful.","index":212,"end_time":688.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But overall question about that, about sharing, because currently I''m doing either once per episode or twice like every other week.","index":213,"end_time":698.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.89,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"You recommend to do it even every day.","index":214,"end_time":701.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.45,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"To post about the episode?","index":215,"end_time":705.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":216,"end_time":706.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":705.61,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I don''t know if necessarily every day, but once or twice a week is great.","index":217,"end_time":713.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":218,"end_time":714.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.77,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay.","index":219,"end_time":714.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":714.21,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":715.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":714.89,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay.","index":221,"end_time":716.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.85,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m thinking maybe even post via Longevity by Design, because I have it at LinkedIn at least maybe even in.","index":222,"end_time":726.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.57,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, only also in Instagram.","index":223,"end_time":729.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.51,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So via Longevity by Design I can post every day.","index":224,"end_time":731.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.27,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And that''s their job.","index":225,"end_time":732.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.87,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean if you can do every day, that''s always best.","index":226,"end_time":736.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But.","index":227,"end_time":737.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":738.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.99,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":229,"end_time":739.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I can just repost or like.","index":230,"end_time":741.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.59,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Or something like that.","index":231,"end_time":742.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.67,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Then yeah, then it''s not me, it''s the.","index":232,"end_time":744.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.59,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yes, I don''t want to be either.","index":233,"end_time":747.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.95,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Some people I see it on social that post like 5 times a day or 10 times a day and it''s starting to be tiring for me.","index":234,"end_time":753.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.35,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I don''t want to see them ever.","index":235,"end_time":754.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.15,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a lot.","index":236,"end_time":756.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know if you see it in your social.","index":237,"end_time":758.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.73,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yes.","index":238,"end_time":759.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s starting to be.","index":239,"end_time":761.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.85,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":240,"end_time":763.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.89,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":241,"end_time":764.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.53,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a lot.","index":242,"end_time":766.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a lot of posting, but that''s it.","index":243,"end_time":768.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a good idea.","index":244,"end_time":769.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.77,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":245,"end_time":770.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.53,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":246,"end_time":771.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, yeah, we.","index":247,"end_time":772.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We love working on the podcast with you.","index":248,"end_time":774.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re really grateful for this partnership and excited for what we can do next year.","index":249,"end_time":779.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":250,"end_time":780.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.1,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"That''s.","index":251,"end_time":780.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.5,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":252,"end_time":781.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.98,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And me, too.","index":253,"end_time":782.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.66,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And, yeah, I''m not planning to stop, so.","index":254,"end_time":786.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.46,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":255,"end_time":788.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":256,"end_time":788.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Might look like that.","index":257,"end_time":790.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.62,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"You''re stuck with me.","index":258,"end_time":791.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.46,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And.","index":259,"end_time":793.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.9,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you so much.","index":260,"end_time":794.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.3,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"It was a pleasure working with you this year.","index":261,"end_time":797.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.46,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And.","index":262,"end_time":797.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.54,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, please send it to me.","index":263,"end_time":798.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.74,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"It''s a good material I can use.","index":264,"end_time":801.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.86,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And.","index":265,"end_time":802.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.42,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, and enjoy your trip and see you early next year.","index":266,"end_time":808.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.86,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Great.","index":267,"end_time":808.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll talk later.","index":268,"end_time":809.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":269,"end_time":810.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.94,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Bye.","index":270,"end_time":811.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-12-18T14:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87632173885?pwd=tg6VuBc6ZqpqwnUGjPIACYH5GrE0KC.1","participants":["gil@segterra.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com","gil@segterra.com","paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC7ST0FA3C02ZMDFG61FJQ5H","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Delivered 24 podcast episodes in 2025, averaging two per month with consistent quality.","Baylee confirmed over 1 million total downloads this year, a major milestone in growth.","Gil''s podcast ranked top 100 in Good Net and top 5 in Feedspot longevity category.","Vertical video clips, updated designs, and thumbnails improved social engagement metrics.","Gil plans to increase posting frequency via Longevity by Design''s LinkedIn and Instagram."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We were able to deliver 24 episodes...90% of podcasts don''t make it past episode three.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"Our biggest one was getting over a million downloads. That is a major milestone.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"I''m not planning to stop… you''re stuck with me.","speaker":"Gil"}],"topics":["delivery","growth","recognition","social"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-19T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Distribution Expansion**\n\nThe team decided to expand the podcast’s presence beyond Apple Podcasts and Spotify to reach more listeners across other platforms.\n\n- **Baylee Gunnell confirmed** adding the podcast to additional channels is straightforward and usually takes **24 to 48 hours** for review after submission (02:02).  \n    - This move aims to increase overall reach and capture audiences not accessible through the current platforms.  \n    - Baylee offered support to handle submissions, easing the operational load on Gil.  \n    - Gil agreed to submit the podcast to these new platforms promptly to accelerate visibility.  \n    - Expanding distribution aligns with the goal of sustained growth and wider brand exposure beyond current markets.\n\n- They agreed to **exclude YouTube from new platform submissions** since videos are already posted there (03:04).  \n    - This avoids redundant efforts and focuses resources on untapped podcast directories.  \n    - Baylee confirmed video posting on YouTube covers that channel’s audience well.  \n    - This strategic choice optimizes workload and leverages existing content effectively.\n\n## **Performance Metrics and Recognition**\n\nThe podcast achieved significant growth milestones, showing strong audience engagement and industry recognition.\n\n- The podcast hit **over 1 million total downloads this year**, with **174,000 downloads** in the current year alone, reflecting steady growth (07:33).  \n    - This positions the podcast well above the 90% of shows that fail before episode three, having delivered **24 episodes averaging two per month** (06:28).  \n    - Consistent publishing frequency is a major factor in maintaining and growing the audience base.  \n    - Baylee highlighted that the most popular topics focus on core health themes like muscle, protein, and fundamentals, guiding future content strategy.  \n    - Gil’s posting of episodes like the one with his parents shows potential for personal connection-driven content to engage listeners.\n\n- The podcast earned **top rankings on multiple platforms**, including **#137 in U.S. health fitness, #25 in Singapore health fitness, top 100 on Good Net Podcast, top 5 longevity podcast on Feedspot, and top 3 on Good Pods** (04:13, 09:31).  \n    - These rankings validate the podcast’s quality and help attract sponsorship opportunities as Gil noted (10:30).  \n    - Recognition on these platforms serves as strong marketing collateral to build credibility with advertisers.  \n    - The data shows the podcast is gaining international traction, though the primary aim remains to climb U.S. rankings.  \n    - Tracking these positions regularly provides insight into global market penetration and growth areas.\n\n## **Content Promotion and Social Strategy**\n\nTo build on growth, the team agreed to intensify promotion efforts across social platforms while maintaining audience comfort.\n\n- Baylee recommended **posting about episodes once or twice a week** as a balanced approach to keep engagement without overwhelming followers (11:45).  \n    - Gil plans to use the **Longevity by Design LinkedIn account** to post daily, leveraging a dedicated channel to avoid personal overload (12:12).  \n    - This approach spreads content efficiently and keeps Gil’s personal channels from being saturated.  \n    - Reposting or lightly sharing content helps maintain visibility without excessive new effort.  \n    - The goal is steady, organic audience growth with loyal listeners rather than aggressive paid tactics.\n\n- The team agreed to continue producing **vertical social clips and updated thumbnails**, which have already contributed positively to engagement (07:15).  \n    - These visual assets help attract attention on social feeds and improve brand consistency.  \n    - Using video clips on YouTube and LinkedIn extends reach beyond audio-only listeners.  \n    - Baylee encouraged tying content back to Gil’s company, **Inside Tracker**, to strengthen brand association and commercial potential (10:44).  \n    - This integrated approach supports both audience growth and monetization goals.\n\n## **Operational Review and Next Steps**\n\nThe partnership between Gil and Baylee’s team is strong, with clear plans for continued collaboration and ongoing improvement.\n\n- Baylee shared that all edits for two recent episodes are complete, with Gil planning to review and post soon (05:41).  \n    - This steady content pipeline supports the twice-monthly release schedule proven effective.  \n    - Baylee prepared a detailed **end-of-year review for 2023** with key stats to share with Gil’s team for internal and marketing use (05:17).  \n    - This report will provide useful data to guide 2024 planning and sponsorship discussions.\n\n- Gil affirmed commitment to continuing the podcast without interruption, signaling stable content delivery and partnership longevity (13:00).  \n    - Baylee expressed enthusiasm for next year’s work and willingness to support growth initiatives.  \n    - They agreed to keep focusing on proven topics and promotion strategies for 2024 to sustain momentum.  \n    - Sharing the review and data promptly will help Gil and his team make informed decisions on marketing and sponsorship approaches.\n\n## **Market Insights and Competitive Context**\n\nGil’s observation about competitors using paid promotion highlights the team’s preference for organic growth and long-term loyalty.\n\n- Gil noted that some popular podcasts boost views through paid ads, which might explain their higher numbers despite similar quality (07:48).  \n    - Baylee stressed that organic growth, though slower, builds a more loyal and engaged audience over time (08:21).  \n    - This philosophy favors sustainable brand equity rather than short-term spikes that may not retain listeners.  \n    - The team’s marketing and promotion plans reflect this long-term strategy, avoiding overuse of paid audience buys.  \n    - This approach aims to differentiate the podcast in a crowded market by focusing on authenticity and consistent value.","outline":null,"keywords":["podcast distribution","podcast rankings","podcast downloads","episode promotion","social media strategy","podcast milestones"],"overview":"- **Podcast Expansion:** The podcast will join other platforms to grow audience reach beyond Apple Podcasts and Spotify.  \n- **Growth Milestones:** Over 1 million total downloads this year with 174,000 from 2025, exceeding industry averages for episode longevity.  \n- **Top Rankings:** Achieved high positions in several regions, strengthening prospects for sponsorship opportunities and international visibility.  \n- **Promotion Strategy:** Posting frequency set to once or twice weekly to enhance audience engagement without overwhelming them.  \n- **Operational Review:** Edits for recent episodes completed; end-of-year review prepared to aid 2024 planning and sponsorship discussions.  \n- **Long-term Growth Focus:** Emphasizing organic growth over paid promotions to build a loyal audience and differentiate in a crowded market.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAssist in submitting Gil’s podcast to additional platforms beyond Apple Podcasts and Spotify (02:12)\nSend Gil the end-of-year podcast performance review including stats and recognition rankings for his team’s use (05:11)\n\n**Gil**\nReview the two edited podcast episodes received and post them, with plans to view one with his parents soon (05:53)\nConsider lengthening social media promotion duration and attempt additional social video clip sharing (10:44)\nExplore posting more frequently via Longevity by Design’s LinkedIn and Instagram channels to increase reach without personal overposting (12:19)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"03e04b9f-6948-426d-bbad-7cadab742054","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
