    '{"id":"01KC6WYST3DXH3G03CG8J2HQNW","title":"VITAL // New North Monthly Check-In","summary":{"notes":"## **Content and Social Media Strategy**\n\nThe team will launch a dedicated **Vital Instagram channel** to better target the construction trades coaching market and separate personal from business content (07:04).\n\n- **Matt Bernath** explained that coaches in adjacent industries use company pages primarily, which is uncommon for trades coaches who tend to mix personal and professional accounts.\n- The approach will start by reposting the **top six successful posts** and adding **two to three pinned posts** explaining Vital’s services to create immediate credibility.\n- New content will be posted **two to three times weekly**, following the current personal page’s flow to maintain consistency.\n- Audience growth will involve following existing contacts from prior outreach lists and industry-relevant accounts, with phased engagement including commenting suggested by the team to build voice authenticity.\n- Baylee Gunnell will provide full account setup support including **thumbnail design, bio creation, and visual assets** to accelerate launch, with Matt giving green light to start immediately (11:58).\n\nThe **LinkedIn outreach campaign remains paused** but follow-up on incoming responses will continue, maintaining access to the account for potential relaunch (04:00).\n\n- Despite the pause, the B2B lead generation on the website runs continuously, feeding a spreadsheet for internal campaign use.\n- Matt affirmed that recent sales from LinkedIn were from his personal efforts, not the paused campaigns (05:14).\n\nSocial content is scheduled through **end of January**, with added posts planned for the **Lidapalooza event** starting late January, focusing on driving registrations (05:46).\n\n- Matt requested coordination with Tom to see if a **special or discount registration code** can be issued for social promotions to increase conversion.\n- All posts must include a **registration link**, ensuring consistent call-to-action across channels (06:16).\n\n## **Website and Event Updates**\n\nMultiple website pages are under active development, including refreshed **Elevate** and **ESA** pages and a new **Lidapalooza landing page**, designed to be sleeker than the previous CEDIA Expo page (12:38).\n\n- The Lidapalooza page is being created separately to avoid reusing the CEDIA URL due to branding differences, with plans to refresh event pages annually (13:24).\n- Two additional new pages have recently launched, improving resource accessibility by reorganizing the resources tab to feature free tools, the podcast, and blog posts more prominently (13:39).\n- Steven Frydrych provided recent feedback to inform design tweaks on Lidapalooza materials, including potential copy changes on the event backdrop to better align messaging (12:21).\n\nMatt emphasized the need to track all website-related items carefully to ensure nothing is missed in the launch plan (14:14).\n\n## **Points System and Budget Management**\n\nThe team averaged **108 points per month over six months**, exceeding the contracted **60 points** and creating a **36-point overage** (14:35).\n\n- Baylee Gunnell recommended upgrading to a **100-point monthly plan at $6,500** to cover current usage and avoid overages, reflecting roughly $2,500 more per month than the current $4,000 plan.\n- Matt decided to maintain the **60-point plan for now and pay the $3,600 overage** separately, with plans to revisit at the end of Q1 based on needs (18:12).\n- Baylee agreed to send the overage invoice and remain flexible with future adjustments.\n\nThe overage is mainly due to **extra web pages and design work** beyond the standard scope (16:59).\n\n## **Services Website Project and Pre-Purchased Points**\n\nA proposal for a new **services website project** was sent to Chris, estimating around **$8,500** for a **17-page site, mini brand kit, and messaging** (19:04).\n\n- Matt expressed concern that this cost is higher than expected, with initial group budgeting around **$3,000–$4,000**.\n- Baylee clarified the scope may be larger than initially understood due to brand identity components like a logo and positioning.\n- Matt proposed pre-purchasing **60 additional points for $4,000** to use flexibly across Vital or client projects, plus paying the **$3,600 overage now**, aiming to have these points available before year-end (21:32).\n- Baylee committed to checking feasibility with Justin and responding quickly to align with the year-end timeline (22:42).\n\n## **Event Backdrop and Copy Adjustments**\n\nUpdated **event backdrop designs** were delivered shortly before the meeting, with Matt flagging a possible minor copy change on the front to better reflect recent insights (12:06).\n\n- Baylee confirmed flexibility to accommodate the copy edit without delay.\n- This reflects a responsive design process adapting to late feedback to optimize event messaging and attendee engagement.\n\n## **Collaboration and Communication Rhythm**\n\nBaylee highlighted the positive working rhythm, noting the current cadence delivers value with about **108 points used monthly**, and the team is open to scaling or adjusting as needed (14:35).\n\n- The team will continue with planned initiatives, including social growth, website updates, and event promotion.\n- Matt expressed appreciation for the collaboration and committed to ongoing communication via Slack through the holidays (23:15).\n- Baylee confirmed readiness to support any immediate needs and keep momentum going into the new year.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Outreach","Instagram Channel Launch","Lidapalooza Event","Website Redesign","Points System","B2B Social Campaigns"],"overview":"- **New Instagram Channel Launch:** A dedicated Vital Instagram channel will focus on the construction trades coaching market. \n\n- **Content Strategy:** Launching with top six posts and two to three pinned posts, updated twice weekly to ensure consistency.\n\n- **Website Development:** New landing pages for Lidapalooza, Elevate, and ESA are in progress, enhancing resource accessibility.\n\n- **Points Management:** Averaged 108 points monthly; upgraded plan proposed at $6,500, but current 60-point plan will continue for now.\n\n- **Service Website Proposal:** New 17-page service site proposed at $8,500, with concerns about higher-than-expected costs.\n\n- **Collaboration and Communication:** Positive team dynamics noted, with ongoing support and plans for Slack communication through the holidays.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSend document outlining Instagram strategy and repost plan to Matt Bernath (09:50)\nSet up Vital Instagram channel with branding, bio, and thumbnail assets (11:58)\nShare updated event backdrop designs and incorporate any copy revisions from Matt (12:21)\nFollow up with client on ESA page feedback and manage Lidapalooza website redesign (13:30)\nTrack and capture website launch services page updates for Matt’s action items (14:15)\nSend the website redesign proposal details to Matt for review (22:05)\nConsult with Justin and confirm feasibility of pre-buy points option and respond quickly due to year-end urgency (22:40)\n\n**Matt Bernath**\nProvide feedback on ESA website page (13:00)\nCoordinate with May and Tom to get special registration or discount code for Lidapalooza event promotion (06:18)\nPay $3,600 points overage fee and plan to re-evaluate points plan end of Q1 2024 (17:58)\n\n**May**\nCoordinate with Tom regarding special registration or discount code for Lidapalooza event outreach (06:18)\nAssist with ongoing B2B social campaigns and spreadsheet management (05:45)\n\n**Steven Frydrych**\nContinue follow-up communications with LinkedIn campaign respondents (04:45)\nProvide feedback on Lidapalooza website redesign (12:00)\n\n**Fernando Rendon**\nParticipate in discussions about website landing pages and Lidapalooza updates (04:10)\n\n**Abner**\nReview B2B website campaign lead spreadsheet and provide suitable leads to client campaigns (05:45)\n"},"duration":23.540000915527344,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"id":2,"name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"id":3,"name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"id":4,"name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s everyone doing?","index":0,"end_time":2.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey baby.","index":1,"end_time":4.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.76,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":8.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anyone have fun?","index":3,"end_time":13.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Things going on for the holidays coming up?","index":4,"end_time":16.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just being run by kids.","index":5,"end_time":21.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":19.52,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Schedules.","index":6,"end_time":22.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":21.56,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":22.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How many kids do you have?","index":8,"end_time":26.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Two kids.","index":9,"end_time":28.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":27.87,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"A seven year old and a four year old.","index":10,"end_time":30.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.39,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Both girls.","index":11,"end_time":31.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":30.27,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh my goodness.","index":12,"end_time":32.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That seems so young for them to have schedules.","index":13,"end_time":36.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It is out of control between the schools and the activities and the recitals.","index":14,"end_time":44.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.07,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"And.","index":15,"end_time":44.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":44.43,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"It''S a lot.","index":16,"end_time":47.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.67,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"They have their own calendar on within my calendar.","index":17,"end_time":50.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.39,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh my goodness.","index":18,"end_time":51.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What about you?","index":19,"end_time":55.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anything going on for the holidays?","index":20,"end_time":57.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":55.73,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Mostly just stuff with family I got.","index":21,"end_time":62.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My family lives about 30 minutes away so we''re gonna be spending lots of time together and then we''ve got our, our two dogs and so not as crazy as with kids with recitals and things.","index":22,"end_time":78.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I just get to put them in Christmas sweaters and chill at home sometimes.","index":23,"end_time":85.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s the best.","index":24,"end_time":85.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":85.16,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":86.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, Matt.","index":26,"end_time":91.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, hey, hey.","index":27,"end_time":92.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.36,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"What''s everybody doing?","index":28,"end_time":94.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":93.68,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Doing great.","index":29,"end_time":96.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We were just talking about our plans for the holidays.","index":30,"end_time":99.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ve got anything fun going on?","index":31,"end_time":101.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A little bits and pieces with my girls.","index":32,"end_time":105.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":103.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So that''ll be a good time.","index":33,"end_time":106.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":105.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"My oldest is home from college until.","index":34,"end_time":110.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":106.8,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Like the 19th of January.","index":35,"end_time":112.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":36,"end_time":113.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":114.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":113.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So it''s be fun to hang out with her.","index":38,"end_time":116.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":114.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Although it''s.","index":39,"end_time":117.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":116.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"It''s crazy.","index":40,"end_time":117.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":117.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Like she comes home and then we don''t see her because she''s out with her friends.","index":41,"end_time":120.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":117.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So it''s almost like she''s still gone.","index":42,"end_time":122.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":120.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":43,"end_time":123.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"When we have to like bribe her to hang out with us.","index":44,"end_time":125.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":123.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":126.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like pretty cool people.","index":46,"end_time":129.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":126.85,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But so yeah, I hear from her when she wants money and, and you know, whether she''s in, whether she''s home.","index":47,"end_time":135.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":129.29,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Or she''s in college.","index":48,"end_time":136.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":135.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But I just have to accept that that''s 18 year old life these days, I guess.","index":49,"end_time":140.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":137.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":50,"end_time":141.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No matter how many times I tell.","index":51,"end_time":143.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":142.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Her no, she still asks.","index":52,"end_time":145.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":143.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":53,"end_time":145.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":54,"end_time":146.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Keep doing it.","index":55,"end_time":147.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":146.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Just part of the age.","index":56,"end_time":150.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":57,"end_time":151.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":150.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We.","index":58,"end_time":151.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":151.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We might go depending on if they get snow in the mountains locally, we.","index":59,"end_time":154.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":152.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Might go to Mammoth.","index":60,"end_time":155.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":154.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":61,"end_time":157.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":156.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So it''s like that''s probably the most fun plan to look forward to.","index":62,"end_time":160.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":157.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But otherwise lots of just hanging out, chilling.","index":63,"end_time":163.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":160.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Nice.","index":64,"end_time":164.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":164.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That should be fun.","index":66,"end_time":165.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, I''m hoping so.","index":67,"end_time":167.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":166.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Well, you''re gonna get dumped on here.","index":68,"end_time":170.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":168.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Soon I think too, right?","index":69,"end_time":171.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":170.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re probably gonna get a lot of snow.","index":70,"end_time":175.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Makes for good skiing.","index":71,"end_time":177.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s the nice thing.","index":72,"end_time":181.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":73,"end_time":183.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":74,"end_time":184.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Don''t love the cold, but there''s fun stuff to do outside when it''s snowy at least.","index":75,"end_time":188.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":76,"end_time":189.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":189.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Well, we have a ton on the agenda today, so we''ll just get to it and I Hope we can get to everything.","index":77,"end_time":198.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So Igor already sent over the stats that we wanted to review with you, so I hope you have time to review those videos.","index":78,"end_time":210.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You had a really great year when it just comes to content performance, so definitely check those videos out.","index":79,"end_time":215.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we wanted to spend this time to talk about the things we need to collaborate on more.","index":80,"end_time":220.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So We''ve got our LinkedIn outreach, some stuff on our B2B social updates.","index":81,"end_time":225.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know you talked about getting a vital Instagram channel started.","index":82,"end_time":229.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The backdrop, some website updates and then your client portal.","index":83,"end_time":235.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''ll also talk about points, but.","index":84,"end_time":238.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So big list, but anything I''m missing that you all wanted to chat through today?","index":85,"end_time":242.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nothing on my agenda.","index":86,"end_time":245.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":244.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"This is all great.","index":87,"end_time":246.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":245.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":88,"end_time":247.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I just have.","index":89,"end_time":249.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.23,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Are we going to touch upon the landing page or not?","index":90,"end_time":251.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.11,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Or is that something briefly?","index":91,"end_time":254.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":254.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"With those website updates.","index":93,"end_time":255.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is this for the Lid of Palooza or.","index":94,"end_time":257.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":95,"end_time":258.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":96,"end_time":259.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just really quick with the podcast, we were able to get a couple episodes distributed since our last meeting, and then we''re working through another episode right now.","index":97,"end_time":270.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":98,"end_time":271.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then per our last meeting, we have paused the LinkedIn outreach campaigns, which was so funny.","index":99,"end_time":280.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We paused the campaigns and then we started seeing responses.","index":100,"end_time":283.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So luckily we still have access to things.","index":101,"end_time":286.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve been communicating with Steven about some of those people who wanted to keep conversations going.","index":102,"end_time":292.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But at least as it stands right now, I think we''ll keep these paused and just keep follow up with anyone who has been reaching out.","index":103,"end_time":300.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we.","index":104,"end_time":301.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We do still have the account, so if you ever want to launch something again, we can do that.","index":105,"end_time":306.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":106,"end_time":306.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":306.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you, Stephen.","index":107,"end_time":308.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":306.85,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I think I recall a sale that came from LinkedIn recently.","index":108,"end_time":311.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":308.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Was it from this work or other work?","index":109,"end_time":313.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":311.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"No, that was me separately on my own LinkedIn.","index":110,"end_time":318.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":314.33,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Got it.","index":111,"end_time":318.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":318.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":112,"end_time":319.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":113,"end_time":320.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":319.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Then even though we''ve paused those campaigns, we still have our B2B running on your website.","index":114,"end_time":327.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''ll still have the spreadsheet that Abner can go through.","index":115,"end_time":331.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And if you.","index":116,"end_time":331.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You find people that are a fit, I would highly recommend just throwing them in the campaigns that you have running internally because I think this is still a good resource because they''re people who are coming to your website.","index":117,"end_time":342.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":118,"end_time":344.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":343.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So then just some social updates.","index":119,"end_time":348.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have a lot of content scheduled all through the end of January and we''re planning on adding in some stuff for the lidapalooza event.","index":120,"end_time":358.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"May sent us over your speaking schedule and some other details.","index":121,"end_time":362.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re currently working through that.","index":122,"end_time":363.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That right now.","index":123,"end_time":364.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can also get that on the calendar and we''re thinking to start Posting end of January, then leading up to the event.","index":124,"end_time":372.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Does that sound okay, or were you thinking something different?","index":125,"end_time":375.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think that sounds great.","index":126,"end_time":377.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":376.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"May, would you get with Tom and see if he wants to issue us a special registration code for anybody who wants, like, maybe share with him that we''re doing a lot of social media outreach regarding lidapalooza, and if he has a special registration code or something that he wants us to use, maybe even a discount code that he wants us to promote, that would be great.","index":127,"end_time":404.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":378.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And get that over to Bailey.","index":128,"end_time":405.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":404.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Otherwise, Bailey, the main thing we want to do is just every single one of those posts needs to include a registration link.","index":129,"end_time":412.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":406.23,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So people.","index":130,"end_time":412.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":412.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, okay, that''s good to know.","index":131,"end_time":415.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll make sure to include that link then.","index":132,"end_time":417.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And yeah, if we hear back on a code, we can easily add that in.","index":133,"end_time":421.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Beautiful.","index":134,"end_time":422.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":422.21,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":135,"end_time":423.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":422.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then you had messaged us about wanting to get a new vital Instagram channel started.","index":136,"end_time":430.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''d love to hear kind of what inspired that.","index":137,"end_time":432.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":430.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":434.369,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":433.889,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"A number of conversations with other coaches in adjacent industries.","index":139,"end_time":439.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":434.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"They.","index":140,"end_time":440.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":439.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"They don''t use their personal pages specifically for their coaching work.","index":141,"end_time":448.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"There.","index":142,"end_time":449.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":449.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"There are a lot of coaches who do.","index":143,"end_time":451.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":449.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But it seems like in the trades, which is where we live, right?","index":144,"end_time":454.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":451.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"The construction trades, most of the coaches in that world are not using their personal page as the primary.","index":145,"end_time":461.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":454.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"They will, you know, they''ll use.","index":146,"end_time":463.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":462.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"They''ll kind of bounce back and forth, but they will use their.","index":147,"end_time":465.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":463.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Their company page as the primary.","index":148,"end_time":468.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":466.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So.","index":149,"end_time":468.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":468.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, so that was interesting to me because I''d always heard that coaches should use their personal pages, but I think it''s unique to the construction trades.","index":150,"end_time":476.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":468.7,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So then there''s also the side benefit of now, you know, my personal page becomes my personal page, and I can, like, you know, have that be more.","index":151,"end_time":486.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":477.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Of a focus of what I do there.","index":152,"end_time":487.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":486.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So.","index":153,"end_time":488.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":488.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I like that idea and the way it was described to me.","index":154,"end_time":493.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":488.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And I don''t know if this is reality or not, so you can correct me, but it.","index":155,"end_time":497.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":493.72,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I think we can just launch the page and then basically just repost all the content over there so that it can feel like that page has been around a while.","index":156,"end_time":504.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":497.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":157,"end_time":504.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then.","index":158,"end_time":505.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":504.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then somebody goes through and.","index":159,"end_time":507.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":505.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And I imagine.","index":160,"end_time":508.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":507.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I don''t know if this is work you guys can do or somebody else.","index":161,"end_time":510.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":508.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"They basically go through and follow all the followers that I have and kind of like follow people who are of our industry, you know, who are from our industry, and.","index":162,"end_time":523.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":511.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And that can turn the page into a, you know, pretty legitimate page fairly quickly.","index":163,"end_time":529.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":523.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Does that sound right?","index":164,"end_time":529.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":530.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You.","index":166,"end_time":531.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You shared a lot of the Things we actually put together in a separate document.","index":167,"end_time":536.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll just jump over there.","index":168,"end_time":537.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I just wanted to get your thoughts to make sure we''re on the same page.","index":169,"end_time":542.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll just jump over here.","index":170,"end_time":543.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And this is kind of a long document, but I''ll just jump over to the main thing.","index":171,"end_time":550.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we''re on a pretty similar page, but I. I don''t know if I''d necessarily post everything, but we were thinking starting with, like, your six most successful posts.","index":172,"end_time":560.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So starting with that.","index":173,"end_time":561.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''d also recommend doing two to three pinned posts to the top that essentially just explain what you do.","index":174,"end_time":569.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''ve probably seen those carousels on Instagram, too, so maybe something like that.","index":175,"end_time":574.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we could do a couple different options there.","index":176,"end_time":577.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just so if people come to your page, they know really quickly who you are.","index":177,"end_time":580.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''d want to start doing new content two to three times a week.","index":178,"end_time":585.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Kind of like using the flow we''re already doing for your personal page.","index":179,"end_time":588.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How does that sound?","index":180,"end_time":590.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I love it.","index":181,"end_time":591.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.84,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":592.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":591.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":183,"end_time":592.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think this is great.","index":184,"end_time":594.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":593.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I mean, the plan that you laid out here is perfect.","index":185,"end_time":596.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":594.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":186,"end_time":597,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":597.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then, yeah, similarly, with audience growth, we can just include that in our weekly management.","index":188,"end_time":603.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can, like, I think when we set it up, we can do a lot of people that we follow that are already on your followers, and then add people every couple weeks.","index":189,"end_time":613.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then if you really wanted to go, the next step is you would start commenting on other people''s posts.","index":190,"end_time":619.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is something that I feel it can be a little tricky because people don''t want to fully give the reins to someone else to comment.","index":191,"end_time":626.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, like, we could find some posts and be like, this is maybe what you could say, and then you could do it.","index":192,"end_time":632.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or maybe we do that for a little bit until you feel like we''ve got your voice there.","index":193,"end_time":637.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s a couple ways we could do that.","index":194,"end_time":639.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":195,"end_time":641.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":640.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And what.","index":196,"end_time":641.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":641.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"What''s the.","index":197,"end_time":642.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":641.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"How do they determine which accounts they''re going to follow?","index":198,"end_time":645.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":643.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Like, what''s the protocol for that?","index":199,"end_time":648.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":645.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So we''d probably.","index":200,"end_time":649.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''d want to put together, like, a Target ICP page.","index":201,"end_time":655.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I.","index":202,"end_time":656.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Essentially, I think we''d use, like, the lists you''ve given us before, so the people we''ve already reached out to, we''d probably, like, maybe actually try to connect with those people that are already on those lists.","index":203,"end_time":667.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If we can buy them or find people who are, like, similar or suggested from those pages.","index":204,"end_time":672.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Love it.","index":205,"end_time":674.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Love it.","index":206,"end_time":674.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":674.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Cool.","index":207,"end_time":675.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":674.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll send over this document, too.","index":208,"end_time":678.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":675.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s, like, a couple things in Here, like we already found some of the posts that seem to do better, so we can use these as the starting point visual framework.","index":209,"end_time":688.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve worked on this a lot with you already, so we''ll just keep following similar things, but it won''t be too different from what we''ve already done with you before.","index":210,"end_time":699.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It will just increase the management of your social points and then they''ll also be like an eight point setup.","index":211,"end_time":707.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if you want our help to like actually get the account set up, we can do like your thumbnail, your bio, all the designs and setup to get that launched.","index":212,"end_time":718.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be amazing.","index":213,"end_time":719.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":718.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":720.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":215,"end_time":721.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll get started on that then if this all sounds good.","index":216,"end_time":724.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, green light.","index":217,"end_time":726.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":725.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":218,"end_time":728.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''ll just come back here.","index":219,"end_time":730.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So the next update is your event drop backdrop.","index":220,"end_time":733.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We just got updated designs, I think before this call, so we''ll make sure those get sent over to you here shortly.","index":221,"end_time":740.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":222,"end_time":741.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":741.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And a little bit of a heads up on that.","index":223,"end_time":744.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":742.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Some recent information that we''ve received makes me think rethink a little bit of the copy on there.","index":224,"end_time":751.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":745.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I may have a copy change on the front, but it''s not going to be significant.","index":225,"end_time":755.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":753.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I just didn''t want that to.","index":226,"end_time":757.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":755.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Be a surprise when you see it.","index":227,"end_time":758.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":757.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s totally fine.","index":228,"end_time":760.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for the website updates, we''ve got quite a few pages in progress.","index":229,"end_time":768.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We finished some edits to the Elevate page.","index":230,"end_time":772.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then I think we''re just waiting for your feedback on the ESA page.","index":231,"end_time":777.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''re also working on the updated design for the lidapalooza.","index":232,"end_time":782.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I say updated because we''re using the Cedia Expo page and we''re gonna refresh it, make it look a bit sleeker.","index":233,"end_time":789.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":782.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We got some feedback from Steven I think just last week, so we''re working on that right now.","index":234,"end_time":794.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":235,"end_time":795.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.02,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"And just so I''m familiar, you''re you''re leaving the CD page because we''re probably going to reuse that next year and then you''re just designing a new one.","index":236,"end_time":802.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":795.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"For Light of Palooza.","index":237,"end_time":803.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":802.78,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''ll create just a brand new one.","index":238,"end_time":806.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we don''t want to because the URLs too, I think it said like CD Expo, so it just makes more sense to create a brand new one.","index":239,"end_time":814.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":240,"end_time":814.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":814.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll refresh those before each event.","index":241,"end_time":817.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":815.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":242,"end_time":819.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we got two new pages on your site as well.","index":243,"end_time":822.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":244,"end_time":823.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.48,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Those ones turned out great, I thought.","index":245,"end_time":825.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just a few other updates we made on your website since our last meeting.","index":246,"end_time":831.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We updated your resources tab so there''s some new dropdowns.","index":247,"end_time":835.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We made your resources page.","index":248,"end_time":837.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I feel like a bit easier to access some of the free tools you have, plus your podcast and the blog posts.","index":249,"end_time":845.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":250,"end_time":846.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just working on getting those new pages added once everything''s been approved.","index":251,"end_time":850.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":252,"end_time":850.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any questions on website or any other edits you''re wanting to make?","index":253,"end_time":853.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I don''t think so.","index":254,"end_time":856.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":854.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"May.","index":255,"end_time":857.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":857.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I think if you could just.","index":256,"end_time":859.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":857.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I think you''re probably tracking and capturing all this.","index":257,"end_time":862.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":860.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Just make sure it gets into my action item for the launch services page or whatever, so I don''t forget any of them.","index":258,"end_time":868.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":862.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I see.","index":259,"end_time":869.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":868.73,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"There''s a chance that I might.","index":260,"end_time":870.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":869.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":261,"end_time":872.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got it.","index":262,"end_time":872.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":263,"end_time":873.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.69,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":264,"end_time":873.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":873.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":265,"end_time":874.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":873.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":266,"end_time":875.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":267,"end_time":877.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we got.","index":268,"end_time":878.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Went through everything a lot faster than I thought we would, but this is great.","index":269,"end_time":880.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think just the last thing is chatting about points and what we want to do for the next steps.","index":270,"end_time":887.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We love working with you.","index":271,"end_time":888.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I feel like we found a really good cadence.","index":272,"end_time":891.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I feel like we''re doing really cool things.","index":273,"end_time":893.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":892.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve been averaging about 108 points a month over the last six months.","index":274,"end_time":899.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And your current plan is for 60 points when that all like, shakes out.","index":275,"end_time":904.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Though you did have like quite a few points overage from beforehand.","index":276,"end_time":909.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re at 36 points over what your contract has been at.","index":277,"end_time":914.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like, with that being said, like, there''s a couple things we could do.","index":278,"end_time":918.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would probably recommend, like, if you''re happy with the cadence we''re at, we could look into maybe just upgrading and getting more points so we can keep going at this cadence.","index":279,"end_time":927.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And if you were to do that, we would just eliminate the points overage.","index":280,"end_time":931.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But it''s really up to you.","index":281,"end_time":933.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we''re flexible.","index":282,"end_time":934.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you want to keep at this, like about 100 points, we can do that or we can try something else.","index":283,"end_time":941.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not sure I''m following that piece.","index":284,"end_time":945.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":943.12,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So help me understand the next steps.","index":285,"end_time":949.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":945.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Like you''re saying we can stay at the $4,000 a month for 60 points and then just pay for the points overage and we''re like back to square or.","index":286,"end_time":961.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":951.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":962.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or.","index":288,"end_time":963.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":962.83,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, I can be more clear.","index":289,"end_time":964.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":963.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I, I would say the preferred option is if you wanted to like stay at around 100 points, we would need to upgrade.","index":290,"end_time":975.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So like every month would be an increased fee.","index":291,"end_time":978.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You don''t have to do that though.","index":292,"end_time":980.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s just if you wanted to keep working at this clip.","index":293,"end_time":985.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if not, it''s fine.","index":294,"end_time":986.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":295,"end_time":987.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can try to trim a few things down to if you need to stay at the 60 points a month.","index":296,"end_time":992.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if, if that doesn''t work, we could just, I think it''s 36 points that we''ve gone over.","index":297,"end_time":1000.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you could just do like a one time fee for that.","index":298,"end_time":1003.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Pay that out.","index":299,"end_time":1004.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1003.61,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1004.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1004.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So it feels to me like we have sort of this bucket of things we''re doing on a regular basis that''s pretty well covered by the 60 points a month.","index":301,"end_time":1015.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1007.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Is that, is that right?","index":302,"end_time":1015.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1015.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And it''s just been the ancillary things that have kind of bumped us over.","index":303,"end_time":1018.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1015.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s usually like the, the extra web pages and the extra designs.","index":304,"end_time":1024.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1019.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s usually what bumps us over.","index":305,"end_time":1026.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1024.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so, so it feels like to me the offer that''s out there right now is if I''m tracking this, is that we move to 65 points a month, which is only five more points than we''re at now, but it costs us fifteen hundred dollars more a month.","index":306,"end_time":1043.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1026.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Is that, am I reading that right?","index":307,"end_time":1045.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1043.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Sorry, no, I''m not explaining this.","index":308,"end_time":1047.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Super clear.","index":309,"end_time":1048.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it would get you a hundred points a month for 6,500.","index":310,"end_time":1053.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1049.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Currently 60 points for 4,000.","index":311,"end_time":1058.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1056.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you still would get more gifted points every month.","index":312,"end_time":1062.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''re recommending a hundred because that''s about where you''ve been sitting at for the last six months.","index":313,"end_time":1068.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":314,"end_time":1069.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1068.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And it''s $2500 more, not $1500.","index":315,"end_time":1072.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1069.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":316,"end_time":1072.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":317,"end_time":1073.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.58,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1073.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1073.26,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, I see.","index":319,"end_time":1076.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1074.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So my decision is either go the $6,500 a month route and, and that''s just how we move forward, or go to stay with the $4,000 a month.","index":320,"end_time":1086.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1076.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Route and I pay the $3,600 overage.","index":321,"end_time":1088.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1086.28,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":322,"end_time":1089.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1089.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Why don''t we go that route for now?","index":323,"end_time":1092.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1090.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":324,"end_time":1093.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right.","index":325,"end_time":1093.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1093.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Because I think a lot of what we''ve been dealing with is like one time stuff.","index":326,"end_time":1097.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1094.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But let''s talk about it at the end of Q1 and if, if we''re still where we are, then let''s re approach that.","index":327,"end_time":1104.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1098.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So, so you have them send me, you know, have the team send me a bill for the overage.","index":328,"end_time":1108.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1104.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That''d be $3,600, right?","index":329,"end_time":1111.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1109.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1111.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then, and then let''s talk at the end of Q1 and see where we''re at.","index":331,"end_time":1115.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1112.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":332,"end_time":1115.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds great.","index":333,"end_time":1117.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Always happy to figure out whatever works best for you.","index":334,"end_time":1120.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1117.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":335,"end_time":1121.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1120.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And real quick, on the points for that services website, or I should say, where are we at with the services website?","index":336,"end_time":1129.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1121.58,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"With Chris.","index":337,"end_time":1130.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1129.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yes.","index":338,"end_time":1131.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I sent a proposal over to Chris about two weeks ago.","index":339,"end_time":1137.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I, I can pull it up really quick if, if you want to see it.","index":340,"end_time":1142.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":341,"end_time":1143.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1143.21,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Let me just grab it and I, I feel like that would maybe be a little different.","index":342,"end_time":1152.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We would probably charge it as just like a one time project.","index":343,"end_time":1154.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1152.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then you''re not having a recurring fee for that.","index":344,"end_time":1160.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1155.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because here''s a thought in my mind.","index":345,"end_time":1163.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1161.93,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Bailey, just to know where I''m at.","index":346,"end_time":1164.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1163.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Like, well, yeah, show me what you''re.","index":347,"end_time":1166.365,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1164.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Doing, what you have first, and then we''ll go from there.","index":348,"end_time":1168.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1166.365,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"You just pulling this up?","index":349,"end_time":1184.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":350,"end_time":1185.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1185.19,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, look at the puppy.","index":351,"end_time":1187.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.95,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":352,"end_time":1187.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s been very rainy today and they want to be outside.","index":353,"end_time":1191.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, Let me share my screen.","index":354,"end_time":1209.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so this is what we sent over to Chris and with what do you explain the project to.","index":355,"end_time":1220.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It shook out to be around 8, $500 for the whole website.","index":356,"end_time":1226.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":357,"end_time":1227.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.93,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a lot more I think than we were thinking.","index":358,"end_time":1230.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1227.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I think as a, as a group we were probably budgeting three, four grand just based on what everybody had done before.","index":359,"end_time":1238.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1231.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"How many pages were in this site.","index":360,"end_time":1240.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1238.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That you were designing?","index":361,"end_time":1241.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1240.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"How many.","index":362,"end_time":1242.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This book is different than we''d all talked about.","index":363,"end_time":1245.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1243.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, 17 pages.","index":364,"end_time":1248.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":365,"end_time":1249.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Me, yeah.","index":366,"end_time":1251,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Happy to reconnect because maybe we understood it as something bigger than it actually was.","index":367,"end_time":1257.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1251,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I didn''t recognize any of the names of the companies in that.","index":368,"end_time":1260.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1257.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Are we sure we''re talking about the right thing?","index":369,"end_time":1262.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1260.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, those were just examples at the bottom.","index":370,"end_time":1264.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":371,"end_time":1264.719,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.24,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah, we just sent over a couple.","index":372,"end_time":1266.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.719,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, 17 pages seems like a lot.","index":373,"end_time":1268.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1266.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Well, because what, what was.","index":374,"end_time":1271.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1269.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I had the mind to just pre buy those points this year and if we didn''t end up using it on this project, we would use it on other projects.","index":375,"end_time":1278.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1271.2,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So is that an option?","index":376,"end_time":1279.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1278.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Can we get like, can you guys quote us out, you know, for about pre buying some points this year that we could use either for our projects or their projects?","index":377,"end_time":1291.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1280.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we could definitely do that.","index":378,"end_time":1294.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we could just do.","index":379,"end_time":1296.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1295.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, like a project of just some points and.","index":380,"end_time":1301.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1296.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, so.","index":381,"end_time":1302.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And this is what we had like specced out.","index":382,"end_time":1306.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it was eight pages, a mini brand kit and messaging.","index":383,"end_time":1310.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1306.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think that might be maybe a little bit what''s going over because we talked about like needing a logo and like a visual identity and just how you''re wanting to position yourself and then.","index":384,"end_time":1325.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":385,"end_time":1327.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.37,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"Yeah, I can send this over to you too if that helps.","index":386,"end_time":1330.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So would you throw this out and maybe something you can prove.","index":387,"end_time":1334.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1330.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":388,"end_time":1334.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1334.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But here''s what I like to throw out.","index":389,"end_time":1336.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1334.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Four grand for another 60 points, we''ll just pre buy.","index":390,"end_time":1344.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1341.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":391,"end_time":1345.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.93,"speaker_name":"Fernando Rendon"},{"text":"And then 3, 600 to clear our overage.","index":392,"end_time":1347.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1345.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And if you can build those before the end of the year.","index":393,"end_time":1351.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1349.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I''m good with that.","index":394,"end_time":1353.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1351.98,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That way kind of preloads us with 60 additional points that we either use for us or for them.","index":395,"end_time":1358.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1353.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then we''ll just clear our overage with you guys.","index":396,"end_time":1361.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1358.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":397,"end_time":1362.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll.","index":398,"end_time":1363.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll chat with Justin and just see if that.","index":399,"end_time":1366.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That works and I''ll get back to you.","index":400,"end_time":1369.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we''ll.","index":401,"end_time":1369.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll move quickly because I know the end of the year is coming soon.","index":402,"end_time":1373.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":403,"end_time":1374.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1374.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll get back to you as soon as possible.","index":404,"end_time":1376.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1374.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":405,"end_time":1377.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1377.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":406,"end_time":1378.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1377.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":407,"end_time":1380.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you for meeting today.","index":408,"end_time":1382.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Lot lots of great stuff going on and we''ll.","index":409,"end_time":1386.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll just keep moving along with the stuff we have planned.","index":410,"end_time":1389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":411,"end_time":1390.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1389.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Look at us.","index":412,"end_time":1390.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1390.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We did it.","index":413,"end_time":1391.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1390.6,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I know.","index":414,"end_time":1391.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I finished with minutes to spare.","index":415,"end_time":1394.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1392.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know.","index":416,"end_time":1395.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1394.6,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Cool.","index":417,"end_time":1395.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1395.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, yeah, thank you both.","index":418,"end_time":1396.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1395.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I''m sure we''ll talk over slack before the holiday, but you know, have an amazing, amazing holiday season.","index":419,"end_time":1402.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1397.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"You too.","index":420,"end_time":1404.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll talk later.","index":421,"end_time":1405.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":422,"end_time":1405.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1405.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"See ya.","index":423,"end_time":1406.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"See ya.","index":424,"end_time":1406.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1406.12,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Bye.","index":425,"end_time":1406.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1407.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-12-17T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/5303795759","participants":["concierge@growwithvital.com,brent@growwithvital.com,steven@growwithvital.com,matt@growwithvital.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,fernando@growwithvital.com,may@growwithvital.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","concierge@growwithvital.com","brent@growwithvital.com","steven@growwithvital.com","matt@growwithvital.com","fernando@growwithvital.com","may@growwithvital.com","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC6WYST3DXH3G03CG8J2HQNW","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Finalized launch of new Vital Instagram channel, targeting trades audience with dedicated content.","Approved Lidapalooza social plan; posts begin end of January with registration link in every post.","Aligned on $3,600 overage payment and deferred upgrade decision to end of Q1.","Proposed buying 60 extra points for $4,000 before year end for future internal or partner use.","Multiple website updates in progress, including updated Lidapalooza and Elevate pages pending feedback."],"highlights":[{"quote":"You had a really great year when it just comes to content performance.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"Green light.","speaker":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"quote":"We love working with you. I feel like we found a really good cadence.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["social","budget","delivery","scope","launch"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-19T21:43:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content and Social Media Strategy**\n\nThe team will launch a dedicated **Vital Instagram channel** to better target the construction trades coaching market and separate personal from business content (07:04).\n\n- **Matt Bernath** explained that coaches in adjacent industries use company pages primarily, which is uncommon for trades coaches who tend to mix personal and professional accounts.\n- The approach will start by reposting the **top six successful posts** and adding **two to three pinned posts** explaining Vital’s services to create immediate credibility.\n- New content will be posted **two to three times weekly**, following the current personal page’s flow to maintain consistency.\n- Audience growth will involve following existing contacts from prior outreach lists and industry-relevant accounts, with phased engagement including commenting suggested by the team to build voice authenticity.\n- Baylee Gunnell will provide full account setup support including **thumbnail design, bio creation, and visual assets** to accelerate launch, with Matt giving green light to start immediately (11:58).\n\nThe **LinkedIn outreach campaign remains paused** but follow-up on incoming responses will continue, maintaining access to the account for potential relaunch (04:00).\n\n- Despite the pause, the B2B lead generation on the website runs continuously, feeding a spreadsheet for internal campaign use.\n- Matt affirmed that recent sales from LinkedIn were from his personal efforts, not the paused campaigns (05:14).\n\nSocial content is scheduled through **end of January**, with added posts planned for the **Lidapalooza event** starting late January, focusing on driving registrations (05:46).\n\n- Matt requested coordination with Tom to see if a **special or discount registration code** can be issued for social promotions to increase conversion.\n- All posts must include a **registration link**, ensuring consistent call-to-action across channels (06:16).\n\n## **Website and Event Updates**\n\nMultiple website pages are under active development, including refreshed **Elevate** and **ESA** pages and a new **Lidapalooza landing page**, designed to be sleeker than the previous CEDIA Expo page (12:38).\n\n- The Lidapalooza page is being created separately to avoid reusing the CEDIA URL due to branding differences, with plans to refresh event pages annually (13:24).\n- Two additional new pages have recently launched, improving resource accessibility by reorganizing the resources tab to feature free tools, the podcast, and blog posts more prominently (13:39).\n- Steven Frydrych provided recent feedback to inform design tweaks on Lidapalooza materials, including potential copy changes on the event backdrop to better align messaging (12:21).\n\nMatt emphasized the need to track all website-related items carefully to ensure nothing is missed in the launch plan (14:14).\n\n## **Points System and Budget Management**\n\nThe team averaged **108 points per month over six months**, exceeding the contracted **60 points** and creating a **36-point overage** (14:35).\n\n- Baylee Gunnell recommended upgrading to a **100-point monthly plan at $6,500** to cover current usage and avoid overages, reflecting roughly $2,500 more per month than the current $4,000 plan.\n- Matt decided to maintain the **60-point plan for now and pay the $3,600 overage** separately, with plans to revisit at the end of Q1 based on needs (18:12).\n- Baylee agreed to send the overage invoice and remain flexible with future adjustments.\n\nThe overage is mainly due to **extra web pages and design work** beyond the standard scope (16:59).\n\n## **Services Website Project and Pre-Purchased Points**\n\nA proposal for a new **services website project** was sent to Chris, estimating around **$8,500** for a **17-page site, mini brand kit, and messaging** (19:04).\n\n- Matt expressed concern that this cost is higher than expected, with initial group budgeting around **$3,000–$4,000**.\n- Baylee clarified the scope may be larger than initially understood due to brand identity components like a logo and positioning.\n- Matt proposed pre-purchasing **60 additional points for $4,000** to use flexibly across Vital or client projects, plus paying the **$3,600 overage now**, aiming to have these points available before year-end (21:32).\n- Baylee committed to checking feasibility with Justin and responding quickly to align with the year-end timeline (22:42).\n\n## **Event Backdrop and Copy Adjustments**\n\nUpdated **event backdrop designs** were delivered shortly before the meeting, with Matt flagging a possible minor copy change on the front to better reflect recent insights (12:06).\n\n- Baylee confirmed flexibility to accommodate the copy edit without delay.\n- This reflects a responsive design process adapting to late feedback to optimize event messaging and attendee engagement.\n\n## **Collaboration and Communication Rhythm**\n\nBaylee highlighted the positive working rhythm, noting the current cadence delivers value with about **108 points used monthly**, and the team is open to scaling or adjusting as needed (14:35).\n\n- The team will continue with planned initiatives, including social growth, website updates, and event promotion.\n- Matt expressed appreciation for the collaboration and committed to ongoing communication via Slack through the holidays (23:15).\n- Baylee confirmed readiness to support any immediate needs and keep momentum going into the new year.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Outreach","Instagram Channel Launch","Lidapalooza Event","Website Redesign","Points System","B2B Social Campaigns"],"overview":"- **New Instagram Channel Launch:** A dedicated Vital Instagram channel will focus on the construction trades coaching market. \n\n- **Content Strategy:** Launching with top six posts and two to three pinned posts, updated twice weekly to ensure consistency.\n\n- **Website Development:** New landing pages for Lidapalooza, Elevate, and ESA are in progress, enhancing resource accessibility.\n\n- **Points Management:** Averaged 108 points monthly; upgraded plan proposed at $6,500, but current 60-point plan will continue for now.\n\n- **Service Website Proposal:** New 17-page service site proposed at $8,500, with concerns about higher-than-expected costs.\n\n- **Collaboration and Communication:** Positive team dynamics noted, with ongoing support and plans for Slack communication through the holidays.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSend document outlining Instagram strategy and repost plan to Matt Bernath (09:50)\nSet up Vital Instagram channel with branding, bio, and thumbnail assets (11:58)\nShare updated event backdrop designs and incorporate any copy revisions from Matt (12:21)\nFollow up with client on ESA page feedback and manage Lidapalooza website redesign (13:30)\nTrack and capture website launch services page updates for Matt’s action items (14:15)\nSend the website redesign proposal details to Matt for review (22:05)\nConsult with Justin and confirm feasibility of pre-buy points option and respond quickly due to year-end urgency (22:40)\n\n**Matt Bernath**\nProvide feedback on ESA website page (13:00)\nCoordinate with May and Tom to get special registration or discount code for Lidapalooza event promotion (06:18)\nPay $3,600 points overage fee and plan to re-evaluate points plan end of Q1 2024 (17:58)\n\n**May**\nCoordinate with Tom regarding special registration or discount code for Lidapalooza event outreach (06:18)\nAssist with ongoing B2B social campaigns and spreadsheet management (05:45)\n\n**Steven Frydrych**\nContinue follow-up communications with LinkedIn campaign respondents (04:45)\nProvide feedback on Lidapalooza website redesign (12:00)\n\n**Fernando Rendon**\nParticipate in discussions about website landing pages and Lidapalooza updates (04:10)\n\n**Abner**\nReview B2B website campaign lead spreadsheet and provide suitable leads to client campaigns (05:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"68959e1a-5070-4b99-b682-be8a0718a5af","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
