    '{"id":"01KC7ST0FDKC5X3N8XAW7VHVPK","title":"NEACH // New North","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Performance and Analytics**\n\nThe **Wrestling Payments podcast published 27 episodes in 2025** and achieved a total of **2,168 downloads**, averaging **80 downloads per episode**, showing strong audience retention (04:50).\n\n- **Notable download spikes occurred in May and July** due to publishing five and six episodes respectively, and October saw high traction from episodes featuring Jordan and Rich.\n- **85% of listeners are based in North America**, with **7% in Europe** and **4% in Asia**, primarily accessing the podcast via iPhone through **Apple Podcasts and Spotify**.\n- The last five episodes collectively garnered **333 downloads**, with John’s episode leading at **88 downloads**, maintaining the North American listener dominance at **81%**.\n- Social media efforts yielded **22 new followers** and a reach of **3,200**, contributing to an overall **10% increase in engagement year-over-year**, with **14,300 views and 743 hours of watch time** indicating rising audience interaction.\n- Igor highlighted that **shorts remain the most effective content format**, accounting for the majority of viewer discovery on YouTube with **779 views and 17.5 hours of watch time in the past 28 days**.\n- Wrestling Payments was recognized by Good Pods as one of the **top three payments podcasts**, underscoring its strong market position even though the listing is recommendation-based rather than a strict ranking (08:36).\n\n## **Podcast Production and Editing Process**\n\nThe team identified **inconsistencies in editing styles between Alyssa and Joe’s filmed episodes**, affecting content flow and review efficiency (02:35).\n\n- Meg clarified that Alyssa often restarts takes after mistakes, whereas Joe keeps rolling, requiring more post-production edits.\n- Baylee confirmed their editing team will **improve review thoroughness to remove unwanted segments**, ensuring cleaner final episodes.\n- Igor noted recent episodes, such as Sanjeev’s, were edited with this approach, allowing the team to **calibrate editing standards based on experience**.\n- Meg suggested adding **clear flags or indicators during filming** for easier identification of cuts, which Baylee supported to streamline the editing workflow.\n\n## **New Podcast Strategy: Payments on Tap**\n\nPayments on Tap will **target executives and decision-makers**, differentiating itself from Wrestling Payments, which remains focused on operational staff (13:15).\n\n- Meg explained that Payments on Tap will offer a **30,000-foot view on industry trends and strategy**, helping leaders stay ahead amid bank mergers and market shifts.\n- The show will leverage the existing **Payments on Tap branded executive networking events** to build brand recognition and regional awareness before scaling nationally.\n- Distribution plans focus on **LinkedIn, the niche website, newsletters, and event promotions**, with social media emphasis on shorts and potential paid campaigns to boost reach (16:41).\n- Meg highlighted that analytics showed the FinTech series did not outperform operational content as expected, prompting a focus on targeted promotion and engagement tactics.\n- TikTok integration was discussed as a possible future channel for short clips, with the team agreeing to prepare vertical video formats to accommodate this (25:57).\n\n## **Branding, Visual Identity, and Design Feedback**\n\nThe Payments on Tap brand will retain **gray and green colors and the arrow element from the original logo** to maintain connection to the niche brand, but explore **variations in color schemes and backgrounds** for clearer differentiation (29:37).\n\n- Igor and Meg agreed to experiment with **inverted color schemes (black on white or white on black)** to reduce similarity with Wrestling Payments.\n- Meg emphasized the importance of a **friendly yet executive tone** with branding that feels inviting but professional.\n- The team favors adding **brewery-related sound effects** and thematic elements without casual or bar-like distractions to tie into the live event atmosphere.\n- Design preferences include **quote cards with quotation marks at the start**, large clean images with faces, and more emphasis on bubbles or tap imagery instead of arrows to create visual variety.\n- Meg and Carlos requested the design team avoid overused arrow motifs and instead **incorporate unique imagery that aligns with the Payments on Tap identity**.\n- Navy blue was identified as a promising accent color to complement or replace dull gray and green tones, with enthusiasm from all stakeholders for testing this option (33:46).\n\n## **Operational and Scheduling Considerations**\n\nThe team plans to **pause meetings during the upcoming holiday period** and schedule a **separate session early next year to review Payments on Tap designs and materials** to maintain momentum (36:19).\n\n- Alyssa is expected to have at least one episode ready to launch around January, supporting a timely rollout.\n- Baylee offered to coordinate calendar invites and suggested including Alyssa in future discussions depending on availability.\n- Meg confirmed ongoing communication about billing and invoices to ensure administrative clarity before year-end.\n- The established workflow for content submission and review will continue, with potential additions for social media content approval to align branding and promotion efforts.\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Analytics","Payments on Tap","Wrestling Payments","Podcast Branding","Social Media Strategy","Financial Services Podcasts"],"overview":"- **Podcast Performance:** Wrestling Payments launched 27 episodes in 2025, achieving 2,168 downloads, averaging 80 per episode.  \n- **Listener Demographics:** 85% of listeners are from North America, primarily using iPhone via Apple Podcasts and Spotify.  \n- **Social Media Growth:** Social media generated 22 new followers, with engagement up 10% year-over-year, totaling 14,300 views.  \n- **New Podcast Launch:** Payments on Tap will focus on executives, providing industry insights amid market changes, with LinkedIn as a key distribution channel.  \n- **Branding Strategy:** Payments on Tap will keep key design elements but explore new colors and unique imagery for better differentiation.  \n- **Operational Planning:** Meetings paused for holidays; session scheduled early next year to review Payments on Tap designs and ensure workflow continuity.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nInform editing team to be more thorough in removing repeated take mistakes in upcoming podcast episodes (03:30)\nIncorporate brewery-themed subtle sound elements into Payments on Tap podcast intro (22:40)\nObtain high-resolution headshot of Alyssa from LinkedIn or request directly (23:25)\nExperiment with alternate logo color schemes including black/white and navy blue variations to distinguish Payments on Tap branding (29:45)\nPrepare social media post guidelines to align with podcast review process (20:10)\nSend calendar invite for a follow-up meeting after holidays to review podcast design concepts (36:15)\n\n**Meg Norlund - NEACH**\nShare Alyssa’s new podcast episode opening clip for review (21:15)\nProvide headshot image of Alyssa if available (23:30)\nReview and provide feedback on payments podcast work order and invoice receipt inquiry (37:05)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nSend graphics and video source files for client portal and asset templates requested by NEACH (05:50)\nProvide detailed 2025 podcast analytics report and Good Pods podcast listing link (09:45)\nCollaborate with design team on logo adjustments, especially regarding arrow/banner element and color tuning (29:30)\n\n**Carlos**\nProvide design input on logos and social media graphics focusing on distinctive imagery apart from arrows (27:00)\n"},"duration":37.79999923706055,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"id":2,"name":"Carlos"},{"id":3,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Yeah.","index":0,"end_time":0.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, what''s up?","index":1,"end_time":0.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How''s it going, Carlos?","index":2,"end_time":4.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Pretty good, Pretty good.","index":3,"end_time":7.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":5.92,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"How about you?","index":4,"end_time":8.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":7.92,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s been.","index":5,"end_time":10.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Been great.","index":6,"end_time":11.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I feel like it''s just so busy this time of year.","index":7,"end_time":15.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":19.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What, do you have any plans for the holidays?","index":9,"end_time":22.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re going to do, like, a brunch at our house for the holiday and then kind of just do cookies with Isabella and, you know, just chill the night before starting our new traditions.","index":10,"end_time":35.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.12,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"That''s adorable.","index":11,"end_time":37.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s exciting.","index":12,"end_time":38.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":37.87,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Is she, like, decorating cookies?","index":13,"end_time":40.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Probably not Licking the frosting.","index":14,"end_time":45.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s probably what it''s going to be.","index":15,"end_time":48.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.15,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"He''s probably going to test each one just to make sure it''s good to go.","index":16,"end_time":51.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.59,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":17,"end_time":53.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.71,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The best taste tester.","index":18,"end_time":55.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":19,"end_time":56.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":56.33,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Hi, Meg.","index":20,"end_time":58.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.61,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Hi, guys.","index":21,"end_time":59.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.21,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How''s your day going?","index":22,"end_time":63.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry, my dog''s barking at the Amazon delivery truck.","index":23,"end_time":70.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Very well, thank you.","index":24,"end_time":72.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Good.","index":25,"end_time":74.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My dogs were doing that right before this call.","index":26,"end_time":76.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They.","index":27,"end_time":76.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They love the.","index":28,"end_time":77.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The mailman.","index":29,"end_time":78.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So calm.","index":30,"end_time":80.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.17,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But today he''s special.","index":31,"end_time":82.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.81,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Has an out about them.","index":32,"end_time":83.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.33,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, Well, we''ve got quite a bit to go over today.","index":33,"end_time":92.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Igor''s got just our regular agenda items, plus we have a 2025 recap for you just with how the podcast did.","index":34,"end_time":102.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we want to talk about next steps for Alyssa''s podcast.","index":35,"end_time":106.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":36,"end_time":110.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":37,"end_time":110.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hey, guys, let''s start with.","index":38,"end_time":113.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":111.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The weekly agenda.","index":39,"end_time":124.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":119.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yeah, these podcasts are.","index":40,"end_time":128.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":126.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Podcast episodes are delivered, and the upcoming episode is with Phil Robin.","index":41,"end_time":136.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":129.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Now, for these four episodes, Meg, did you have time to go through them?","index":42,"end_time":141.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":136.67,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think that we covered Mickey Marshall.","index":43,"end_time":147.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":141.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Also, you had some feedback on Brian, Holly, and then for these two, I just recently sent them.","index":44,"end_time":154.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":147.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So Mickey is with the.","index":45,"end_time":157.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.55,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Their PR team, needed to review.","index":46,"end_time":159.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that''s over with them right now.","index":47,"end_time":161.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And I''m not sure when she''s going to get back to us, honestly, with the holiday season kicking in, Brian''s.","index":48,"end_time":169.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.27,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think I made my edits.","index":49,"end_time":171.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m not sure if I made the all of them.","index":50,"end_time":175.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.35,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And I did have a question about the editing process.","index":51,"end_time":177.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.23,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"When Alyssa films versus when Joe films, Joe rolls, he just.","index":52,"end_time":185.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.39,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"If he makes a mistake, he just keeps going.","index":53,"end_time":186.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.15,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Alyssa says, new North, I''m cutting this out.","index":54,"end_time":191.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.23,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Whatever she''s.","index":55,"end_time":192.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She makes, she says it, and she''s like, okay, I''m going to start again.","index":56,"end_time":196.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How is that just something we''ll edit when we get the videos?","index":57,"end_time":200.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Or is that something your team notices when they go through editing?","index":58,"end_time":205,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.44,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Because the Brian one, I did notice all of those pieces were still in there.","index":59,"end_time":210.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I just wanted to confirm, like, yes, we take care of it on our end.","index":60,"end_time":213.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.16,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we can build in that extra time or your team does usually catch it.","index":61,"end_time":220.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And that was just like a one off.","index":62,"end_time":222.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, our team should catch that.","index":63,"end_time":225.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we will let them know to be more thorough with the.","index":64,"end_time":229.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The review there.","index":65,"end_time":230.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that gets edited out.","index":66,"end_time":232.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":67,"end_time":233.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.63,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And if there''s a way that we can indicate it to you, we could try doing that as well.","index":68,"end_time":240.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then the, the other two, Patricia''s and Sanjeev''s, we should probably have those turned around shortly.","index":69,"end_time":249.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a good thing that you mentioned that actually with the four.","index":70,"end_time":256.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Four Alyssa''s episodes.","index":71,"end_time":257.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":256.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":258.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":258.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the one with the Sanji was edited more thoroughly.","index":73,"end_time":263.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":258.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":74,"end_time":263.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.27,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":75,"end_time":263.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And there were like similar, similar things.","index":76,"end_time":266.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So Ellis, I was like, okay, now we''re just going to cut this out and then start again from.","index":77,"end_time":272.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, so yeah, that was the second one.","index":78,"end_time":274.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":272.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then also.","index":79,"end_time":275.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, we, we had, let''s say more experience with the first one.","index":80,"end_time":280.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":275.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we could calibrate on that.","index":81,"end_time":281.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":280.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":82,"end_time":282.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I wasn''t sure because we''re.","index":83,"end_time":284.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Joe just filmed so differently.","index":84,"end_time":286,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.2,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I just wanted to make sure it was.","index":85,"end_time":287.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.16,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We understood how to do it.","index":86,"end_time":289.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Sure, no problem.","index":87,"end_time":291.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":290,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Social content is scheduled through end of February, as you can see.","index":88,"end_time":299.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.69,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And These are some YouTube analytics.","index":89,"end_time":305.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":302.89,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"779 views and seven 17.5 hours of watch time in the past 28 days.","index":90,"end_time":313.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":305.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And your viewers find you mainly through shorts.","index":91,"end_time":319.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315.05,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So shorts are the way to go still.","index":92,"end_time":322.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":319.77,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And that it''s a great thing that they''re published on the channel.","index":93,"end_time":327.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":322.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then for the 