 Gunnell"},{"text":"It usually takes some time to get on those lists.","index":171,"end_time":728.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":172,"end_time":731.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.05,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But any other questions?","index":173,"end_time":732.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Igor will send over all that stuff afterwards.","index":174,"end_time":734.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Probably something Joe would love to see too.","index":175,"end_time":737.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just great stuff there.","index":176,"end_time":741.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so we want to talk about our new podcast.","index":177,"end_time":747.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve got Payments on Tap.","index":178,"end_time":751.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Super excited.","index":179,"end_time":752.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You got.","index":180,"end_time":753.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I love the concepts you put together for this.","index":181,"end_time":755.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just, just to confirm this though, this is still how we talked about it initially, right.","index":182,"end_time":760.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.83,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Where we''re just splitting, we''re doing one resting payments and one payments on tap.","index":183,"end_time":764.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.99,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":184,"end_time":766.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.07,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we''re just going to see how this plays out for the year and if it does incredibly well, we''ll probably move it into a better cadence, which I think it probably will do pretty well.","index":185,"end_time":777.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.23,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But yeah, for now it''s just the one in one.","index":186,"end_time":780.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.47,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yep, yep, that''s the plan.","index":187,"end_time":782.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we do want to clarify a few things and just make sure we''re on the same page with the.","index":188,"end_time":788.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The future of the show.","index":189,"end_time":790.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So yeah, just want to make sure we''re on the same page.","index":190,"end_time":795.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Page.","index":191,"end_time":795.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But it sounds like like the primary goal of the show, like kind of what you''ve been doing with Wrestling Payments.","index":192,"end_time":802.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Are they the same?","index":193,"end_time":803.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Seems like a lot of it is like community and thought leadership.","index":194,"end_time":808.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But correct me if I''m wrong there.","index":195,"end_time":811.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So Wrestling Payments is going to keep going after our core audience.","index":196,"end_time":817.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.86,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"This is sort of your operations people, these are the doers.","index":197,"end_time":820.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"They need to know about modernization, but from a perspective of like how, how do I do it?","index":198,"end_time":826.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.45,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"What do I need to know to get my job done?","index":199,"end_time":829.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.05,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So it''s still, they''re similar themed, kind of where Payments on Tap is a little bit different is it''s going to speak to your decision makers, influencers and sort of executives.","index":200,"end_time":843.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we think more like the fintech Shark Week series that Alyssa did where it''s really that like 30,000 foot view.","index":201,"end_time":854.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.33,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":202,"end_time":855.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And these are, these are what executives or department leaders need to know in order to fight against mergers and acquisitions.","index":203,"end_time":865.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"They, you know, really getting them ahead of the game instead of behind the game.","index":204,"end_time":869.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.92,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s not that day to day approach to payments workflow.","index":205,"end_time":873.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So.","index":206,"end_time":874.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I think it is different.","index":207,"end_time":876.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"One''s a little bit higher ranked and one''s a little bit more lower ranked in terms of doing and executing and decisioning and strategic direction.","index":208,"end_time":886.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I will say Payments on Tap sounds strange until you know that we have a capstone strategic event called the Future of Payment Symposium and we do networking sessions with executives called Payments on Tap.","index":209,"end_time":905.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.36,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So around these Things we do breweries, like we rent out a brewery and we bring in executives to have conversations.","index":210,"end_time":911.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.13,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And that''s branded as Payments on tap.","index":211,"end_time":913.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And so she wants to be that, to be an extension so that they understand.","index":212,"end_time":916.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s where that all came from.","index":213,"end_time":918.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.37,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Also, I think it fits with her style and it still kind of has that kitschy, fun feeling that Wrestling Payments has.","index":214,"end_time":924.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.21,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But it''s geared towards.","index":215,"end_time":926.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.45,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The audience will know the name, at least local, you know, the regional aspect.","index":216,"end_time":931.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.49,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then we''ll work on getting it national as we use this podcast to do that.","index":217,"end_time":936.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.59,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I would say this would be more leaders of fintechs, leaders of financial institutions, or the influencers in the financial institution that have influence over the executive team.","index":218,"end_time":950.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.07,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Topics are going to be very heavily focused on staying relevant in a very complicated and shifting market space where banks, as I''m sure you know, just anecdotally from being in the world, they''re just merging left, right and center.","index":219,"end_time":969.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.75,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So if you don''t, these community banks, these credit unions, it''s really going to be like, where do you need to keep your eyes and focus on in order to stay operating?","index":220,"end_time":978.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.92,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And how could you do that?","index":221,"end_time":981.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.16,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How could you do that?","index":222,"end_time":981.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.08,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Even as a small fish in a, you know, a big C. Yeah, love it.","index":223,"end_time":986.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That, that''s, that''s going to be great.","index":224,"end_time":988.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then where do you expect most of your listeners to find the show?","index":225,"end_time":994.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, is it going to be at your events or are you wanting to do some social distribution for this as well?","index":226,"end_time":1000.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This.","index":227,"end_time":1002.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1001.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So this will be interesting because your analytics disproved a thought.","index":228,"end_time":1007.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.07,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The analytics Igor just went through disproved a thought that we had internally.","index":229,"end_time":1011.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that was a little rough to see it because I anticipated the FinTech series to have done much better than the more operational focused ones simply because the topic point should have been a little bit more broad.","index":230,"end_time":1026.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1012.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we obviously will push it through our membership.","index":231,"end_time":1031.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.27,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So the way we''ve been doing Wrestling Payments, we email it out to the appropriate audiences, we include it in our LinkedIn.","index":232,"end_time":1038.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.47,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''d love to do or consider some social pushes around this, but I think we can work on that with different ads and stuff that we have internally.","index":233,"end_time":1048.289,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.929,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":234,"end_time":1049.009,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.449,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think what''s really going to hit hard is going to be those shorts.","index":235,"end_time":1054.728,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.329,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think those shorts are going to continue to do really well.","index":236,"end_time":1057.729,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.728,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that''s going to be probably a prime focus.","index":237,"end_time":1060.209,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.049,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then we want to, obviously we''ll, we''ll promote it at all of our events and we go to you a lot of different trade shows where the, there''s an Executive audience, so we''ll be pushing it there as well.","index":238,"end_time":1072.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.369,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":239,"end_time":1074.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I''m guessing for social, it''s going to be mostly LinkedIn.","index":240,"end_time":1078.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":1078.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":242,"end_time":1079.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":243,"end_time":1079.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Keep that in mind because that affects, like, the dimensions we use for a lot of the video clips and.","index":244,"end_time":1085.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And all that good stuff.","index":245,"end_time":1087.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":246,"end_time":1087.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.18,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then I''m guessing we''re going to want to follow the same process.","index":247,"end_time":1092.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1089.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like that was what we''ve been doing for Wrestling Payments.","index":248,"end_time":1095.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ll submit using the link or is there anything different you''re wanting to do?","index":249,"end_time":1100.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s a really good question.","index":250,"end_time":1102.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1101.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m glad you actually asked that because from we''ve seen.","index":251,"end_time":1106.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":252,"end_time":1109.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Engagement with the podcast on that LinkedIn Wrestling payments page, but I think we still see maybe better when we put it on the niche page.","index":253,"end_time":1118.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.36,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And now that we have two podcasts and potentially a third.","index":254,"end_time":1122.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Bailey, how many is too many?","index":255,"end_time":1124.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1122.89,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, honestly tell me, because we have interest now in potentially developing with two other staff members, something called ach Fraud files.","index":256,"end_time":1132.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.33,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like a true crime, but around payments fraud.","index":257,"end_time":1136.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.77,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I was like, okay, that''s actually one I would want to listen to.","index":258,"end_time":1139.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1136.89,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":259,"end_time":1140.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.81,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But if three is too many, please tell me.","index":260,"end_time":1142.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1140.21,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that''s something for 2027.","index":261,"end_time":1145.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1144.25,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":262,"end_time":1146.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1145.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Love this.","index":263,"end_time":1146.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1146.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But I''m wondering if we should bring it all back into the niche page again and maybe shut, because we just don''t.","index":264,"end_time":1155.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.45,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t even know how many followers.","index":265,"end_time":1156.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.65,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''ll take a look and see how many followers we have.","index":266,"end_time":1158.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s just not.","index":267,"end_time":1159.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.73,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s not a lot of traction.","index":268,"end_time":1161.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1160.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":1162.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":270,"end_time":1163.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And I think we originally did that because you didn''t have time to review the content.","index":271,"end_time":1168.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1168.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We had talked about maybe putting together guidelines.","index":273,"end_time":1171.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, if you have.","index":274,"end_time":1173.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1172.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If we had like a short list of these are the things you should do, not, not do, then we can, I think, make sure we''re nailing the content better.","index":275,"end_time":1182.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":276,"end_time":1184.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.47,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But yeah, or if you have any posts that you feel like you really like that you''ve shared, we could use that and put together just some, like, best practices.","index":277,"end_time":1193.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I really like what you guys send us in the show notes, how at the bottom there''s like, how to put this on different, like, areas of social.","index":278,"end_time":1202.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1194.11,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That''s really good.","index":279,"end_time":1204.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.14,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And we use that information for the shorts when we post them, and it always seems to work really well.","index":280,"end_time":1209.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.34,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m wondering if maybe that can be part of our.","index":281,"end_time":1214.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.66,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Our review process.","index":282,"end_time":1215.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"When we review all of that information, we can maybe just put in some things for the social media.","index":283,"end_time":1222.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that process will still go through, but we''ll just have upfront line of sight to it and approval there.","index":284,"end_time":1231.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1222.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, no, yeah, I love that.","index":285,"end_time":1235.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.06,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":286,"end_time":1235.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then.","index":287,"end_time":1238.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":288,"end_time":1240.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You already know all that stuff, so we''d love some thoughts on, like, branding and identity.","index":289,"end_time":1246.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We also mood board that will go through.","index":290,"end_time":1249.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, like, what elements are you wanting to keep in this brand?","index":291,"end_time":1253.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, should it feel very, like gray and green or you wanting to do something a little different?","index":292,"end_time":1260.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1253.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What are your thoughts there?","index":293,"end_time":1261.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we have the Payments on Tap logo and it is gray and green.","index":294,"end_time":1265.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I know.","index":295,"end_time":1266.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I just hope, like, the audience doesn''t see it as much as we do and get frustrated with it, but I think we need to kind of keep into that.","index":296,"end_time":1275.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1267.18,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":297,"end_time":1275.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.02,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She has.","index":298,"end_time":1276.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She wrote.","index":299,"end_time":1276.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"She''s gonna film something so that we''re ready in January.","index":300,"end_time":1280.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Ish.","index":301,"end_time":1280.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1280.46,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Whenever we start getting this ready, she has an episode ready to go.","index":302,"end_time":1284.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1280.86,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":303,"end_time":1284.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And she did a really cute opening.","index":304,"end_time":1287.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":305,"end_time":1288.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.7,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Cute is the wrong word.","index":306,"end_time":1289.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1288.82,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It was fun.","index":307,"end_time":1290.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m not gonna be able put hands on it so quickly, but I will get that over to you.","index":308,"end_time":1295.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, you know how Wrestling Payments has the announcer voice?","index":309,"end_time":1298.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.38,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":310,"end_time":1298.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1298.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Which is like my favorite part of the.","index":311,"end_time":1300.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1298.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The podcast.","index":312,"end_time":1301.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1300.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Anyways, she wrote something that''s kind of fun that feels like it''s similar for a company, you know, two different podcasts.","index":313,"end_time":1308.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.38,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So if they had been watching Wrestling Payments, it''s not such a far leap.","index":314,"end_time":1312.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.74,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Or Payments on Tap.","index":315,"end_time":1313.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.08,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":316,"end_time":1314.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I will get that over to you guys to take a look at.","index":317,"end_time":1318.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.48,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I love.","index":318,"end_time":1319.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1318.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think she agrees with me in that, like, we both really like that kind of breakup where it starts with a little clip and then this really fun kind of announcement comes through and then it leads into the.","index":319,"end_time":1330.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1319.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The programming.","index":320,"end_time":1332.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we feeling the.","index":321,"end_time":1334.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.44,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I did share the.","index":322,"end_time":1335.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The logo with you, right?","index":323,"end_time":1336.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yep.","index":324,"end_time":1337.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1336.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I love the idea of incorporating some sounds like brewery type sounds.","index":325,"end_time":1344.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"This group does not.","index":326,"end_time":1346.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.7,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know how to do that.","index":327,"end_time":1348.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1347.86,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m not that creative.","index":328,"end_time":1349.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But hopefully someone on your team is.","index":329,"end_time":1351.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1349.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Maybe they could do something with that.","index":330,"end_time":1354.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1351.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, we could totally do that.","index":331,"end_time":1356.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''ll probably be doing things like playing bits of it at the Payments On Tap events, maybe in doing like a live taping at one of those things.","index":332,"end_time":1367.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1356.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I think having it tie into that brewery feel would be really great, but not be we''re drunk at bar.","index":333,"end_time":1374.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":334,"end_time":1375.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1374.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, yeah, we don''t want like chatter in the background maybe.","index":335,"end_time":1380.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like.","index":336,"end_time":1380.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.14,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I get.","index":337,"end_time":1381.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I get what you''re saying.","index":338,"end_time":1382.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":339,"end_time":1383.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1383.34,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know how to do it.","index":340,"end_time":1384.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1383.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But yeah, we''ll let our team get creative with that.","index":341,"end_time":1389.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I saw Alyssa has a really nice headshot on LinkedIn.","index":342,"end_time":1393.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you know if she wants us to use her headshot in any of the imagery or.","index":343,"end_time":1398.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, cool, cool, cool.","index":344,"end_time":1401.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll grab what we have from LinkedIn, but if she is like a high res version of her headshot, I can shoot her an email too.","index":345,"end_time":1409.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If I''ve got it, I can send it over to you.","index":346,"end_time":1411.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1409.04,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":347,"end_time":1412.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"When we were looking at that payment, Good pods or whatever we have, we have a pretty strong competitor in this.","index":348,"end_time":1423.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1415.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I wanted to go, oh, podcast payments nerds.","index":349,"end_time":1428.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1423.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Is they.","index":350,"end_time":1433.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"They''ll speak to the same audience.","index":351,"end_time":1434.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1433.17,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So that is somebody to sort of take a look at.","index":352,"end_time":1440.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1436.49,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We don''t want to be too similar.","index":353,"end_time":1441.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.13,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1442.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"To the payments nerds.","index":355,"end_time":1443.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I want to make sure.","index":356,"end_time":1445.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.49,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Because they also go to a bar.","index":357,"end_time":1448.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1445.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Payments and beer.","index":358,"end_time":1450.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.46,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Is that what it is?","index":359,"end_time":1451.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, payments beer nerds.","index":360,"end_time":1457.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1455.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, it''s.","index":361,"end_time":1461.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1458.34,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think the same people.","index":362,"end_time":1462.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.22,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Let me see if I can get onto their site.","index":363,"end_time":1465.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1464.1,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think it''s the same people that run the payments nerds.","index":364,"end_time":1468.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1465.46,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Or at least there''s a little crossover there.","index":365,"end_time":1469.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1468.22,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":366,"end_time":1470.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1470.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But they''re very passionate.","index":367,"end_time":1474.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1472.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"They.","index":368,"end_time":1475.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.9,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We know these people.","index":369,"end_time":1476.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1475.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like we''re all very good friends, but they''re very passionate about beer and pigments and they merge.","index":370,"end_time":1483.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.06,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like that is their thing.","index":371,"end_time":1485.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1483.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We don''t want to go in that direction.","index":372,"end_time":1487.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.34,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We don''t want this to feel like glasses together.","index":373,"end_time":1490.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like we''re going to tell you about beer.","index":374,"end_time":1491.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1490.06,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''re not going to talk about beer.","index":375,"end_time":1492.939,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1491.7,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s just going to be in a brewery that it often happens.","index":376,"end_time":1495.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we just want to make sure, like if they have any type of opening or, you know, slogan or whatever that it''s not like, okay, yeah, we.","index":377,"end_time":1508.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.7,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Can listen to some of those episodes and make sure we do something different from what they have.","index":378,"end_time":1513.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1508.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":379,"end_time":1515.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1514.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it sounds like too like the tone we want it to feel like friendly and inviting but not too casual.","index":380,"end_time":1522.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1516.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like we''re still talking to executives, but okay, loving.","index":381,"end_time":1526.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for.","index":382,"end_time":1530.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We kind of already talked about distribution.","index":383,"end_time":1533.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like you''ll probably go on your website, mostly LinkedIn.","index":384,"end_time":1537,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think you''re still doing your newsletter so you''ll probably share it on that.","index":385,"end_time":1543.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then you''re also doing some paid.","index":386,"end_time":1544.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1543.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":387,"end_time":1545.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1545,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then so we''ll probably do like similar deliverables to what we we do for wrestling payments.","index":388,"end_time":1552.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1547.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But is there anything you''d want to change or add in there?","index":389,"end_time":1555.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have talked a few times now about potentially trying TikTok and seeing if some of the shorts would work there.","index":390,"end_time":1563.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1557.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m not on TikTok, so I don''t know too much about it, but maybe just knowing that that is something we might try.","index":391,"end_time":1571.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1563.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":392,"end_time":1572.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.2,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Just making sure there''s space for that or sizing for that.","index":393,"end_time":1575.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1572.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":394,"end_time":1577,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":395,"end_time":1577.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do some of those vertical clips too.","index":396,"end_time":1580.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll take a look now at a mood board just to get your thoughts.","index":397,"end_time":1589.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1582.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll hop over here to logos.","index":398,"end_time":1592.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1589.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I. I like to preface that.","index":399,"end_time":1594.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You can point out things you like and things that you don''t like, and that''s just going to help our design team.","index":400,"end_time":1600.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1596.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have a preference between these logos?","index":401,"end_time":1604.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1601.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Which one?","index":402,"end_time":1604.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We prioritize in the designs.","index":403,"end_time":1607.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The first one is what we use the most.","index":404,"end_time":1610.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":405,"end_time":1611.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.4,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So it would.","index":406,"end_time":1614.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1612.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Would that reflect in the other designs?","index":407,"end_time":1616.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1614.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, are you wanting maybe like a mostly white background that could stand out from Wrestling Payments?","index":408,"end_time":1621.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1616.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve grabbed some of these because I think of most of the stuff is a gray background, so that could be a good way to differentiate.","index":409,"end_time":1628.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But do you have any preferences there?","index":410,"end_time":1629.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1628.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":411,"end_time":1631.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''d love to see what you guys come up with.","index":412,"end_time":1633.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.76,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Just.","index":413,"end_time":1635.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1634.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I. I do like the idea of maybe like.","index":414,"end_time":1637.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like you said, that would be distinct from Wrestling Payments.","index":415,"end_time":1640.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, but.","index":416,"end_time":1642.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1641.2,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And I think the original logo, the intention of.","index":417,"end_time":1645.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1643.12,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"There''s like, foam over the payments and in the glass.","index":418,"end_time":1651.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.2,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, you kind of reverse it.","index":419,"end_time":1652.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.36,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"It doesn''t look as foamy.","index":420,"end_time":1654.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1652.8,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Foamy, but yeah.","index":421,"end_time":1656.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.04,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I just remember having that conversation and it being.","index":422,"end_time":1660.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1657.44,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"But yeah, there''s like, foam there from the beer.","index":423,"end_time":1663.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1661.53,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Love it.","index":424,"end_time":1664.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did you make this logo?","index":425,"end_time":1666.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did not.","index":426,"end_time":1666.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1666.25,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"No.","index":427,"end_time":1667.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1666.93,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s too nice.","index":428,"end_time":1668.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1667.37,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"You''re selling yourself short.","index":429,"end_time":1671.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It looks.","index":430,"end_time":1673.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s so good.","index":431,"end_time":1674.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.49,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"When I saw it, I was so excited.","index":432,"end_time":1676.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1674.73,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I was like, this looks so great.","index":433,"end_time":1678.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1676.17,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I love beer, so.","index":434,"end_time":1679.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.49,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And I love niche, so.","index":435,"end_time":1681.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.41,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s great.","index":436,"end_time":1682.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1681.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"This is awesome.","index":437,"end_time":1684.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1683.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so, um, these are some other designs we''ve done for you as well.","index":438,"end_time":1689.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1685.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we do have some white background designs for Wrestling Payments, but we could try and find ways to make sure it looks different here.","index":439,"end_time":1698.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But are there any elements from, like, some of these Wrestling payment designs that you love or any that you want to stay away from?","index":440,"end_time":1704.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I like the quote cards where it''s both logos at top.","index":441,"end_time":1712.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1707.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":442,"end_time":1713.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1712.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, I love all of this for Wrestling Payments, but maybe leaning less into the arrows and I don''t know, maybe doing something more with those bubbles or something more with, like, the tap kind of.","index":443,"end_time":1729.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":444,"end_time":1730.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1729.44,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m not really sure.","index":445,"end_time":1731.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1730.32,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That would maybe help distinguish it a little bit as well.","index":446,"end_time":1735.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.12,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1736.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1736.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":448,"end_time":1737.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Leaning into the on tap part a bit more.","index":449,"end_time":1740.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Mm.","index":450,"end_time":1741.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Do you have any thoughts, Carlos?","index":451,"end_time":1744.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s the same Thing.","index":452,"end_time":1746,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1745.04,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, the arrows.","index":453,"end_time":1746.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1746,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I think we''ve used it for so many designs, so it would be nice to see those, like a little contact, not the.","index":454,"end_time":1756.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1746.92,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"The contact card, whatever, but a little image.","index":455,"end_time":1759.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1756.4,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Something there would make it look really.","index":456,"end_time":1761.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1759.6,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Different for this part.","index":457,"end_time":1763.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1761.56,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":458,"end_time":1765.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1764.08,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"So no arrows, but playing with some other type of imagery.","index":459,"end_time":1768.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1765.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, Bailey, can I just jump in on this really quickly?","index":460,"end_time":1773.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1769.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Can we go back to the logo?","index":461,"end_time":1775.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1773.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Payments on tap logo.","index":462,"end_time":1777.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1775.61,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":463,"end_time":1777.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1777.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I don''t know if this is like set in stone logo, but if there is some, like, space to work.","index":464,"end_time":1788.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1778.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Actually, I think there''s like in the word payments, so it''s highlighted basically with this banner.","index":465,"end_time":1796.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1789.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So this thing is, I think, an arrow.","index":466,"end_time":1800.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1797,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So now that you said that you wouldn''t like an arrow, so maybe that''s a detail that we could rework.","index":467,"end_time":1807.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1800.76,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So maybe not like foam or something.","index":468,"end_time":1811.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1808.6,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Maybe just like have it a single color.","index":469,"end_time":1814.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1811.56,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just like a gray or green.","index":470,"end_time":1815.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1814.16,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then just to leave out this arrow sign so that it doesn''t.","index":471,"end_time":1820.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1815.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So it''s not too similar to niche.","index":472,"end_time":1824.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1821.62,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So I do know that they requested the payments like that.","index":473,"end_time":1829.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1825.38,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So it tied back to the niche logo.","index":474,"end_time":1831.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1829.1,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if they would be comfortable going just a solid color.","index":475,"end_time":1837.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1833.46,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But maybe from that point of view, Igor, it might be better to go towards the white on black or black on white and make it less obvious in that way.","index":476,"end_time":1847.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1838.26,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Because when you see it in color, it really does look very green, gray, Very similar to wrestling payments, very similar to niche.","index":477,"end_time":1854.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1847.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Maybe if it''s the more inverse over here that cuts down on that a little bit.","index":478,"end_time":1860.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1855.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The Blick, the lower two logos.","index":479,"end_time":1863.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1861,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, where.","index":480,"end_time":1864.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1863.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re the same color.","index":481,"end_time":1865.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have we tried.","index":482,"end_time":1867.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1867,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And I''m only thinking of the Koozies.","index":483,"end_time":1870.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1868.44,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I wish I had the Koozies, but I think we had a two color logo on black.","index":484,"end_time":1874.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1870.4,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"So it''d be a combination of the.","index":485,"end_time":1877.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1876.63,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Of the top right and the bottom left.","index":486,"end_time":1880.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1877.95,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"But.","index":487,"end_time":1882.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1881.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think we did that for the Koozies.","index":488,"end_time":1885.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1884.07,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"That might be another option.","index":489,"end_time":1888.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1886.79,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"We were open to looking at anything as well.","index":490,"end_time":1891.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1889.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, whatever you guys can.","index":491,"end_time":1893.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1891.83,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay.","index":492,"end_time":1895.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1895.11,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Come up with.","index":493,"end_time":1896.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1895.75,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":494,"end_time":1897.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1897.11,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I just know that was one of the requests to make it kind of look.","index":495,"end_time":1900.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1897.79,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":496,"end_time":1902.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1901.11,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we.","index":497,"end_time":1902.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1902.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We gotta keep the arrow, but we could play around with the.","index":498,"end_time":1905.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1902.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The colors or play around with like the white, black, black, white kind of thing.","index":499,"end_time":1911.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we want to introduce a whole different color scheme.","index":500,"end_time":1916.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.15,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like we want to keep it on brand in that way, but.","index":501,"end_time":1919.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1916.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":502,"end_time":1921.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.11,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":503,"end_time":1924.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.91,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''ll put.","index":504,"end_time":1925.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1924.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll play around and.","index":505,"end_time":1926.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1925.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, well, we''ll come back with designs and I''m sure you''ll have feedback and we''ll.","index":506,"end_time":1930.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1926.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll figure out something.","index":507,"end_time":1932.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1930.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":508,"end_time":1932.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1932.02,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":509,"end_time":1933.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1932.78,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":510,"end_time":1934.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.58,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"So then looking at some.","index":511,"end_time":1936.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1934.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just other inspo to get your thoughts on things that you like and don''t like.","index":512,"end_time":1940.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1936.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So here''s some stuff that we did for Nichu a while back, plus just some other things we saw on your LinkedIn.","index":513,"end_time":1947.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1940.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any elements from these that you really love or you don''t love that we should avoid?","index":514,"end_time":1953.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1949.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I do like the quote card here better than the wrestling payments one where the.","index":515,"end_time":1958.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1955.01,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The quotation marks are before and not behind.","index":516,"end_time":1961.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1958.73,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s a little bit easier to read.","index":517,"end_time":1963.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1962.21,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":518,"end_time":1964.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1964.05,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I mean, I like everything about Michu.","index":519,"end_time":1967.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1965.25,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s a shame we''re not really focused on that anymore.","index":520,"end_time":1969.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1967.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But I do.","index":521,"end_time":1971.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1970.77,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I do tend to like that kind of quote style a little bit better.","index":522,"end_time":1974.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1971.73,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I also like that first one you did for niche where the two speakers are boxed like that.","index":523,"end_time":1982.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1976.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":524,"end_time":1984.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1984.17,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Can introduce some color on the.","index":525,"end_time":1987.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1985.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We don''t have a shield, so I don''t know if that still works, but however.","index":526,"end_time":1990.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1987.73,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":527,"end_time":1993.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1990.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Because I think the shield was really just a Nichu.","index":528,"end_time":1996.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1993.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll have to find something more just niche themed.","index":529,"end_time":2003.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1997.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":530,"end_time":2003.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2003.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Love it.","index":531,"end_time":2004.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2004.09,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And then any, like, notes or thoughts on these designs?","index":532,"end_time":2008.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2004.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve noticed that pictures work like people''s faces work well and clean.","index":533,"end_time":2016.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2010.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Very clean.","index":534,"end_time":2017.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2016.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Works well.","index":535,"end_time":2017.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2017.34,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"People tend to read it better.","index":536,"end_time":2019.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2017.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So.","index":537,"end_time":2020.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2020.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":538,"end_time":2022.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2021.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m noticing you''re using more of this navy blue.","index":539,"end_time":2025.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2022.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can.","index":540,"end_time":2026.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2026.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Can we use that?","index":541,"end_time":2027.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2026.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or do we need to stick with gray?","index":542,"end_time":2030.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2028.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or should we combine the gray plus the blue?","index":543,"end_time":2033.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2030.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re happy to look at something if you think the navy would have, like, a.","index":544,"end_time":2039.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2034.06,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"A better look or feel.","index":545,"end_time":2042.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2039.43,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, the navy looks really nice.","index":546,"end_time":2044.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2042.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We love the navy.","index":547,"end_time":2046.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2045.27,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"We''re, like, trying to, like, test run some colors here.","index":548,"end_time":2050.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.47,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"See?","index":549,"end_time":2051.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2051.109,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":550,"end_time":2051.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2051.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":551,"end_time":2053.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2053.03,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The gray just looks very dull and the green is challenging.","index":552,"end_time":2056.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2053.47,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So.","index":553,"end_time":2057.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2056.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":554,"end_time":2057.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2057.35,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, The.","index":555,"end_time":2059.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2059.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The navy could be really nice.","index":556,"end_time":2061.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2059.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":557,"end_time":2063.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2062.76,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So we can play around with that.","index":558,"end_time":2064.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2063.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then here are just some other podcasts that we run for other clients.","index":559,"end_time":2070.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2065.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Obviously, their branding''s very different, but, like, any elements from these that you''re liking or not liking that we should avoid.","index":560,"end_time":2079.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2070.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I really like the woman in the blue.","index":561,"end_time":2083.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2079.88,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I like that.","index":562,"end_time":2085,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2084.2,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It actually kind of reminds me of what I was thinking with the bubbles from the payment app by.","index":563,"end_time":2090.829,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2085.16,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Good idea, Meg.","index":564,"end_time":2092.909,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2091.869,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I think she looks.","index":565,"end_time":2094.829,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2093.789,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":566,"end_time":2095.229,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2094.829,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Wow.","index":567,"end_time":2096.029,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2095.629,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Other people use this green.","index":568,"end_time":2097.589,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2096.029,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Huh?","index":569,"end_time":2098.029,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2097.589,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"FT ship that looks very similar to our green.","index":570,"end_time":2103.469,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2100.509,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":571,"end_time":2104.429,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2103.949,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I like how they do that, though.","index":572,"end_time":2105.989,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2104.589,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s subtle.","index":573,"end_time":2106.669,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2105.989,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s not so in your face.","index":574,"end_time":2109.549,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2106.669,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''re.","index":575,"end_time":2110.309,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2109.869,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We.","index":576,"end_time":2110.629,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2110.309,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We lead with green often.","index":577,"end_time":2112.029,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2110.629,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":578,"end_time":2114.109,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2112.269,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The.","index":579,"end_time":2114.389,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2114.109,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The white keeps it.","index":580,"end_time":2116.029,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2114.389,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":581,"end_time":2117.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2117.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not so bold.","index":582,"end_time":2119.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2117.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":583,"end_time":2120.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2119.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":584,"end_time":2121.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2121.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I like both of those blue ones that are there.","index":585,"end_time":2123.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2121.92,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think the first column guy looks.","index":586,"end_time":2128.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2124.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know why, because it''s not.","index":587,"end_time":2132.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2130.24,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But it kind of gives me more wrestling payments feel.","index":588,"end_time":2134.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2132.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But it might be just because of the gray.","index":589,"end_time":2136.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2134.96,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":590,"end_time":2137.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2136.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s probably just his.","index":591,"end_time":2139.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2137.48,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"His face.","index":592,"end_time":2141,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2140.4,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"He looks like he''s ready for a match or something.","index":593,"end_time":2143.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2141,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Intensity.","index":594,"end_time":2144.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2143.68,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yep.","index":595,"end_time":2146.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2146.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":596,"end_time":2147.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2146.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I usually like the big images for these types of posts, but I think out of all of them, I like the blue one the best.","index":597,"end_time":2154.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2147.25,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And we never get, like high res.","index":598,"end_time":2156.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2154.69,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Like, sometimes we''ll have a picture that''s this big and sometimes we have one that''s this big, so we can never make it work.","index":599,"end_time":2161.929,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2156.85,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"But I think that that route, the third one looks the cleanest.","index":600,"end_time":2166.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2161.929,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":601,"end_time":2167.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2166.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I know.","index":602,"end_time":2169.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2168.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I like that one that''s next to it as well.","index":603,"end_time":2171.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2169.49,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The.","index":604,"end_time":2171.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2171.49,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The.","index":605,"end_time":2172.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2172.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The opposite direction.","index":606,"end_time":2173.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2172.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, this one?","index":607,"end_time":2174.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2173.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":608,"end_time":2176.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2174.77,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":609,"end_time":2177.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2177.25,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Looks really awesome.","index":610,"end_time":2179.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2178.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Well, thank you for feedback.","index":611,"end_time":2181.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2179.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know we went over a little bit on time, but this will be really helpful so we can start putting together the designs.","index":612,"end_time":2189.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2181.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I just want to look.","index":613,"end_time":2191.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2190.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It looks like, like the next two weeks is holidays, so we probably won''t have any meetings.","index":614,"end_time":2197.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2191.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we might want to just schedule something separate from our regular meetings so that we can keep this moving.","index":615,"end_time":2206.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2198.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you''re wanting to launch next year, I''ll just send over a calendar invite so we can try and schedule something whenever you''re free so we can go over the designs.","index":616,"end_time":2217.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2206.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And if you want to invite Alyssa, she''s always welcome if we want to pull her in, but up to you.","index":617,"end_time":2224.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2217.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m not sure what her vacation schedule looks like, but yeah, if you send over a calendar, we can try to work through some things.","index":618,"end_time":2231.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2225.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":619,"end_time":2232.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2231.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":620,"end_time":2233.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2233.2,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Did you get my email as well?","index":621,"end_time":2235.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2233.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I just literally sent it one minute before a meeting.","index":622,"end_time":2237.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2235.16,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know whose card the invoice went to, so I''m just trying to hunt down a receipt to figure it out.","index":623,"end_time":2244.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2237.84,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":624,"end_time":2246.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2244.68,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I will ask and let you know.","index":625,"end_time":2248.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2246.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":626,"end_time":2249.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2248.48,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":627,"end_time":2250.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2249.48,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, well, great.","index":628,"end_time":2253.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2251.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks for chatting.","index":629,"end_time":2254.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2253.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":630,"end_time":2254.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2254.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll be in touch here soon.","index":631,"end_time":2256.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2254.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":632,"end_time":2257.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2256.82,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Happy holidays.","index":633,"end_time":2257.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2257.18,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"If we don''t chat beforehand.","index":634,"end_time":2259.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2257.94,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You too.","index":635,"end_time":2260.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2259.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll talk later.","index":636,"end_time":2261.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2260.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"See you guys.","index":637,"end_time":2262.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2261.54,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Bye.","index":638,"end_time":2262.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2262.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-12-18T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88046600611?pwd=5o555CNd3jppz39fBqq2aKtgUYF0MV.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,cortiz@neach.org,mnorlund@neach.org,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","cortiz@neach.org","mnorlund@neach.org","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC7ST0FDKC5X3N8XAW7VHVPK","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Reviewed 2025 podcast performance: 27 episodes, 2,168 downloads, and standout spikes in May and October.","Confirmed continued split strategy: Resting Payments targets operations, Payments on Tap for executive audiences.","Finalized January launch prep for new podcast; Alyssa''s introductory episode already filmed and approved.","Discussed editing consistency; team to improve Alyssa’s content review and ensure re-recorded phrases are cut.","Aligned on visual branding tweaks to distinguish Payments on Tap from other NEACH podcast properties."],"highlights":[{"quote":"These are really, really great numbers.","speaker":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"quote":"Payments on Tap is going to speak to your decision makers, influencers and sort of executives.","speaker":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"quote":"Still an awesome accomplishment. It usually takes some time to get on those lists.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["podcast","branding","delivery","strategy"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo-2024-04-09","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-19T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Performance and Analytics**\n\nThe **Wrestling Payments podcast published 27 episodes in 2025** and achieved a total of **2,168 downloads**, averaging **80 downloads per episode**, showing strong audience retention (04:50).\n\n- **Notable download spikes occurred in May and July** due to publishing five and six episodes respectively, and October saw high traction from episodes featuring Jordan and Rich.\n- **85% of listeners are based in North America**, with **7% in Europe** and **4% in Asia**, primarily accessing the podcast via iPhone through **Apple Podcasts and Spotify**.\n- The last five episodes collectively garnered **333 downloads**, with John’s episode leading at **88 downloads**, maintaining the North American listener dominance at **81%**.\n- Social media efforts yielded **22 new followers** and a reach of **3,200**, contributing to an overall **10% increase in engagement year-over-year**, with **14,300 views and 743 hours of watch time** indicating rising audience interaction.\n- Igor highlighted that **shorts remain the most effective content format**, accounting for the majority of viewer discovery on YouTube with **779 views and 17.5 hours of watch time in the past 28 days**.\n- Wrestling Payments was recognized by Good Pods as one of the **top three payments podcasts**, underscoring its strong market position even though the listing is recommendation-based rather than a strict ranking (08:36).\n\n## **Podcast Production and Editing Process**\n\nThe team identified **inconsistencies in editing styles between Alyssa and Joe’s filmed episodes**, affecting content flow and review efficiency (02:35).\n\n- Meg clarified that Alyssa often restarts takes after mistakes, whereas Joe keeps rolling, requiring more post-production edits.\n- Baylee confirmed their editing team will **improve review thoroughness to remove unwanted segments**, ensuring cleaner final episodes.\n- Igor noted recent episodes, such as Sanjeev’s, were edited with this approach, allowing the team to **calibrate editing standards based on experience**.\n- Meg suggested adding **clear flags or indicators during filming** for easier identification of cuts, which Baylee supported to streamline the editing workflow.\n\n## **New Podcast Strategy: Payments on Tap**\n\nPayments on Tap will **target executives and decision-makers**, differentiating itself from Wrestling Payments, which remains focused on operational staff (13:15).\n\n- Meg explained that Payments on Tap will offer a **30,000-foot view on industry trends and strategy**, helping leaders stay ahead amid bank mergers and market shifts.\n- The show will leverage the existing **Payments on Tap branded executive networking events** to build brand recognition and regional awareness before scaling nationally.\n- Distribution plans focus on **LinkedIn, the niche website, newsletters, and event promotions**, with social media emphasis on shorts and potential paid campaigns to boost reach (16:41).\n- Meg highlighted that analytics showed the FinTech series did not outperform operational content as expected, prompting a focus on targeted promotion and engagement tactics.\n- TikTok integration was discussed as a possible future channel for short clips, with the team agreeing to prepare vertical video formats to accommodate this (25:57).\n\n## **Branding, Visual Identity, and Design Feedback**\n\nThe Payments on Tap brand will retain **gray and green colors and the arrow element from the original logo** to maintain connection to the niche brand, but explore **variations in color schemes and backgrounds** for clearer differentiation (29:37).\n\n- Igor and Meg agreed to experiment with **inverted color schemes (black on white or white on black)** to reduce similarity with Wrestling Payments.\n- Meg emphasized the importance of a **friendly yet executive tone** with branding that feels inviting but professional.\n- The team favors adding **brewery-related sound effects** and thematic elements without casual or bar-like distractions to tie into the live event atmosphere.\n- Design preferences include **quote cards with quotation marks at the start**, large clean images with faces, and more emphasis on bubbles or tap imagery instead of arrows to create visual variety.\n- Meg and Carlos requested the design team avoid overused arrow motifs and instead **incorporate unique imagery that aligns with the Payments on Tap identity**.\n- Navy blue was identified as a promising accent color to complement or replace dull gray and green tones, with enthusiasm from all stakeholders for testing this option (33:46).\n\n## **Operational and Scheduling Considerations**\n\nThe team plans to **pause meetings during the upcoming holiday period** and schedule a **separate session early next year to review Payments on Tap designs and materials** to maintain momentum (36:19).\n\n- Alyssa is expected to have at least one episode ready to launch around January, supporting a timely rollout.\n- Baylee offered to coordinate calendar invites and suggested including Alyssa in future discussions depending on availability.\n- Meg confirmed ongoing communication about billing and invoices to ensure administrative clarity before year-end.\n- The established workflow for content submission and review will continue, with potential additions for social media content approval to align branding and promotion efforts.\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Analytics","Payments on Tap","Wrestling Payments","Podcast Branding","Social Media Strategy","Financial Services Podcasts"],"overview":"- **Podcast Performance:** Wrestling Payments launched 27 episodes in 2025, achieving 2,168 downloads, averaging 80 per episode.  \n- **Listener Demographics:** 85% of listeners are from North America, primarily using iPhone via Apple Podcasts and Spotify.  \n- **Social Media Growth:** Social media generated 22 new followers, with engagement up 10% year-over-year, totaling 14,300 views.  \n- **New Podcast Launch:** Payments on Tap will focus on executives, providing industry insights amid market changes, with LinkedIn as a key distribution channel.  \n- **Branding Strategy:** Payments on Tap will keep key design elements but explore new colors and unique imagery for better differentiation.  \n- **Operational Planning:** Meetings paused for holidays; session scheduled early next year to review Payments on Tap designs and ensure workflow continuity.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nInform editing team to be more thorough in removing repeated take mistakes in upcoming podcast episodes (03:30)\nIncorporate brewery-themed subtle sound elements into Payments on Tap podcast intro (22:40)\nObtain high-resolution headshot of Alyssa from LinkedIn or request directly (23:25)\nExperiment with alternate logo color schemes including black/white and navy blue variations to distinguish Payments on Tap branding (29:45)\nPrepare social media post guidelines to align with podcast review process (20:10)\nSend calendar invite for a follow-up meeting after holidays to review podcast design concepts (36:15)\n\n**Meg Norlund - NEACH**\nShare Alyssa’s new podcast episode opening clip for review (21:15)\nProvide headshot image of Alyssa if available (23:30)\nReview and provide feedback on payments podcast work order and invoice receipt inquiry (37:05)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nSend graphics and video source files for client portal and asset templates requested by NEACH (05:50)\nProvide detailed 2025 podcast analytics report and Good Pods podcast listing link (09:45)\nCollaborate with design team on logo adjustments, especially regarding arrow/banner element and color tuning (29:30)\n\n**Carlos**\nProvide design input on logos and social media graphics focusing on distinctive imagery apart from arrows (27:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"752ce011-fa16-4304-9fc0-203221afa388","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
