    '{"id":"01KCQ0DBXVMMMKDK37FFGNMNFN","title":"KTC // MiD: Riverside Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Scheduling**\n\nThe team established a clear process for content creation using a new studio platform to streamline recording and publishing.  \n\n- **Colin Costigan** detailed the studio setup where users create studios for each recording and can plan interviews up to a week ahead, integrating calendar invites directly (04:22).  \n    - This platform records hosts and guests separately, improving audio quality and reducing latency.  \n    - Typical output includes a full episode, several short videos, an MP3, quote cards, and show notes for syndication on platforms like Spotify, Apple, YouTube, and the website.  \n    - The team can adjust distribution channels as needed depending on content or audience.  \n    - This system aims to increase production efficiency and content reach with minimal manual coordination.  \n\n- A **content calendar** will be created as a living Notion document, allowing real-time updates and collaboration between teams (05:44).  \n    - Colin promised to deliver the initial calendar draft by next week for review.  \n    - Kristen emphasized getting the first month''s content on Michael’s calendar to maintain momentum amid his many demands (07:17).  \n    - This approach ensures alignment on publishing goals and deadlines early in the year, supporting consistent output.  \n\n## **Branding and Visual Identity**\n\nThe team is refining logos to better match the client’s brand color palette, focusing on deeper green tones for stronger alignment.  \n\n- Kristen relayed Michael’s feedback requesting more use of darker greens rather than lighter shades in the logos, especially in key branding areas (10:03).  \n    - Guille demonstrated updated logo versions with greener gradients and variations using the KTC portion and middle triangle.  \n    - Colin confirmed the design team is incorporating these darker green versions to meet client preferences (11:37).  \n    - Finalized logo options with adjusted hex colors are expected next week for review.  \n\n- Kristen offered to obtain exact hex codes from her creative director to help the team match colors precisely (08:45).  \n    - The team agreed this would streamline the design process and reduce back-and-forth corrections.  \n    - She also committed to facilitating communication with Michael to avoid delays due to his heavy workload (12:26).  \n\n## **Project Management and Collaboration Tools**\n\nA centralized client portal is in place to track all project elements, improving transparency and accountability.  \n\n- Colin explained the portal houses project goals, pending items, upcoming tasks, and completed deliverables with direct links to final assets (12:41).  \n    - The portal supports filtering by date and status, allowing both teams to monitor progress efficiently.  \n    - This setup minimizes confusion by clearly showing who is responsible for what and what is outstanding.  \n    - An invite to the portal will be sent to Kristen to integrate her fully into project tracking.  \n\n- This tool helps reduce status update meetings and manual follow-ups, speeding up issue resolution and delivery.  \n\n## **Team Coordination and Resource Allocation**\n\nNew hires and busy schedules require careful planning to keep projects on track without overloading key stakeholders.  \n\n- Kristen shared that a new hire recently started on her team, which may increase capacity and requires proper onboarding and coordination (02:10).  \n    - She expressed intent to organize content and meetings to avoid overloading Michael, who manages multiple urgent priorities (07:36).  \n    - Colin acknowledged the challenge and committed to managing timelines and dependencies thoughtfully.  \n\n- Clear role definitions and shared calendars are crucial to maintain momentum and avoid bottlenecks as the team scales content production and branding work.","outline":null,"keywords":["Riverside","Content Calendar","Logo Colors","Recording Setup","Client Portal","Podcast Production"],"overview":"- **Content Creation Process:** New studio platform improves recording, publishing, and efficiency, allowing planning interviews a week ahead.  \n- **Content Calendar:** A living Notion document will help teams collaborate on content, with initial draft due next week.  \n- **Branding Adjustments:** Logos refined to incorporate darker green tones, with finalized options expected for review next week.  \n- **Client Portal:** Centralized portal tracks project goals and tasks, enhancing transparency and reducing need for status updates.  \n- **Resource Management:** New hire will increase capacity; proper onboarding and planning are essential for avoiding project delays.  \n- **Role Definitions:** Clear roles and shared calendars are vital for maintaining project momentum and preventing bottlenecks.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare Riverside login credentials with Kristen Baller in the Zoom chat and by follow-up (06:12)\nFinalize and send over the new logo versions with darker green tones that align with Richie Mae’s colors (12:17)\nPrepare and deliver the interactive content calendar for Q1 next week (07:36)\nShare client portal invite and access details with Kristen Baller (12:38)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nProvide hex color codes for darker green shades from the Richie Mae creative director to Colin and Guille (12:23)\nAssist in obtaining any additional approvals or materials from Michael as needed to avoid delays related to his busy schedule (12:30)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nReview and possibly send over finalized hex color details for the logo next week or during the upcoming meeting (09:34)\n"},"duration":13.630000114440918,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":2,"name":"Kristen Baller"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":0.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, just another meeting.","index":1,"end_time":31.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.69,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":2,"end_time":32.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re getting tired of seeing me already.","index":3,"end_time":34.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you out next week?","index":4,"end_time":39.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Nope.","index":5,"end_time":40.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I imagine it''ll be a little slower.","index":6,"end_time":50.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hope so.","index":7,"end_time":52.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.62,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I can catch up on things.","index":8,"end_time":56.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should have just put all my plan documents for next week.","index":9,"end_time":62.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":64.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, she''s here.","index":11,"end_time":85.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":12,"end_time":98.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.19,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Hey.","index":13,"end_time":99.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":14,"end_time":100.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":15,"end_time":100.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.51,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Why is this not.","index":16,"end_time":102.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Do you mind if I hop off and hop back?","index":17,"end_time":107.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":105.81,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Oh, okay, I''m here.","index":18,"end_time":109.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.33,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"All right.","index":19,"end_time":109.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.49,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"There you go.","index":20,"end_time":110.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the beauty of.","index":21,"end_time":114.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.49,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''m working out of Microsoft Teams and Zoom and Google right now, and so sometimes I think maybe one still shutting down while others opening has.","index":22,"end_time":125.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":114.61,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yep, totally get it.","index":23,"end_time":127.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going so far?","index":24,"end_time":129.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So far so good.","index":25,"end_time":131.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.06,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I have a new hire who started, so.","index":26,"end_time":135.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":133.34,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":27,"end_time":136.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":28,"end_time":137.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.1,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Great.","index":29,"end_time":138.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you had any specific questions to go through, but I was going to walk through, just.","index":30,"end_time":142.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll give you your login so you can copy and paste that into your notes and save that and then just walk through, like creating a studio.","index":31,"end_time":150.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":32,"end_time":152.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.42,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I''ll share your login credentials, but once you log in, this is what you''ll come to as a screen.","index":33,"end_time":159.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so the series is the Executive Advantage series.","index":34,"end_time":162.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll update the logo with the new KTC Search logo that we made.","index":35,"end_time":168.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But essentially when you come in here, you''ll just see there''s no active studios yet.","index":36,"end_time":173.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what you''ll do is create a studio for any new recording that you''re doing.","index":37,"end_time":177.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like Michael mentioned maybe talking to someone tomorrow that I think was like a recent hire that he''s placed and.","index":38,"end_time":187.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe having conversation around that or testimonials.","index":39,"end_time":190.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can record any content in here, really.","index":40,"end_time":192.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":41,"end_time":193.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.51,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So you just come in, create a studio, name it, you know, whoever you''re talking to.","index":42,"end_time":198.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can just call this Test one and then pretty much just hit Create.","index":43,"end_time":203.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you are like ahead of schedule, then you can hit like plan.","index":44,"end_time":210.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you wanted to, for example, invite them to an interview a week from now, you could just hit Plan and then it''ll give you some links.","index":45,"end_time":217.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can name it, set what time you want it, and then you can invite people directly here just by adding their email address and it''ll pop up on their calendar.","index":46,"end_time":224.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":47,"end_time":227.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.11,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then basically when you go in, and we can also send you a video that walks through this, but you''ll just go in and hit record and it''ll pop up and just ask you about the tools that you''re using.","index":48,"end_time":241.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not going to hit anything because it''ll stop you from being able to hear me on this Zoom call.","index":49,"end_time":245.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''ll pull up your camera, you''ll select that you''re the host, and you''ll put in your name whether or not you''re using headphones, and it''ll allow access, and the guest will go through a similar login.","index":50,"end_time":257.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then essentially, it''s just like working on Zoom.","index":51,"end_time":259.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you said you''ve worked in Riverside before, so I''m sure you''re familiar.","index":52,"end_time":262.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can''t remember.","index":53,"end_time":264.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.49,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Does Riverside pick up better with headphones or not?","index":54,"end_time":268.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.24,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, we recommend headphones, so I joined a lot of our podcasts as well.","index":55,"end_time":274.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like wearing headphones.","index":56,"end_time":278.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t always wear these big ones.","index":57,"end_time":280.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I might use, like, earbuds.","index":58,"end_time":282.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I also have a microphone, which I don''t know if my camera is going to pick up, but I have this microphone down here.","index":59,"end_time":288.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not all of it is absolutely necessary.","index":60,"end_time":291.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just helps with sound quality.","index":61,"end_time":293.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":294.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.83,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Because there''s one platform.","index":63,"end_time":295.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.19,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I can''t remember what it was, but I.","index":64,"end_time":296.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":295.27,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"If I.","index":65,"end_time":297.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.95,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"If I didn''t have headphones on, it would pick up like an echo.","index":66,"end_time":301.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.47,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, Riverside is better.","index":67,"end_time":302.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it actually records you both separately, which is really cool.","index":68,"end_time":306.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it doesn''t have any latency or anything like that.","index":69,"end_time":308.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have MP4s of both of you, and that''s what we download and extract to basically create a bunch of assets.","index":70,"end_time":315.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so our typical package out of this is like three or four short videos out of the long conversation, the actual full episode, a full MP3, and then a few quote cards as well, and then a whole document of, like, show notes, and it''ll be up to you guys whether we want to syndicate that.","index":71,"end_time":332.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We typically, channel wise, do Spotify, Apple, the website, and YouTube.","index":72,"end_time":338.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if there''s anything else or anything out of that list you don''t want to do, we can obviously make that decision.","index":73,"end_time":343.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":344.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.47,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":75,"end_time":346.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.87,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then you guys mentioned you''re creating a content calendar.","index":76,"end_time":350.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.47,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yes.","index":77,"end_time":351.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll be creating a content calendar based on our conversation with Michael the other and you joining the other day.","index":78,"end_time":357.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''ll send that over.","index":79,"end_time":360.389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''ll be a notion document.","index":80,"end_time":362.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.389,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that way it''s interactive.","index":81,"end_time":363.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can both go in and edit.","index":82,"end_time":364.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you say, like, hey, I got this person that I talked to and they want to join, you can just add it right there.","index":83,"end_time":369.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":84,"end_time":371.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.56,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":85,"end_time":372.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I will send the credentials into the Zoom chat right now.","index":86,"end_time":376.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":87,"end_time":378.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.6,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":88,"end_time":396,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And it doesn''t look like the username or is that Accounts plus the.","index":89,"end_time":400.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.08,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"It''s Accounts plus the.","index":90,"end_time":401.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that whole thing in blue okay.","index":91,"end_time":405.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s just because we.","index":92,"end_time":409.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a relationship with Riverside, so we''re able to get you guys a discount, so you''re just under our account.","index":93,"end_time":413.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":94,"end_time":416.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.1,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then what?","index":95,"end_time":422.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":421.22,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Michael used this too?","index":96,"end_time":423.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.02,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"If he were Trevor Login.","index":97,"end_time":425.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":423.06,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":98,"end_time":427.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.8,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"How long have you guys been.","index":99,"end_time":429.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":428.44,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Actually.","index":100,"end_time":429.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Recent kickoff for this engagement.","index":101,"end_time":432.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually kicked off, like at the beginning of this month.","index":102,"end_time":434.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":103,"end_time":437,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So then my next question.","index":104,"end_time":439.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":437.96,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So for the content calendar, what''s like the timeline of kind of trying to finalize that.","index":105,"end_time":449.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.28,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So we''re going into the new year knowing what we''re.","index":106,"end_time":452.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.48,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"What we''re trying to achieve and when we''re trying to achieve it by.","index":107,"end_time":456.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.81,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll have that ready next week to review in our meeting and we''ll plan out as far as we can, but obviously it''ll be a living document.","index":108,"end_time":465.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of course it will.","index":109,"end_time":468.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.13,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I just.","index":110,"end_time":469.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.93,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"The first.","index":111,"end_time":470.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.41,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"The first few.","index":112,"end_time":472.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.33,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I asked.","index":113,"end_time":473.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.45,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Michael runs a million miles an hour.","index":114,"end_time":475.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":473.25,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''m sure you''ve all like, he.","index":115,"end_time":478.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.21,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I don''t know how he.","index":116,"end_time":479.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.53,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"How he does it.","index":117,"end_time":481.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.13,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So I try to get everything at least on his calendar.","index":118,"end_time":485.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.83,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So if you''ve got the content, I want to at least get it on his calendar, even if it''s for like the first month or Q1, so that I can keep him moving with the project so he doesn''t get distracted by anything else.","index":119,"end_time":500.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.63,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Because he''s got a lot of.","index":120,"end_time":502.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Of asks coming through, I''m sure.","index":121,"end_time":505.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.39,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yes.","index":122,"end_time":505.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys get at your.","index":123,"end_time":507.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.95,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"You know, he''s wanting us to mirror some of the, like the logos with exact.","index":124,"end_time":511.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.59,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"With Richie Mae for that.","index":125,"end_time":514.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.95,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So the other question I had for you outside of the Riverside was the logos that came in.","index":126,"end_time":520.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.63,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"They look good, but we probably need to match the Richie May colors.","index":127,"end_time":525.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.35,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re working on that right now.","index":128,"end_time":527.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did I not mention that in my email?","index":129,"end_time":528.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You may have.","index":130,"end_time":530.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I just want to open the zip file because my Michael was asking.","index":131,"end_time":534.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.27,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"There was a long story.","index":132,"end_time":537.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.56,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So what can I do to help, though?","index":133,"end_time":541.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.68,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So would it.","index":134,"end_time":542.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.4,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Instead of you trying to act like.","index":135,"end_time":544.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.32,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Trying to match it, should I ask for, like, the color.","index":136,"end_time":547.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.12,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"The color numbers from my creative director.","index":137,"end_time":551.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.48,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Is there things that I could help in giving.","index":138,"end_time":554.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":551.4,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Giving you in the team that would allow you to match the colors a little bit more easily?","index":139,"end_time":560.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.28,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, if you want to ask them for the hex values, that''s fine.","index":140,"end_time":564.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re just.","index":141,"end_time":564.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re extracting it straight from their logo to match.","index":142,"end_time":568.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So our team''s actually working on that right now.","index":143,"end_time":570.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll have those.","index":144,"end_time":571.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think.","index":145,"end_time":572.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yay.","index":146,"end_time":572.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those will be ready next week, I think.","index":147,"end_time":573.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":148,"end_time":574.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re ready.","index":149,"end_time":575.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.42,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Maybe we can send them over or we can go over them on our meeting next week.","index":150,"end_time":581.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.78,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, look at them right now.","index":151,"end_time":584.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":581.94,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":585.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.38,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Are they the ones that you sent in the.","index":153,"end_time":588.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.34,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"No, they''re very similar.","index":154,"end_time":590.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.63,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They''re just like, more green.","index":155,"end_time":592.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.95,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Let me.","index":156,"end_time":594.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.75,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":157,"end_time":594.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.39,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Because I was gonna say the feedback Michael had given me today on the logos was there wasn''t enough green.","index":158,"end_time":600.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.71,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So you may have.","index":159,"end_time":601.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.87,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":160,"end_time":605.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.91,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":161,"end_time":607.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.67,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So it''s pretty much same logo but more green.","index":162,"end_time":613.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":607.99,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And we use the hex colors.","index":163,"end_time":615.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.48,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It used to be just blue.","index":164,"end_time":619.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":617.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":620.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.32,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":166,"end_time":622.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.96,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s pretty.","index":167,"end_time":626.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.44,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We may ask for more green.","index":168,"end_time":629.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.32,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":169,"end_time":631.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you look at the Richie.","index":170,"end_time":633.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":631.68,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"May, we even have a few versions of these.","index":171,"end_time":636.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":172,"end_time":639.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638.24,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"See if I can''t show you.","index":173,"end_time":640.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":639.61,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"All right.","index":174,"end_time":651.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.81,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And when I say he may ask for more green.","index":175,"end_time":654.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.29,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So you know how you have like the lighter green into the darker.","index":176,"end_time":656.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.41,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"He''s looking for more of the darker scale.","index":177,"end_time":659.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":656.97,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":178,"end_time":660.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, for example, I''ll just share my screen so you can see it.","index":179,"end_time":665.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":661.37,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"This is just a job description that I''m doing right here.","index":180,"end_time":674.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.78,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"See how this logo, they don''t like, and a lot of the logos, they really just go the hard blue in.","index":181,"end_time":680.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":674.5,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"In the green.","index":182,"end_time":681.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":680.74,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And so they typically, while in some of their logos, they have more of the, like, of that flow he''s going to look for, they don''t really leverage any of the lighter greens.","index":183,"end_time":692.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.86,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":184,"end_time":693.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good to know.","index":185,"end_time":697.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you had asked me that.","index":186,"end_time":699.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":697.56,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I passed that on.","index":187,"end_time":703.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.6,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":188,"end_time":705.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":189,"end_time":706.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we actually did mock up a few different versions with how we use the green.","index":190,"end_time":711,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like here is one with using it.","index":191,"end_time":714.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The gradient.","index":192,"end_time":715.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then this was playing a little bit more with actually using it in the KTC portion, then using the middle triangle on this version and then kind of a similar approach on this one.","index":193,"end_time":731.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":715.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we can definitely get in a darker green.","index":194,"end_time":735.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":195,"end_time":736.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.23,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And send that version over as well.","index":196,"end_time":739.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":197,"end_time":740.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.67,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":198,"end_time":741.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you could send us a hex.","index":199,"end_time":744.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The hex code.","index":200,"end_time":745.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.95,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The hex code.","index":201,"end_time":746.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":202,"end_time":747.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.59,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":748.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.91,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then if you need anything between now and then and it''s dependent on Michael and you''re not getting it, just ping me and I''ll.","index":204,"end_time":755.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.63,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":205,"end_time":755.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.15,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''ll get it over to you.","index":206,"end_time":757.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.91,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":207,"end_time":758.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s got so much on this plate.","index":208,"end_time":760.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.15,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So.","index":209,"end_time":760.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.51,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":761.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also one thing I''ll show you and we can send you an invite to this, but we do have a client portal and this has everything that we''re working on, everything we''ve ever worked on is all in here.","index":211,"end_time":770.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can send you an invite over to it.","index":212,"end_time":772.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But just as a quick overview.","index":213,"end_time":775.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll have our goals up here.","index":214,"end_time":776.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get those added.","index":215,"end_time":777.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything that we''re waiting on you for ever.","index":216,"end_time":779.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then what''s coming up and what''s also been completed.","index":217,"end_time":784.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have a few tabs over here you can filter by date that''ll show you anything we''re working on or deliverables.","index":218,"end_time":791.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And at any point when we''re like, okay, cool, this part of the project is wrapped up, that will live under final deliverables with a link to whatever document or asset or webpage or anything like that.","index":219,"end_time":801.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":220,"end_time":801.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":221,"end_time":802.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.03,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":222,"end_time":804.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":223,"end_time":806.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":224,"end_time":806.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":806.11,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":225,"end_time":807.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that''s it.","index":226,"end_time":808.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.39,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":227,"end_time":809.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":228,"end_time":809.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, thank you very much and we will see you next week.","index":229,"end_time":811.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":230,"end_time":812.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.71,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Talk soon.","index":231,"end_time":812.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":812.07,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"}],"dateString":"2025-12-18T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82606927411?pwd=ZbGbOaDb6bVHj6SGPqPqUT0Aeb0E0T.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KCQ0DBXVMMMKDK37FFGNMNFN","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Walked Kristen through Riverside setup, content creation, and planning tools for future recordings.","Confirmed next week delivery of content calendar; Kristen emphasized early Q1 planning for Michael.","Discussed logo revisions to align with Richie May brand; darker green variants shown and approved.","Granted Kristen access to shared client portal for deliverables, timelines, and collaboration tracking.","Agreed on media output formats and syndication channels including Spotify, YouTube, and internal site."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''ll be creating a content calendar...we''ll send that over.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"He''s looking for more of the darker scale.","speaker":"Kristen Baller"},{"quote":"We actually did mock up a few different versions with how we use the green.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","branding","planning","tools"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-18T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Scheduling**\n\nThe team established a clear process for content creation using a new studio platform to streamline recording and publishing.  \n\n- **Colin Costigan** detailed the studio setup where users create studios for each recording and can plan interviews up to a week ahead, integrating calendar invites directly (04:22).  \n    - This platform records hosts and guests separately, improving audio quality and reducing latency.  \n    - Typical output includes a full episode, several short videos, an MP3, quote cards, and show notes for syndication on platforms like Spotify, Apple, YouTube, and the website.  \n    - The team can adjust distribution channels as needed depending on content or audience.  \n    - This system aims to increase production efficiency and content reach with minimal manual coordination.  \n\n- A **content calendar** will be created as a living Notion document, allowing real-time updates and collaboration between teams (05:44).  \n    - Colin promised to deliver the initial calendar draft by next week for review.  \n    - Kristen emphasized getting the first month''s content on Michael’s calendar to maintain momentum amid his many demands (07:17).  \n    - This approach ensures alignment on publishing goals and deadlines early in the year, supporting consistent output.  \n\n## **Branding and Visual Identity**\n\nThe team is refining logos to better match the client’s brand color palette, focusing on deeper green tones for stronger alignment.  \n\n- Kristen relayed Michael’s feedback requesting more use of darker greens rather than lighter shades in the logos, especially in key branding areas (10:03).  \n    - Guille demonstrated updated logo versions with greener gradients and variations using the KTC portion and middle triangle.  \n    - Colin confirmed the design team is incorporating these darker green versions to meet client preferences (11:37).  \n    - Finalized logo options with adjusted hex colors are expected next week for review.  \n\n- Kristen offered to obtain exact hex codes from her creative director to help the team match colors precisely (08:45).  \n    - The team agreed this would streamline the design process and reduce back-and-forth corrections.  \n    - She also committed to facilitating communication with Michael to avoid delays due to his heavy workload (12:26).  \n\n## **Project Management and Collaboration Tools**\n\nA centralized client portal is in place to track all project elements, improving transparency and accountability.  \n\n- Colin explained the portal houses project goals, pending items, upcoming tasks, and completed deliverables with direct links to final assets (12:41).  \n    - The portal supports filtering by date and status, allowing both teams to monitor progress efficiently.  \n    - This setup minimizes confusion by clearly showing who is responsible for what and what is outstanding.  \n    - An invite to the portal will be sent to Kristen to integrate her fully into project tracking.  \n\n- This tool helps reduce status update meetings and manual follow-ups, speeding up issue resolution and delivery.  \n\n## **Team Coordination and Resource Allocation**\n\nNew hires and busy schedules require careful planning to keep projects on track without overloading key stakeholders.  \n\n- Kristen shared that a new hire recently started on her team, which may increase capacity and requires proper onboarding and coordination (02:10).  \n    - She expressed intent to organize content and meetings to avoid overloading Michael, who manages multiple urgent priorities (07:36).  \n    - Colin acknowledged the challenge and committed to managing timelines and dependencies thoughtfully.  \n\n- Clear role definitions and shared calendars are crucial to maintain momentum and avoid bottlenecks as the team scales content production and branding work.","outline":null,"keywords":["Riverside","Content Calendar","Logo Colors","Recording Setup","Client Portal","Podcast Production"],"overview":"- **Content Creation Process:** New studio platform improves recording, publishing, and efficiency, allowing planning interviews a week ahead.  \n- **Content Calendar:** A living Notion document will help teams collaborate on content, with initial draft due next week.  \n- **Branding Adjustments:** Logos refined to incorporate darker green tones, with finalized options expected for review next week.  \n- **Client Portal:** Centralized portal tracks project goals and tasks, enhancing transparency and reducing need for status updates.  \n- **Resource Management:** New hire will increase capacity; proper onboarding and planning are essential for avoiding project delays.  \n- **Role Definitions:** Clear roles and shared calendars are vital for maintaining project momentum and preventing bottlenecks.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare Riverside login credentials with Kristen Baller in the Zoom chat and by follow-up (06:12)\nFinalize and send over the new logo versions with darker green tones that align with Richie Mae’s colors (12:17)\nPrepare and deliver the interactive content calendar for Q1 next week (07:36)\nShare client portal invite and access details with Kristen Baller (12:38)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nProvide hex color codes for darker green shades from the Richie Mae creative director to Colin and Guille (12:23)\nAssist in obtaining any additional approvals or materials from Michael as needed to avoid delays related to his busy schedule (12:30)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nReview and possibly send over finalized hex color details for the logo next week or during the upcoming meeting (09:34)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"e06fe679-16ba-4b10-a02a-ec5b04ead20b","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
