.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If I see 777, I think angel numbers, so.","index":345,"end_time":1254.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which is actually impressive to see because.","index":346,"end_time":1256.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1254.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of the time of year people are typically less engaged and surfing less and browsing Amazon more.","index":347,"end_time":1264.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the fact that that number stayed consistent is actually almost can be viewed as an improvement.","index":348,"end_time":1270.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But YouTube podcast views did take a significant jump.","index":349,"end_time":1273.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not a massive number, but comparatively 55% increase.","index":350,"end_time":1277.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1273.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s bulbul because I was looking at her engagement on stuff and she really has quite the fan club and it was very.","index":351,"end_time":1285.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s a big brand.","index":352,"end_time":1286.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1285.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we need to Definitely.","index":353,"end_time":1288.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Outreach.","index":354,"end_time":1288.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":355,"end_time":1290.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It already has me thinking for the.","index":356,"end_time":1292.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1290.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Next podcast, I''m like, I feel like I need to email the Next person and say, if you want to promote, here''s what to do.","index":357,"end_time":1297.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.15,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because it worked.","index":358,"end_time":1298.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.47,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So.","index":359,"end_time":1298.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s a great, it''s a great point because we, you know, I, I give them the heads up but we don''t like spoon feed them how to promote.","index":360,"end_time":1311.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1299.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m thinking maybe we should start doing that.","index":361,"end_time":1313.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We figure out an easy way to do it.","index":362,"end_time":1315.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, that might be something to include in future frameworks.","index":363,"end_time":1318.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1315.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, like you''ll get.","index":364,"end_time":1319.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1318.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys want to share.","index":365,"end_time":1320.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1319.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what your production process is going to be, but let''s just save for sake of argument that it''s the same assets you''re getting that we''re producing.","index":366,"end_time":1327.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1320.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You could be like, hey, you''re gonna have quote cards and a short video that you can promote on your channel.","index":367,"end_time":1333.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1327.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re gonna tag you, we ask that you tag us.","index":368,"end_time":1335.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1333.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of just give them like expectations.","index":369,"end_time":1337.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1335.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a good idea.","index":370,"end_time":1340.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.25,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be, that would be a great way to do it.","index":371,"end_time":1341.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then yeah know afterward when we thank them, you know, we can just resend it just to have a top of mind.","index":372,"end_time":1347.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1341.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I like, I like that idea as it being like a one stop shopping place that we can put it.","index":373,"end_time":1354.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":374,"end_time":1356.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":375,"end_time":1357.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1357.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1357.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know the Riverside conversation is evolving.","index":377,"end_time":1360.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1357.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with setting that up, I mean, Rachel, I think you''ve downloaded every episode out of Pulse.","index":378,"end_time":1365.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1360.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But Pulse will be live until the end of the month as well.","index":379,"end_time":1368.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you need to download anything else.","index":380,"end_time":1369.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1368.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All the final deliverables for everything that we''ve done this year are in there.","index":381,"end_time":1373.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1369.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":382,"end_time":1374.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And when do we have Riverside access.","index":383,"end_time":1375.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1374.01,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Until that''ll sunset on the 31st as well.","index":384,"end_time":1379.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":385,"end_time":1380.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":386,"end_time":1381.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just good to know.","index":387,"end_time":1382.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But I do have off of the other.","index":388,"end_time":1384.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But sometimes it''s just good to have like the plain stuff too.","index":389,"end_time":1386.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1387.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1386.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll be sending an email with these dates and everything too.","index":391,"end_time":1389.569,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1387.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll detail like points purchased all.","index":392,"end_time":1392.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1390.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way through to like when the last day to request any work and.","index":393,"end_time":1396.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1392.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When Pulse shuts down, things like that.","index":394,"end_time":1398.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1396.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you, Colin.","index":395,"end_time":1399.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":396,"end_time":1400.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s everything that we had in the deck.","index":397,"end_time":1404.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you wanted to dedicate any time to any questions around what we''re.","index":398,"end_time":1408.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1404.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Talking about Friday, that would be fine.","index":399,"end_time":1410.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1408.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Tiffany and Raki have had a few questions or they just had.","index":400,"end_time":1414.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1410.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually one question on like receipts that came through on the first that they.","index":401,"end_time":1418.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were trying to count in November.","index":402,"end_time":1419.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1418.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we sent that over to them.","index":403,"end_time":1420.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1419.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I haven''t seen anything else come through.","index":404,"end_time":1422.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the biggest thing is Just our sorting out what we want to do from a platform standpoint.","index":405,"end_time":1428.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1423.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think with Riverside, I don''t know if you guys know this, but because I know for sure we''re going to want that one is when we looked at it ourselves, they have sort of like their.","index":406,"end_time":1441.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1430.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Their basic.","index":407,"end_time":1442.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1441.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''re elevated, whatever.","index":408,"end_time":1443.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1442.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then they have their, like, Business Premium.","index":409,"end_time":1447.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1443.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And.","index":410,"end_time":1448.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1448.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And based upon their site, they ask for.","index":411,"end_time":1451.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1448.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, tell me if I get this wrong, but they ask for like a.","index":412,"end_time":1455.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A call to like, figure out what you want is like, do you know, like, are you able to share with us, like, what features we have turned on and what we don''t.","index":413,"end_time":1469,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":414,"end_time":1469.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1469,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I just don''t want to start from scratch.","index":415,"end_time":1471.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1469.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, the way we have it is the way we want it.","index":416,"end_time":1473.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1471.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":417,"end_time":1474.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1474.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they don''t, like.","index":418,"end_time":1476.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They don''t promote it that way.","index":419,"end_time":1478.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1476.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":420,"end_time":1478.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1478.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So your guys can''t.","index":421,"end_time":1479.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1478.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So every account that we set up.","index":422,"end_time":1480.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1479.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For any client is on Business Premium.","index":423,"end_time":1482.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s any feature that they come out with also, like, early access to.","index":424,"end_time":1487.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1483.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"AI features and things like that.","index":425,"end_time":1489.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so it is.","index":426,"end_time":1491.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1490.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It is Business Premium.","index":427,"end_time":1493.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1492.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so it''s basically like any.","index":428,"end_time":1495.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Any feature that they have you get access to.","index":429,"end_time":1497.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1495.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":430,"end_time":1498.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1498.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":431,"end_time":1499.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1498.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right, well, that answers it, I think.","index":432,"end_time":1501.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1499.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":433,"end_time":1501.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":434,"end_time":1502.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And we were able to get you.","index":435,"end_time":1503.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1502.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys that discount as well because we have over 50 accounts on there.","index":436,"end_time":1507.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1503.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Huh?","index":437,"end_time":1508.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1508.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":438,"end_time":1509.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1508.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so do they.","index":439,"end_time":1510.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1509.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do they do any kind of like a discount if you pay the annual fee all at once?","index":440,"end_time":1517.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1513.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I believe they do.","index":441,"end_time":1519.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1519.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Most.","index":443,"end_time":1520.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Most places do that.","index":444,"end_time":1521.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, that''s helpful.","index":445,"end_time":1523.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1522.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, No, I think.","index":446,"end_time":1525.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that''s it.","index":447,"end_time":1526,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think the rest of it we should just understand better with Tiffany in the conversation.","index":448,"end_time":1530.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1526,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":449,"end_time":1532.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1531.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want to make you guys retread.","index":450,"end_time":1533.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1532.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I couldn''t get her.","index":451,"end_time":1534.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I couldn''t get us all aligned.","index":452,"end_time":1536.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1534.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I did want to give us a minute on just figuring out what we wanted to do with AI campaign.","index":453,"end_time":1540.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1536.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So let''s let it roll.","index":454,"end_time":1541.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1540.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, turn it on today and let''s just see what we got.","index":455,"end_time":1546.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1541.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep, sounds good.","index":456,"end_time":1548.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1546.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":457,"end_time":1550.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1549.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I did want to share with you that I have a call with Waymo.","index":458,"end_time":1554.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1550.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Third call tomorrow.","index":459,"end_time":1556.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1555.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, not tomorrow.","index":460,"end_time":1558.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1557.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Friday.","index":461,"end_time":1559.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''ll.","index":462,"end_time":1561.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1561.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''ll keep you up to speed.","index":463,"end_time":1562.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1561.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think there''s real work there.","index":464,"end_time":1564.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1562.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":465,"end_time":1565.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1564.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was trying to find the reaction.","index":466,"end_time":1566.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1565.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The party.","index":467,"end_time":1568.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1567.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":468,"end_time":1568.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1568.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":469,"end_time":1569.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1568.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that is amazing.","index":470,"end_time":1570.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So happy to hear that.","index":471,"end_time":1571.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":472,"end_time":1572.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s a super interesting brand and from.","index":473,"end_time":1577.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Anything, from everything I''ve seen, it is.","index":474,"end_time":1579.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1577.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just poised for insane growth.","index":475,"end_time":1581.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":476,"end_time":1583.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1582.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t think something like this, they''re.","index":477,"end_time":1584.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1583.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going to have to proactively manage their brand.","index":478,"end_time":1586.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1584.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like they, you know, people have differing feelings about driverless vehicles.","index":479,"end_time":1594.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1586.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":480,"end_time":1595.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1594.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they get a lot of weird press and Elon, Elon really doesn''t want them to succeed.","index":481,"end_time":1605.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1596.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":482,"end_time":1606.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1605.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, he''s doing a lot of stuff in social.","index":483,"end_time":1608.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I just think brand reputation is going to be really important over time.","index":484,"end_time":1613.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1609.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I haven''t yet like delved on, you know, what is your priority?","index":485,"end_time":1618.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1613.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, like what''s the plan?","index":486,"end_time":1619.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1618.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":487,"end_time":1620.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1620.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I saw their CEO quoted recently and I was like, ooh.","index":488,"end_time":1626.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1620.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, like, I really, I don''t know.","index":489,"end_time":1629.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1626.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think they need to up their game.","index":490,"end_time":1630.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In my humble opinion in that area, that''s not us.","index":491,"end_time":1632.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1630.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, I agree with you.","index":492,"end_time":1636.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It almost seems like they''re almost not.","index":493,"end_time":1641.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1637.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Picturing really how crazy it could get.","index":494,"end_time":1643.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1641.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":495,"end_time":1647.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1644.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And look, they''re a tech company so it''s a lot of like, you know, we''re gonna break some things.","index":496,"end_time":1654.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":497,"end_time":1655.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, but I think regulatory wise they really gotta watch it.","index":498,"end_time":1660.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1656.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":499,"end_time":1662.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean even look at massive tech companies like Palantir and they have their slip ups, but, you know.","index":500,"end_time":1666.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":501,"end_time":1668.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1666.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To say the least.","index":502,"end_time":1668.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1668.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":503,"end_time":1668.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1668.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Julius?","index":504,"end_time":1669.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1668.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They do pride themselves on being aggressive and they have done test markets and the test markets have gone well.","index":505,"end_time":1675.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1670.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I think they''re just like, let''s go.","index":506,"end_time":1677.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1675.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":507,"end_time":1678.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, but not every market''s the same and scaling is hard and.","index":508,"end_time":1682.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":509,"end_time":1684.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s coming in at an interesting time.","index":510,"end_time":1685.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1684.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, you know, not to get ahead of myself, but like, are they a logo we''re going to automatically want to put into our credentials?","index":511,"end_time":1692.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1685.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We might wait.","index":512,"end_time":1693.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":513,"end_time":1694.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tbd.","index":514,"end_time":1694.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1694.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":515,"end_time":1695.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We might wait.","index":516,"end_time":1696.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Not as easy as if Nike was okay with it.","index":517,"end_time":1699.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":518,"end_time":1700.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Exactly, Exactly.","index":519,"end_time":1701.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1700.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, really appreciate you guys taking the time today.","index":520,"end_time":1704.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Looking forward to seeing what the AI in the short run can do for us and appreciate all the due diligence on helping us get everything transferred.","index":521,"end_time":1714.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1704.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of course.","index":522,"end_time":1715.289,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1714.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":523,"end_time":1715.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1715.289,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"More than happy to do it.","index":524,"end_time":1716.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1715.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll have that compilation video for you guys tomorrow.","index":525,"end_time":1719.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1716.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":526,"end_time":1721.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll see you guys Friday.","index":527,"end_time":1722.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1721.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got you feedback back on Friday morning to anticipate being on pace to.","index":528,"end_time":1729.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1722.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To be able to do the teaser next week.","index":529,"end_time":1731.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1729.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":530,"end_time":1732.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1731.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Keep working through the other asset packages and continue to send them your way.","index":531,"end_time":1737.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1732.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But we''re making progress.","index":532,"end_time":1739.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''re getting through them.","index":533,"end_time":1740,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1739.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":534,"end_time":1740.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then lastly, I did want to ask because our usual meeting, and I think, I think it would be our last or our second to last meeting falls on Christmas Eve Eve.","index":535,"end_time":1753.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m assuming nobody probably wants to do that.","index":536,"end_time":1756.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1753.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we had canceled that last week.","index":537,"end_time":1760.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1758.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think maybe we did.","index":538,"end_time":1762.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1761.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":539,"end_time":1763.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1762.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So do we think we need something or should we hold off and get through Friday and then decide?","index":540,"end_time":1767.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I think let''s.","index":541,"end_time":1769.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s meet Friday if we need to have a meeting next week more than open.","index":542,"end_time":1772.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1769.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only day that we''re closed.","index":543,"end_time":1774.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1772.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, Natalie, actually, you might have.","index":544,"end_time":1775.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1774.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some days off, but we''re closed on the 25th and the 1st.","index":545,"end_time":1779.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1775.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the only.","index":546,"end_time":1779.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1779.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":547,"end_time":1781.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1780.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":548,"end_time":1782,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":549,"end_time":1782.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1782.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And we''re kind of.","index":550,"end_time":1783.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1782.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Julia and Rachel and I are around.","index":551,"end_time":1785.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1783.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We have, like, bits and bobs off, but we''re holding down the fort, so.","index":552,"end_time":1791.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1786,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree with that.","index":553,"end_time":1792.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":554,"end_time":1792.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1792.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s get through Friday and see what we think we need.","index":555,"end_time":1794.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1792.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":556,"end_time":1795.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1794.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we do have our meeting on the 31st.","index":557,"end_time":1797.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1795.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want to hold that for now or.","index":558,"end_time":1799.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1797.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s hold that for now, but we can look at that as well, because I think for sure we''re going to want to meet at least one more time.","index":559,"end_time":1805.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1800.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Anopholy switch to.","index":560,"end_time":1807.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1806.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just look at what are the metrics doing on AI and then to button anything up.","index":561,"end_time":1811.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1807.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m not working on the 31st.","index":562,"end_time":1814.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1811.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I would say.","index":563,"end_time":1817.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I would need to do.","index":564,"end_time":1819.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1818.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I. I would need to bump it up to the 29th or the 30th.","index":565,"end_time":1823.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1819.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So let''s just see.","index":566,"end_time":1824.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1823.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let''s just make that a point on the agenda on Friday.","index":567,"end_time":1827.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1824.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":568,"end_time":1829.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1828.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll do.","index":569,"end_time":1829.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1829.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":570,"end_time":1830.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1829.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right.","index":571,"end_time":1831.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thanks, everybody.","index":572,"end_time":1831.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1831.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":573,"end_time":1832.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1831.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great rest of your day.","index":574,"end_time":1833.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":575,"end_time":1834.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1833.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You too.","index":576,"end_time":1835.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1834.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"}],"dateString":"2025-12-17T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1","participants":["nancie@noeticconsultants.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,samantha@noeticconsultants.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,rachel@noeticconsultants.com,julia@noeticconsultants.com","nancie@noeticconsultants.com","samantha@noeticconsultants.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","rachel@noeticconsultants.com","julia@noeticconsultants.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC4WAEMBHQY49MHWB0RVE843","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed podcast scheduling through February; older recordings prioritized for faster release post-holiday.","Compilation video delivery set for December 18, with teaser clip planned before New Year launch.","AI campaign to go live immediately and run through December 31; asset handoff process clarified.","Landing page and tools transferred or in process; team confirmed WordPress integration and access flow.","Team discussed future guest promotion tactics to increase post-launch engagement and podcast reach."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re making progress. We''re getting through them.","speaker":"Rachel Curtis"},{"quote":"We''ll have that compilation video for you guys tomorrow.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Let''s let it roll... turn it on today and let''s just see what we got.","speaker":"nancieruder"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","handoff","campaign","scheduling"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-17T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Release Schedule**\n\nThe team is accelerating podcast releases to clear backlog by end of March and improve audience engagement.\n\n- **Podcast episodes recorded on January 21 and February 4** have been scheduled for release to speed up backlog clearance (08:25)\n    - Rachel Curtis confirmed the team reordered episodes based on recording dates to prioritize older content\n    - The goal is to release summer episodes faster after holiday compilations to maintain momentum\n    - This tighter schedule addresses previous delays and aims to increase audience retention through consistent posting\n    - Rachel and Julia will keep updating release dates as progress continues\n\n- **Compilation video will be completed by January 18 and reviewed on January 19** to prep for a teaser launch next week (11:01)\n    - Rachel suggested teasing a clip the week before full launch for two weeks during early January\n    - The teaser and full video rollout plan aligns with holiday timing to maximize visibility\n    - Friday’s 30-minute review meeting is set to finalize marketing details and asset preparation\n    - This approach supports continuous engagement during a typically slow season\n\n- **Increasing podcast guest promotional support to boost reach** was recommended (21:29)\n    - Rachel proposed providing guests with clear promotional assets and instructions for sharing\n    - Colin agreed that setting expectations for tagging and sharing could amplify audience growth\n    - This formalizes guest involvement as part of the podcast marketing framework\n    - The team plans to implement this to maximize each episode’s impact\n\n## **AI Campaign Launch and Management**\n\nThe AI marketing campaign will launch immediately with a 10-day managed run and ongoing asset use planned.\n\n- **Decision to launch the AI campaign now with a cutoff on December 31** to test early engagement during the holiday period (16:38)\n    - Nancy requested the campaign start immediately with the ability to pause at year-end\n    - Colin confirmed the campaign tools (Smart Lead for email and Heyreach for LinkedIn) are ready for handoff\n    - The initial run will serve as a test to gather early performance data during a slower week\n    - Follow-up discussions on campaign management and tool subscriptions are scheduled for Friday\n\n- **Landing page for AI campaign is live but hidden from site navigation and accessible via direct link** (17:25)\n    - Colin confirmed the page is on the WordPress site and ready for use in outreach\n    - Nancy requested the direct URL for easy insertion into email templates and LinkedIn messages\n    - This setup allows controlled traffic flow while keeping the page ready for future navigation inclusion\n    - The team is monitoring user engagement as a leading indicator for AI campaign interest\n\n- **Account transfers and tool subscriptions for campaign management are under review** (19:40)\n    - Colin noted Riverside cannot be transferred due to account linking, but Bussprout and Adroll transfers are in progress\n    - Nancy emphasized the need to list tools with their functions to decide on subscriptions versus pausing\n    - Riverside is confirmed at Business Premium level with all features and discounted pricing due to volume\n    - Final decisions on tool ownership and outsourcing will be made after further internal discussions with Tiffany\n\n## **Platform and Tool Management**\n\nThe team is aligning on platform ownership and feature retention to ensure continuity and cost efficiency.\n\n- **Riverside access will end on January 31, requiring downloads of final assets before then** (22:50)\n    - Rachel confirmed downloading episodes from Pulse while Riverside remains active\n    - Colin will send detailed shutdown timelines and last request deadlines via email\n    - This ensures no loss of content and smooth transition as accounts transfer or close\n    - The team is preparing for this transition to avoid operational disruptions\n\n- **Riverside’s Business Premium tier provides early access to features including AI tools** (24:34)\n    - Nancy sought confirmation on feature levels and discounts for annual payment\n    - Colin clarified all client accounts are Business Premium with ongoing feature updates and discounts\n    - This ensures the team retains full functionality without feature gaps post-transfer\n    - Understanding subscription terms helps inform budgeting and renewal strategies\n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Coordination**\n\nUpcoming meetings are being adjusted around holidays to maintain focus on deliverables without overloading the team.\n\n- **The team agreed to hold the next meeting on Friday and reconsider meetings during holiday weeks** (29:01)\n    - Colin noted closures on December 25 and January 1; team members have partial availability\n    - Nancy suggested canceling the December 22 meeting and possibly moving the December 31 meeting earlier if needed\n    - The focus will be on reviewing AI campaign metrics and finalizing outstanding items\n    - Flexibility in scheduling supports workload balance during a busy season\n\n## **Strategic Client Engagement: Waymo Opportunity**\n\nThere is promising client interest from Waymo, signaling potential for significant future work.\n\n- **Nancy has a third call scheduled with Waymo on Friday indicating serious engagement** (25:49)\n    - Colin shared enthusiasm, noting Waymo’s strong growth potential and market impact\n    - Nancy highlighted the need for proactive brand reputation management due to mixed public sentiment and competitive pressure from Elon Musk\n    - The team recognizes the sensitivity and complexity of this client’s public image\n    - Decisions on featuring Waymo as a client logo will be made cautiously based on progress\n\n- **Waymo’s tech-driven, rapid expansion requires specialized communication strategies** (26:24)\n    - The client’s aggressive market testing and regulatory challenges present unique messaging needs\n    - Nancy and Colin agreed that thoughtful brand management will be critical to long-term success\n    - This opportunity aligns with the team''s expertise in managing complex tech client reputations\n    - The team is preparing to support Waymo’s evolving priorities as engagement deepens","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast scheduling","Compilation video","AI campaign","Marketing tools transfer","Riverside subscription","Waymo client engagement"],"overview":"- **Accelerated Podcast Schedule:** Team aims to clear podcast backlog by end of March; older content prioritized for engagement.  \n- **Teaser Video Completion:** Compilation video ready by January 18; teaser clips to enhance visibility pre-launch.  \n- **AI Campaign Launch:** Immediate AI campaign launch planned to gather early data; runs until December 31 with management discussions scheduled.  \n- **Riverside Access Deadline:** Riverside access ends January 31; team coordinating downloads to ensure no content loss before shutdown.  \n- **Waymo Client Engagement:** Positive client interest from Waymo; strategic communication is vital due to their rapid expansion and public sentiment.  \n- **Meeting Adjustments:** Upcoming meetings to be rescheduled around holidays; focus on workload balance and reviewing campaign metrics.","action_items":"\n**Rachel Curtis**\nContinue sending podcast episode feedback and updates on asset packages (07:31)\nPrepare for real-time review of compilation video during Friday''s Cred Stack meeting (14:02)\nCoordinate posts and asset preparation during compilation video run post-New Year (14:49)\n\n**Nancieruder**\nCoordinate with Tiffany on financial and logistical closeout to ensure alignment and oversight (06:53)\nApprove compilation video teaser release early next week and full release following week of New Year’s (13:59)\nConfirm AI campaign launch and end date (stop by Dec 31) (16:38)\nConfirm use and access to AI campaign landing page, request URL for outreach use (18:10)\nAssess and decide on subscription renewals or pauses across marketing platforms including Riverside and others; consult with Tiffany for full review (20:08)\nProceed with launching AI campaign immediately and monitor results (25:31)\nProvide meeting availability and preferences for December 31 follow-up and potentially reschedule (29:27)\nUpdate team on Waymo call outcomes and ongoing discussions (25:49)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nManage AI campaign setup, transfer tool access and subscriptions to Noetic Consultants, and assist billing handoff (16:10)\nSet AI campaign close dates to December 31 (17:11)\nProvide AI campaign landing page URL in Zoom chat and follow up (18:24)\nAssist with transfer options of Riverside, Bussprout, and Adroll accounts; liaise with respective support teams (19:41)\nSend detailed email with timeline for campaign asset access, platform sunset dates, and other deliverables (23:06)\nDeliver compilation video by December 18 (10:56)\nAttend Friday’s Cred Stack meeting for compilation video review and discuss scheduling of year-end meetings (14:02)\n\n**Julia**\nCollaborate with Rachel on podcast posts and asset prep (10:15)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"80ac508d-0af9-483b-8059-a20930d7b0bb","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
