  'Meeting Notes: MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards',
  '## **Podcast Production and Release Schedule**

The team is accelerating podcast releases to clear backlog by end of March and improve audience engagement.

- **Podcast episodes recorded on January 21 and February 4** have been scheduled for release to speed up backlog clearance (08:25)
    - Rachel Curtis confirmed the team reordered episodes based on recording dates to prioritize older content
    - The goal is to release summer episodes faster after holiday compilations to maintain momentum
    - This tighter schedule addresses previous delays and aims to increase audience retention through consistent posting
    - Rachel and Julia will keep updating release dates as progress continues

- **Compilation video will be completed by January 18 and reviewed on January 19** to prep for a teaser launch next week (11:01)
    - Rachel suggested teasing a clip the week before full launch for two weeks during early January
    - The teaser and full video rollout plan aligns with holiday timing to maximize visibility
    - Friday’s 30-minute review meeting is set to finalize marketing details and asset preparation
    - This approach supports continuous engagement during a typically slow season

- **Increasing podcast guest promotional support to boost reach** was recommended (21:29)
    - Rachel proposed providing guests with clear promotional assets and instructions for sharing
    - Colin agreed that setting expectations for tagging and sharing could amplify audience growth
    - This formalizes guest involvement as part of the podcast marketing framework
    - The team plans to implement this to maximize each episode’s impact

## **AI Campaign Launch and Management**

The AI marketing campaign will launch immediately with a 10-day managed run and ongoing asset use planned.

- **Decision to launch the AI campaign now with a cutoff on December 31** to test early engagement during the holiday period (16:38)
    - Nancy requested the campaign start immediately with the ability to pause at year-end
    - Colin confirmed the campaign tools (Smart Lead for email and Heyreach for LinkedIn) are ready for handoff
    - The initial run will serve as a test to gather early performance data during a slower week
    - Follow-up discussions on campaign management and tool subscriptions are scheduled for Friday

- **Landing page for AI campaign is live but hidden from site navigation and accessible via direct link** (17:25)
    - Colin confirmed the page is on the WordPress site and ready for use in outreach
    - Nancy requested the direct URL for easy insertion into email templates and LinkedIn messages
    - This setup allows controlled traffic flow while keeping the page ready for future navigation inclusion
    - The team is monitoring user engagement as a leading indicator for AI campaign interest

- **Account transfers and tool subscriptions for campaign management are under review** (19:40)
    - Colin noted Riverside cannot be transferred due to account linking, but Bussprout and Adroll transfers are in progress
    - Nancy emphasized the need to list tools with their functions to decide on subscriptions versus pausing
    - Riverside is confirmed at Business Premium level with all features and discounted pricing due to volume
    - Final decisions on tool ownership and outsourcing will be made after further internal discussions with Tiffany

## **Platform and Tool Management**

The team is aligning on platform ownership and feature retention to ensure continuity and cost efficiency.

- **Riverside access will end on January 31, requiring downloads of final assets before then** (22:50)
    - Rachel confirmed downloading episodes from Pulse while Riverside remains active
    - Colin will send detailed shutdown timelines and last request deadlines via email
    - This ensures no loss of content and smooth transition as accounts transfer or close
    - The team is preparing for this transition to avoid operational disruptions

- **Riverside’s Business Premium tier provides early access to features including AI tools** (24:34)
    - Nancy sought confirmation on feature levels and discounts for annual payment
    - Colin clarified all client accounts are Business Premium with ongoing feature updates and discounts
    - This ensures the team retains full functionality without feature gaps post-transfer
    - Understanding subscription terms helps inform budgeting and renewal strategies

## **Meeting Scheduling and Coordination**

Upcoming meetings are being adjusted around holidays to maintain focus on deliverables without overloading the team.

- **The team agreed to hold the next meeting on Friday and reconsider meetings during holiday weeks** (29:01)
    - Colin noted closures on December 25 and January 1; team members have partial availability
    - Nancy suggested canceling the December 22 meeting and possibly moving the December 31 meeting earlier if needed
    - The focus will be on reviewing AI campaign metrics and finalizing outstanding items
    - Flexibility in scheduling supports workload balance during a busy season

## **Strategic Client Engagement: Waymo Opportunity**

There is promising client interest from Waymo, signaling potential for significant future work.

- **Nancy has a third call scheduled with Waymo on Friday indicating serious engagement** (25:49)
    - Colin shared enthusiasm, noting Waymo’s strong growth potential and market impact
    - Nancy highlighted the need for proactive brand reputation management due to mixed public sentiment and competitive pressure from Elon Musk
    - The team recognizes the sensitivity and complexity of this client’s public image
    - Decisions on featuring Waymo as a client logo will be made cautiously based on progress

- **Waymo’s tech-driven, rapid expansion requires specialized communication strategies** (26:24)
    - The client’s aggressive market testing and regulatory challenges present unique messaging needs
    - Nancy and Colin agreed that thoughtful brand management will be critical to long-term success
    - This opportunity aligns with the team''s expertise in managing complex tech client reputations
    - The team is preparing to support Waymo’s evolving priorities as engagement deepens',
