    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1',
    '{"id":"01KC4WAEM00QVEKVZBJ1K3FNKG","title":"Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)","summary":{"notes":"## **Project Wrap-up and Website Updates**\n\nThe team finalized the core project deliverables and prepared the website for production deployment.\n\n- **A general landing page template for all Zenda builds has been created and staged**, allowing easy duplication for new pages (07:46).  \n    - This template standardizes future page creation and streamlines launch processes.  \n    - The homepage carousel was converted into a global component to enable single updates across all pages.  \n    - Colin confirmed the staging to production push will happen the next day, making the template live on the production site.  \n    - Video assets from Daniela remain outstanding, so corresponding pages are still in draft to avoid incomplete launches.\n\n- **Final deliverables and assets are consolidated in Pulse under a final deliverables tab** (11:19).  \n    - Pulse will shut down on December 31st, so all necessary files must be downloaded beforehand.  \n    - The team reviewed outstanding invoices and confirmed a final deadline of December 22nd for submitting any remaining work requests.  \n    - Colin emphasized the importance of wrapping up all loose ends before the year-end office closure on December 23rd.  \n\n## **Email and Domain Management Strategy**\n\nDecisions focused on domain ownership, email tools, and future campaign management to ensure continuity.\n\n- **The domains were primarily purchased via Mailforge but had to switch due to blacklisting; Inbox Kit paired with Smart Lead is now the main tool** (08:50).  \n    - Colin advised transferring ownership of the Smart Lead account, which holds all domains, leads, and historical campaigns, costing **$94 per month**.  \n    - Edwin will review Smart Lead to assess if it meets their email campaign needs, especially integrating domains with a new tool he’s built.  \n    - The Smart Lead platform offers prospecting lists and stores all previous email contacts, facilitating smoother future outreach.\n\n- **Other tools like Heyreach (for LinkedIn connections) and LinkedIn ad campaigns are in use but require no immediate transfer** (11:41).  \n    - Heyreach data upload to LinkedIn is in progress and expected to complete shortly, improving contact matching.  \n    - Colin confirmed no current need to take over AdRoll or Active accounts, though transfers remain an option if desired.\n\n## **LinkedIn Advertising Performance and Audience Insights**\n\nLinkedIn campaigns were optimized to control costs and target high-value roles, yielding qualified leads.\n\n- **Switching to a manual bid strategy reduced cost per click to about $9, which is low for LinkedIn’s B2B platform** (12:23).  \n    - The most effective ad featured a woman looking at her screen and generated **two leads** this month sent to HubSpot.  \n    - Top call-to-actions driving engagement were \"Claim your spot\" and \"Take the AI survey.\"  \n    - Despite one lead being a potential bot, the audience built was highly targeted at **71,000 professionals** based on job titles, industries, and interests.\n\n- **Engagement peaked among Chief Technical Officers, VP of Product, and Chief Product Officers, indicating strong alignment with decision-makers** (13:29).  \n    - Colin highlighted the campaign’s success in reaching the right roles compared to competitors, achieving about **7% audience depth**.  \n    - The LinkedIn audiences and campaign assets are fully configured and remain under client control for future use.\n\n## **Offboarding Timeline and Final Meeting Scheduling**\n\nClear deadlines and meeting plans were set to ensure a smooth transition and closure of collaboration.\n\n- **The final day to submit work requests is December 22nd, with the team closing offices on December 23rd through January 1st** (15:59).  \n    - A final 15-minute meeting is scheduled for December 23rd at 11:00 AM Eastern to address any last questions and deliver closing remarks.  \n    - Colin will cancel the following week’s meeting to respect the holiday schedule and finalize the offboarding.  \n    - Edwin committed to reviewing Smart Lead and domain needs before the 23rd and will communicate any additional requests promptly.\n\n- **The team agreed to keep deliverables and platform handoff discussions open until the final meeting** (16:56).  \n    - Colin offered support to liaise with any vendor support teams if Edwin requests further assistance with tool transfers.  \n    - The offboarding plan ensures all assets, domains, and campaign data remain accessible for the client after project closure.\n\n## **Strategic Reflections and Next Steps**\n\nTeam members shared practical concerns and aligned on the final phase of the engagement.\n\n- **Edwin expressed caution about continuing email campaigns and domain use depending on platform capabilities and cost-effectiveness** (15:30).  \n    - He is evaluating the need for ongoing email sends before committing to Smart Lead subscription fees.  \n    - Colin supported a flexible approach, emphasizing that the client controls what tools to maintain based on evolving business needs.\n\n- **Misty confirmed the team’s year-end office closure from December 23rd through January 1st, highlighting the importance of finalizing tasks soon** (15:59).  \n    - This closure influences final timelines and meeting availability, prompting the December 23rd wrap-up session.  \n    - Both Misty and Kai indicated no additional concerns at this time, focusing on completing the current scope.\n\n- **Colin plans to review tier updates and share key insights during the December 23rd meeting, ensuring a comprehensive close** (17:45).  \n    - This will serve as a final opportunity for knowledge transfer and to discuss any remaining details before the project fully concludes.","outline":null,"keywords":["Domain management","LinkedIn ads","Email campaigns","Offboarding","Website templates","Pulse platform"],"overview":"- **Project Deliverables Finalized:** Core outputs completed; website updates ready for production deployment, including a new landing page template.  \n- **Pulse Shutdown Deadline:** All final deliverables must be downloaded from Pulse before December 31; wrap-up tasks due by December 22.  \n- **Email Tool Strategy Established:** Smart Lead becomes primary email tool; costs $94/month; evaluating its fit for ongoing campaigns.  \n- **LinkedIn Campaign Success:** Manual bidding lowered cost per click to $9; engaged 71,000 professionals, especially decision-makers in tech.  \n- **Final Meeting Scheduled:** Last work request due by December 22; final wrap-up meeting on December 23 at 11 AM Eastern.  \n- **Year-End Closure Reminder:** Team will be unavailable from December 23 to January 1; urge to finalize tasks before closure.","action_items":"\n**Edwin Huertas**\nReview Smart Lead domains and decide on continued usage or transfer (09:34)\nVerify final collateral designs and assets availability on Pulse (11:14)\nAttend final wrap-up meeting on 12/23 at 11:00 am ET and bring any last questions (16:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nAssist with domain and Smart Lead account transfer if needed (09:30)\nPush staging Zenda template and homepage carousel to production site (14:40)\nCoordinate final deliverables on Pulse and confirm outstanding invoices (10:56)\nPrepare final tiers presentation for 12/23 meeting (17:50)\nCancel the meeting scheduled after 12/23 (17:38)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nConfirm office closure schedule and communicate to the team (15:52)\nParticipate in final 12/23 wrap-up meeting (16:55)\n"},"duration":18.06999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Misty Smith"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Edwin Huertas"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":204.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":235.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ah, good.","index":2,"end_time":237.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.17,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Do we know who''s joining the call?","index":3,"end_time":255.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.93,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is it just that when they all accepted, but they''ve declined the next two weeks?","index":4,"end_time":261.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":5,"end_time":281.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":6,"end_time":338.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Hi, Misty.","index":7,"end_time":340.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":8,"end_time":341.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.95,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":9,"end_time":343.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you?","index":10,"end_time":344.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":11,"end_time":345.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s gray sweatshirt day.","index":12,"end_time":346.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"There you go.","index":13,"end_time":347.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":347.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, goodness.","index":14,"end_time":351.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"How''s the week been so far?","index":15,"end_time":353.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s been all right.","index":16,"end_time":355.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.31,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Been busy.","index":17,"end_time":356.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.83,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But when are they not?","index":18,"end_time":359.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":360.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I guess if there was ever a time where you maybe think it wouldn''t be so busy, it would be right now.","index":20,"end_time":364.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re gonna.","index":21,"end_time":367.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.52,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Well, we.","index":22,"end_time":368.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.84,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We''re at least close Wednesday through the 1st, so I think everybody''s scrambling to make sure all their.","index":23,"end_time":377.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.4,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All your year and stuff is tied up.","index":24,"end_time":380.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":381.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":26,"end_time":383.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":383.2,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hey, Edwin.","index":27,"end_time":384.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":28,"end_time":385.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.19,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Hi.","index":29,"end_time":386.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":386.23,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":30,"end_time":387.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How.","index":31,"end_time":388.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How did everything go with your mom?","index":32,"end_time":391.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you don''t mind sharing?","index":33,"end_time":393.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want to Oversight.","index":34,"end_time":394.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":393.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it went well, I think, relatively Monday, when was good?","index":35,"end_time":398.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":394.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"They say Wednesday today.","index":36,"end_time":399.829,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":398.67,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Went Monday, Went back to the hospital.","index":37,"end_time":402.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":399.829,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"They did a lot of things.","index":38,"end_time":403.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":402.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And now she''s back there again today.","index":39,"end_time":406.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":403.99,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But I''m.","index":40,"end_time":407.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":406.59,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m in Richmond, so there''s a couple more things that they have to check, and I think they''re gonna have another surgery going next week, which is interesting because we didn''t think we have an extra one, but I''m back to Richmond.","index":41,"end_time":420.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":407.11,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m not sure I''m gonna go back to Ecuador.","index":42,"end_time":422.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":420.06,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"My hope is that they figure it out.","index":43,"end_time":425.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":422.18,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know they will.","index":44,"end_time":426.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":425.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":429.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":46,"end_time":429.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you for asking.","index":47,"end_time":430.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":429.46,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":48,"end_time":430.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":431.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":430.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Things are moving, definitely.","index":50,"end_time":434.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":432.58,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":434.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, keep her in my thoughts.","index":52,"end_time":436.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":434.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":53,"end_time":436.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":436.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Of course.","index":54,"end_time":437.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":55,"end_time":439.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I see Kai''s connecting as well.","index":56,"end_time":440.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":439.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":57,"end_time":443.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Did you guys get hit with some snow in Richmond?","index":58,"end_time":447.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not the last couple of days, but.","index":59,"end_time":451.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Last week was a little crazy, wasn''t it?","index":60,"end_time":453.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":451.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last week and the week before, I think.","index":61,"end_time":455.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, we had some snow.","index":62,"end_time":458.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.82,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":63,"end_time":460.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":461.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":65,"end_time":462.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Kai, how''s it going?","index":66,"end_time":463.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":67,"end_time":465.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"How are you, Colin?","index":68,"end_time":466.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.47,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":69,"end_time":467.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":70,"end_time":467.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":71,"end_time":468.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, okay, we''ll.","index":72,"end_time":470.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":469.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll touch on the.","index":73,"end_time":471.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":470.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your guys office closure at the end.","index":74,"end_time":474.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we will go through our deck today.","index":75,"end_time":481.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So wrapping up everything.","index":76,"end_time":483.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":482.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll go through just some final.","index":77,"end_time":488,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Project wrap up and updates that we have and then have the offboarding information.","index":78,"end_time":493.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":488,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As well to go through.","index":79,"end_time":494.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can touch on your domain question.","index":80,"end_time":496.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":494.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And everything like that.","index":81,"end_time":497.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have built a general landing.","index":82,"end_time":501.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":498.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Page for any of the Zenda builds.","index":83,"end_time":503.359,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that is built into staging Shako.","index":84,"end_time":506.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":503.359,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are just placeholder images.","index":85,"end_time":509,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it''s built just like this so we can just Duplicate this and.","index":86,"end_time":513.105,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then that''ll be the easiest way to.","index":87,"end_time":514.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":513.105,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Move forward with creating new pages.","index":88,"end_time":515.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions there, Kai?","index":89,"end_time":520.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":90,"end_time":522.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ve also.","index":91,"end_time":524.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":523.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Edwin converted the homepage carousel into a.","index":92,"end_time":526.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":524.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Global so that you can just update it once and it''ll update.","index":93,"end_time":529.639,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great, thank you.","index":94,"end_time":530.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":530.04,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":95,"end_time":531.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So regarding domains, there''s two possible approaches that we can take here.","index":96,"end_time":539.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":534.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one, we had purchased the bulk of domains through a tool called mailforge and then we had to switch everything.","index":97,"end_time":545.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":539.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thing because that server got blacklisted.","index":98,"end_time":546.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we bought other domains through a tool called Inbox Kit that''s partnered with Smart Lead.","index":99,"end_time":551.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are able to work with Mailforge support to get you access to those domains.","index":100,"end_time":557.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The easiest way is actually if you guys just want to take over your Smart Lead account.","index":101,"end_time":562.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It has all of your domains and everything already loaded into it, as well.","index":102,"end_time":566.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":563.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As leads and things like that.","index":103,"end_time":567.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is $94 a month.","index":104,"end_time":570.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":567.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is smart Lead is the name of the tool?","index":105,"end_time":574.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":572.35,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, Smartly AI, that''s the email tool that we''ve used.","index":106,"end_time":577.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let me take a look at this and see if we want to take over that one.","index":107,"end_time":583.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":578.35,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I was actually looking for some email campaign list kind of thing.","index":108,"end_time":588.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":583.87,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":588.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":588.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they.","index":110,"end_time":589.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":588.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They actually have a new feature for prospecting.","index":111,"end_time":591.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":589.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they have lists in there that.","index":112,"end_time":593.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can build, but it''ll have historical campaigns, contacts that we''ve sent emails to and all of the domains already connected.","index":113,"end_time":600.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":593.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we''ve ever sent emails from.","index":114,"end_time":601.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":115,"end_time":602.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we talked last week also.","index":116,"end_time":607.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":605.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"About building out a list of connections from heyreach.","index":117,"end_time":610.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''ve done that.","index":118,"end_time":611.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This has been uploaded to your LinkedIn.","index":119,"end_time":614.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Account and it is going through matching.","index":120,"end_time":616.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":614.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It takes a few days.","index":121,"end_time":617.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was done Monday, so it should.","index":122,"end_time":619.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":617.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be wrapped up today or tomorrow.","index":123,"end_time":620.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":124,"end_time":621.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that is done and.","index":125,"end_time":626.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then just regarding offboarding, just kind of a snapshot.","index":126,"end_time":630.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":626.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in our time working together, you.","index":127,"end_time":632.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":630.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys purchased 1480 points, we''ve delivered 1842 and we have 52 left in working that''ll be wrapped up this year.","index":128,"end_time":640.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":632.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mostly just management.","index":129,"end_time":641.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s one standing outstanding invoice when I wrote this or when we put this together yesterday.","index":130,"end_time":647.519,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if that''s been updated since.","index":131,"end_time":650.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":648.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that is due the 16th, which is yesterday.","index":132,"end_time":654.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I should have updated that to say yesterday.","index":133,"end_time":656.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the final day to submit any worker requests or anything would be the 22nd, giving us just a few.","index":134,"end_time":662.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":657.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Days of buffer to make sure that.","index":135,"end_time":663.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can get it done.","index":136,"end_time":664.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Pulse will be shutting down on the 31st.","index":137,"end_time":669.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pulse has all the assets and images and Everything.","index":138,"end_time":679.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":674.23,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Correct.","index":139,"end_time":679.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":140,"end_time":680.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":141,"end_time":680.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":680.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of our final deliverables are in there.","index":14