tas"},{"text":"Adroll.","index":156,"end_time":720.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":719.26,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know we used it before.","index":157,"end_time":721.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":720.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Nothing in there that we need access to anymore.","index":158,"end_time":724.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":722.3,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Correct?","index":159,"end_time":724.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":724.5,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No, but that is an option.","index":160,"end_time":726.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":725.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you want we can reach out.","index":161,"end_time":727.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To their support team and if you wanted to take over, we could request that they transfer it over to you.","index":162,"end_time":732.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":727.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s just your decision.","index":163,"end_time":733.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":164,"end_time":735.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, those are the only things that I know.","index":165,"end_time":738.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":736.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I remember we needed to look into that.","index":166,"end_time":741.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":738.75,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We were using Active in the last three months.","index":167,"end_time":743.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":741.19,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":168,"end_time":744.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":169,"end_time":745.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just some wrap up analytics.","index":170,"end_time":749.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":746.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we shifted the bid strategy to a manual bid just to have even more control over it versus LinkedIn''s maximum delivery.","index":171,"end_time":755.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":750.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cost per click is $9.","index":172,"end_time":759.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":756.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So seeing that stay relatively low for LinkedIn which tends to be a more expensive platform but obviously for business to business delivers high quality.","index":173,"end_time":767.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as far as the ads that were performing the best is the woman looking at her screen which generated the.","index":174,"end_time":775.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":769.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Two leads this month that we sent over through your HubSpot.","index":175,"end_time":778.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the top call to action on.","index":176,"end_time":780.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":778.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those ads were claim your spot or take the AI survey.","index":177,"end_time":783.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, one of them, it was not a good one.","index":178,"end_time":787.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":783.83,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The other one, she never ever.","index":179,"end_time":790.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":788.07,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t know if it was her or not.","index":180,"end_time":791.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":790.67,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It was no reply either.","index":181,"end_time":794.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":791.95,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Try both ways.","index":182,"end_time":795.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":794.49,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I connected via LinkedIn and I also.","index":183,"end_time":798.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":795.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But the first one is, I don''t know, I think it''s just bot or something.","index":184,"end_time":804.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":798.81,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s open to work and they just start sending random messages.","index":185,"end_time":808.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":805.21,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":186,"end_time":809.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":809.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good to know.","index":187,"end_time":811.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":809.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the audience that we built up for that was 71,000 people.","index":188,"end_time":817.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":814.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Based on job titles, industries and interests.","index":189,"end_time":819.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":817.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''Ve gotten 7% of that depth compared to competitors.","index":190,"end_time":822.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":819.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":191,"end_time":824.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":824.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a highly aligned audience.","index":192,"end_time":825.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":824.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you guys ever want to continue LinkedIn ads, all of that is.","index":193,"end_time":828.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":825.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Built out in your LinkedIn audiences tools.","index":194,"end_time":831.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":828.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as far as the roles that were engaging the most, Chief Technical Officer was the most engaged role that we.","index":195,"end_time":846.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":839.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Saw but also a lot from VP.","index":196,"end_time":848.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":846.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of Product and Chief Product Officers.","index":197,"end_time":850.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So definitely getting in front of the Right, people.","index":198,"end_time":856.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that is.","index":199,"end_time":859.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is everything that we had as we''re closing up.","index":200,"end_time":862.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":201,"end_time":864.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":863.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"As far as the website, there any changes that are still pending?","index":202,"end_time":870.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":866.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know you mentioned at the beginning.","index":203,"end_time":871.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":870.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I didn''t pay attention.","index":204,"end_time":873.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":871.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Just.","index":205,"end_time":874.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":206,"end_time":876.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just the Zenda.","index":207,"end_time":877.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":876.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we built out that template.","index":208,"end_time":878.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":877.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once we push staging to production.","index":209,"end_time":881.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tomorrow, that''ll be also template on the production site and same with the homepage carousel.","index":210,"end_time":886.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":881.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":211,"end_time":887.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":886.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The template is a template.","index":212,"end_time":888.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":887.27,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No, there''s no page because we''re still missing videos from Daniela, I guess.","index":213,"end_time":891.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":888.75,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And correct.","index":214,"end_time":892.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":891.95,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We''ve kept that in draft every time we push it.","index":215,"end_time":895.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":216,"end_time":896.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":895.51,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That works.","index":217,"end_time":896.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":896.15,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":218,"end_time":898.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":898.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think those are the only things.","index":219,"end_time":899.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":898.55,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Anything else, Mr. Kai, that you think about right now?","index":220,"end_time":902.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":899.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know we have until the 22nd for anything that we might.","index":221,"end_time":906.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":902.55,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":222,"end_time":906.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":906.07,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":223,"end_time":909.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.64,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think of.","index":224,"end_time":909.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.04,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I can''t think of anything else at this juncture.","index":225,"end_time":913.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.84,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Nope, me neither.","index":226,"end_time":914.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":914.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right, so.","index":227,"end_time":917.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":916,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":228,"end_time":920.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Edwin, just let me know on the platforms if you want anything else, if you want me to work through.","index":229,"end_time":924.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":920.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any support teams for anything else, or if you reach a decision on Smart Lead.","index":230,"end_time":929.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I look into the Smart Lead.","index":231,"end_time":932.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":930.56,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If all of the domains are there.","index":232,"end_time":934.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":932.48,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I was just looking for a domain that I can connect to another tool that I was.","index":233,"end_time":938.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":934.96,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I built recently.","index":234,"end_time":939.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":938.64,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And I do want to use an email one, but if I don''t see a need on our plan to continue sending emails, then might not be needed anymore.","index":235,"end_time":951.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":939.88,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Understood.","index":236,"end_time":952.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":237,"end_time":953.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Misty, you mentioned you guys are closed.","index":238,"end_time":956.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":953.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was it the 23rd through the rest of the year?","index":239,"end_time":959.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":956.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The 23rd is our last day in the office.","index":240,"end_time":962.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959.4,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, 24th through the first.","index":241,"end_time":965.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.68,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So unless we reschedule for Monday or.","index":242,"end_time":971.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":968.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tuesday of next week, then this would.","index":243,"end_time":973.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":971.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be our last meeting.","index":244,"end_time":974.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":973.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is it Monday?","index":245,"end_time":978.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":977.08,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Tuesday?","index":246,"end_time":978.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":978.24,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Is it 21st?","index":247,"end_time":979.456,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":978.56,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"22nd?","index":248,"end_time":980.008,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":979.567,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"22Nd, 23rd, 23rd.","index":249,"end_time":981.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.119,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could even just have a placeholder.","index":250,"end_time":986.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":984.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On if you guys want to go through any questions.","index":251,"end_time":988,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if not, then we can just remove it.","index":252,"end_time":989.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":988,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do the 23rd calling just to make sure nothing else.","index":253,"end_time":993.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":989.96,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I mean, nothing else needed.","index":254,"end_time":996.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":993.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know you said 22nd, but if I have anything else.","index":255,"end_time":1000.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":996.49,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I looked into this final and two things that I''m really worried.","index":256,"end_time":1003.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1000.01,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Worry, not worry.","index":257,"end_time":1004.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1003.77,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Looking into main Forge or Smart Lead and the any collateral designs, assets, anything that we don''t have that''s in your.","index":258,"end_time":1015.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1004.89,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"On the pulse.","index":259,"end_time":1016.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1015.69,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yep.","index":260,"end_time":1017.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1016.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll try to get through this week and then if we think about anything else, then I''ll get back to you.","index":261,"end_time":1024.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1017.53,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll final close 20 minutes saying goodbyes, happy holidays, and every other message you may think about.","index":262,"end_time":1031.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1025.09,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"On the 23rd.","index":263,"end_time":1031.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1031.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":264,"end_time":1033.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1032.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What time on the 23rd would work for you guys?","index":265,"end_time":1035.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1033.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have 11:00am or 2:00pm Eastern time.","index":266,"end_time":1041.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1035.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s do 11:00am okay.","index":267,"end_time":1043.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1041.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And you said to just reduce that maybe to 30 minutes?","index":268,"end_time":1046.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1043.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, 15.","index":269,"end_time":1047.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1046.7,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":270,"end_time":1048.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1048.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that works.","index":271,"end_time":1054.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1052.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":272,"end_time":1057.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll delete the one for the week after.","index":273,"end_time":1059.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":1061.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1060.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":275,"end_time":1065.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, then we don''t have to do our goodbyes.","index":276,"end_time":1069.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1065.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t want to show you guys my tiers right now.","index":277,"end_time":1071.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1069.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll save them for our 15 minute meeting on Tuesday.","index":278,"end_time":1074.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1072.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s do that.","index":279,"end_time":1075.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1074.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":280,"end_time":1076.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.9,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Thank you, Nina.","index":281,"end_time":1077.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1076.38,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you guys for everything.","index":282,"end_time":1077.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1077.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-17T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1","participants":["kylee.anger@shockoe.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,edwin@shockoe.com,misty.smith@shockoe.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","kylee.anger@shockoe.com","edwin@shockoe.com","misty.smith@shockoe.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC4WAEM00QVEKVZBJ1K3FNKG","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Delivered 1842 of 1480 purchased points; only 52 in progress to complete by year end.","Edwin confirmed Pulse holds all final assets and downloads for post-project handoff.","Smart Lead account includes connected domains, leads, and historical email campaigns.","LinkedIn campaign shifted to manual bid; cost per click stable at $9 with quality leads.","Template and homepage carousel pushing to production tomorrow; Zenda page still in draft."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''ve delivered 1842 and we have 52 left in working that''ll be wrapped up this year.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Pulse will be shutting down on the 31st.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"The cost per click is $9... but obviously for business to business delivers high quality.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","handoff","ads","tools","offboarding"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-17T23:35:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Project Wrap-up and Website Updates**\n\nThe team finalized the core project deliverables and prepared the website for production deployment.\n\n- **A general landing page template for all Zenda builds has been created and staged**, allowing easy duplication for new pages (07:46).  \n    - This template standardizes future page creation and streamlines launch processes.  \n    - The homepage carousel was converted into a global component to enable single updates across all pages.  \n    - Colin confirmed the staging to production push will happen the next day, making the template live on the production site.  \n    - Video assets from Daniela remain outstanding, so corresponding pages are still in draft to avoid incomplete launches.\n\n- **Final deliverables and assets are consolidated in Pulse under a final deliverables tab** (11:19).  \n    - Pulse will shut down on December 31st, so all necessary files must be downloaded beforehand.  \n    - The team reviewed outstanding invoices and confirmed a final deadline of December 22nd for submitting any remaining work requests.  \n    - Colin emphasized the importance of wrapping up all loose ends before the year-end office closure on December 23rd.  \n\n## **Email and Domain Management Strategy**\n\nDecisions focused on domain ownership, email tools, and future campaign management to ensure continuity.\n\n- **The domains were primarily purchased via Mailforge but had to switch due to blacklisting; Inbox Kit paired with Smart Lead is now the main tool** (08:50).  \n    - Colin advised transferring ownership of the Smart Lead account, which holds all domains, leads, and historical campaigns, costing **$94 per month**.  \n    - Edwin will review Smart Lead to assess if it meets their email campaign needs, especially integrating domains with a new tool he’s built.  \n    - The Smart Lead platform offers prospecting lists and stores all previous email contacts, facilitating smoother future outreach.\n\n- **Other tools like Heyreach (for LinkedIn connections) and LinkedIn ad campaigns are in use but require no immediate transfer** (11:41).  \n    - Heyreach data upload to LinkedIn is in progress and expected to complete shortly, improving contact matching.  \n    - Colin confirmed no current need to take over AdRoll or Active accounts, though transfers remain an option if desired.\n\n## **LinkedIn Advertising Performance and Audience Insights**\n\nLinkedIn campaigns were optimized to control costs and target high-value roles, yielding qualified leads.\n\n- **Switching to a manual bid strategy reduced cost per click to about $9, which is low for LinkedIn’s B2B platform** (12:23).  \n    - The most effective ad featured a woman looking at her screen and generated **two leads** this month sent to HubSpot.  \n    - Top call-to-actions driving engagement were \"Claim your spot\" and \"Take the AI survey.\"  \n    - Despite one lead being a potential bot, the audience built was highly targeted at **71,000 professionals** based on job titles, industries, and interests.\n\n- **Engagement peaked among Chief Technical Officers, VP of Product, and Chief Product Officers, indicating strong alignment with decision-makers** (13:29).  \n    - Colin highlighted the campaign’s success in reaching the right roles compared to competitors, achieving about **7% audience depth**.  \n    - The LinkedIn audiences and campaign assets are fully configured and remain under client control for future use.\n\n## **Offboarding Timeline and Final Meeting Scheduling**\n\nClear deadlines and meeting plans were set to ensure a smooth transition and closure of collaboration.\n\n- **The final day to submit work requests is December 22nd, with the team closing offices on December 23rd through January 1st** (15:59).  \n    - A final 15-minute meeting is scheduled for December 23rd at 11:00 AM Eastern to address any last questions and deliver closing remarks.  \n    - Colin will cancel the following week’s meeting to respect the holiday schedule and finalize the offboarding.  \n    - Edwin committed to reviewing Smart Lead and domain needs before the 23rd and will communicate any additional requests promptly.\n\n- **The team agreed to keep deliverables and platform handoff discussions open until the final meeting** (16:56).  \n    - Colin offered support to liaise with any vendor support teams if Edwin requests further assistance with tool transfers.  \n    - The offboarding plan ensures all assets, domains, and campaign data remain accessible for the client after project closure.\n\n## **Strategic Reflections and Next Steps**\n\nTeam members shared practical concerns and aligned on the final phase of the engagement.\n\n- **Edwin expressed caution about continuing email campaigns and domain use depending on platform capabilities and cost-effectiveness** (15:30).  \n    - He is evaluating the need for ongoing email sends before committing to Smart Lead subscription fees.  \n    - Colin supported a flexible approach, emphasizing that the client controls what tools to maintain based on evolving business needs.\n\n- **Misty confirmed the team’s year-end office closure from December 23rd through January 1st, highlighting the importance of finalizing tasks soon** (15:59).  \n    - This closure influences final timelines and meeting availability, prompting the December 23rd wrap-up session.  \n    - Both Misty and Kai indicated no additional concerns at this time, focusing on completing the current scope.\n\n- **Colin plans to review tier updates and share key insights during the December 23rd meeting, ensuring a comprehensive close** (17:45).  \n    - This will serve as a final opportunity for knowledge transfer and to discuss any remaining details before the project fully concludes.","outline":null,"keywords":["Domain management","LinkedIn ads","Email campaigns","Offboarding","Website templates","Pulse platform"],"overview":"- **Project Deliverables Finalized:** Core outputs completed; website updates ready for production deployment, including a new landing page template.  \n- **Pulse Shutdown Deadline:** All final deliverables must be downloaded from Pulse before December 31; wrap-up tasks due by December 22.  \n- **Email Tool Strategy Established:** Smart Lead becomes primary email tool; costs $94/month; evaluating its fit for ongoing campaigns.  \n- **LinkedIn Campaign Success:** Manual bidding lowered cost per click to $9; engaged 71,000 professionals, especially decision-makers in tech.  \n- **Final Meeting Scheduled:** Last work request due by December 22; final wrap-up meeting on December 23 at 11 AM Eastern.  \n- **Year-End Closure Reminder:** Team will be unavailable from December 23 to January 1; urge to finalize tasks before closure.","action_items":"\n**Edwin Huertas**\nReview Smart Lead domains and decide on continued usage or transfer (09:34)\nVerify final collateral designs and assets availability on Pulse (11:14)\nAttend final wrap-up meeting on 12/23 at 11:00 am ET and bring any last questions (16:55)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nAssist with domain and Smart Lead account transfer if needed (09:30)\nPush staging Zenda template and homepage carousel to production site (14:40)\nCoordinate final deliverables on Pulse and confirm outstanding invoices (10:56)\nPrepare final tiers presentation for 12/23 meeting (17:50)\nCancel the meeting scheduled after 12/23 (17:38)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nConfirm office closure schedule and communicate to the team (15:52)\nParticipate in final 12/23 wrap-up meeting (16:55)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"d5869b19-3449-4f55-8beb-2523be51e55d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
