  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)',
  '## **Project Wrap-up and Website Updates**

The team finalized the core project deliverables and prepared the website for production deployment.

- **A general landing page template for all Zenda builds has been created and staged**, allowing easy duplication for new pages (07:46).  
    - This template standardizes future page creation and streamlines launch processes.  
    - The homepage carousel was converted into a global component to enable single updates across all pages.  
    - Colin confirmed the staging to production push will happen the next day, making the template live on the production site.  
    - Video assets from Daniela remain outstanding, so corresponding pages are still in draft to avoid incomplete launches.

- **Final deliverables and assets are consolidated in Pulse under a final deliverables tab** (11:19).  
    - Pulse will shut down on December 31st, so all necessary files must be downloaded beforehand.  
    - The team reviewed outstanding invoices and confirmed a final deadline of December 22nd for submitting any remaining work requests.  
    - Colin emphasized the importance of wrapping up all loose ends before the year-end office closure on December 23rd.  

## **Email and Domain Management Strategy**

Decisions focused on domain ownership, email tools, and future campaign management to ensure continuity.

- **The domains were primarily purchased via Mailforge but had to switch due to blacklisting; Inbox Kit paired with Smart Lead is now the main tool** (08:50).  
    - Colin advised transferring ownership of the Smart Lead account, which holds all domains, leads, and historical campaigns, costing **$94 per month**.  
    - Edwin will review Smart Lead to assess if it meets their email campaign needs, especially integrating domains with a new tool he’s built.  
    - The Smart Lead platform offers prospecting lists and stores all previous email contacts, facilitating smoother future outreach.

- **Other tools like Heyreach (for LinkedIn connections) and LinkedIn ad campaigns are in use but require no immediate transfer** (11:41).  
    - Heyreach data upload to LinkedIn is in progress and expected to complete shortly, improving contact matching.  
    - Colin confirmed no current need to take over AdRoll or Active accounts, though transfers remain an option if desired.

## **LinkedIn Advertising Performance and Audience Insights**

LinkedIn campaigns were optimized to control costs and target high-value roles, yielding qualified leads.

- **Switching to a manual bid strategy reduced cost per click to about $9, which is low for LinkedIn’s B2B platform** (12:23).  
    - The most effective ad featured a woman looking at her screen and generated **two leads** this month sent to HubSpot.  
    - Top call-to-actions driving engagement were "Claim your spot" and "Take the AI survey."  
    - Despite one lead being a potential bot, the audience built was highly targeted at **71,000 professionals** based on job titles, industries, and interests.

- **Engagement peaked among Chief Technical Officers, VP of Product, and Chief Product Officers, indicating strong alignment with decision-makers** (13:29).  
    - Colin highlighted the campaign’s success in reaching the right roles compared to competitors, achieving about **7% audience depth**.  
    - The LinkedIn audiences and campaign assets are fully configured and remain under client control for future use.

## **Offboarding Timeline and Final Meeting Scheduling**

Clear deadlines and meeting plans were set to ensure a smooth transition and closure of collaboration.

- **The final day to submit work requests is December 22nd, with the team closing offices on December 23rd through January 1st** (15:59).  
    - A final 15-minute meeting is scheduled for December 23rd at 11:00 AM Eastern to address any last questions and deliver closing remarks.  
    - Colin will cancel the following week’s meeting to respect the holiday schedule and finalize the offboarding.  
    - Edwin committed to reviewing Smart Lead and domain needs before the 23rd and will communicate any additional requests promptly.

- **The team agreed to keep deliverables and platform handoff discussions open until the final meeting** (16:56).  
    - Colin offered support to liaise with any vendor support teams if Edwin requests further assistance with tool transfers.  
    - The offboarding plan ensures all assets, domains, and campaign data remain accessible for the client after project closure.

## **Strategic Reflections and Next Steps**

Team members shared practical concerns and aligned on the final phase of the engagement.

- **Edwin expressed caution about continuing email campaigns and domain use depending on platform capabilities and cost-effectiveness** (15:30).  
    - He is evaluating the need for ongoing email sends before committing to Smart Lead subscription fees.  
    - Colin supported a flexible approach, emphasizing that the client controls what tools to maintain based on evolving business needs.

- **Misty confirmed the team’s year-end office closure from December 23rd through January 1st, highlighting the importance of finalizing tasks soon** (15:59).  
    - This closure influences final timelines and meeting availability, prompting the December 23rd wrap-up session.  
    - Both Misty and Kai indicated no additional concerns at this time, focusing on completing the current scope.

- **Colin plans to review tier updates and share key insights during the December 23rd meeting, ensuring a comprehensive close** (17:45).  
    - This will serve as a final opportunity for knowledge transfer and to discuss any remaining details before the project fully concludes.',
